char_195_glassb_CN_001.voiceText: Hello, I'm on duty right now. You don't seem happy about it... Do I look that unreliable to you?

char_195_glassb_CN_002.voiceText: I'm not willingly putting myself on the battlefield... but none are as determined to survive as I am. It is my hope that you understand my sentiment.

char_195_glassb_CN_003.voiceText: Zima, I, and the others all come from different schools, but one thing all schools have in common is that they know of Zima's reputation. She's widely known as the Winter General. A cool nickname, is it not? Literally...

char_195_glassb_CN_004.voiceText: How did we escape from Chernobog? Um... you don't really want to know. Sometimes the truth is better left untold.

char_195_glassb_CN_005.voiceText: I'm reading a mystery novel... As a matter of fact, the things it taught me came in use when I fled that catastrophe.

char_195_glassb_CN_006.voiceText: What other genres do I read? Well, books on topics like politics, economics, and dialectical materialism... I also read magazines on making snacks.

char_195_glassb_CN_007.voiceText: My home? You mean where we came from? Obviously we can't go back there. You know as well as I do that there's nothing left there. Even if we rebuild Chernobog, I still...

char_195_glassb_CN_008.voiceText: Rhodes Island is safe. And there are so many books here in your office! If possible, I really don't want to leave...

char_195_glassb_CN_009.voiceText: What about the future? Mmm... No idea. The books didn't say. I hope someone will be able to tell me someday...

char_195_glassb_CN_010.voiceText: Whoa, I never expected this solution! "All the passengers on this train are murderers!"

char_195_glassb_CN_011.voiceText: I am Istina. I'm still a student, but I'm able to use Arts, so I was recruited as a Caster... I know, it is rather strange for a student to be in a place like this.

char_195_glassb_CN_012.voiceText: Do you want me to become stronger?

char_195_glassb_CN_013.voiceText: Do you feel like you understand me better now? Too bad... you actually don't know a thing!

char_195_glassb_CN_014.voiceText: I suppose I must cast a spell that turns this office into fine dust... I'm merely joking. There are too many valuable books in here for me to ever do such a thing.

char_195_glassb_CN_018.voiceText: The team... Hmm, it's somewhat different to what I imagined.

char_195_glassb_CN_019.voiceText: Let's show everyone our determination, earnestness, and burning passion!

char_195_glassb_CN_020.voiceText: May the star of victory shine upon us.

char_195_glassb_CN_023.voiceText: I am not fond of the battlefield.

char_195_glassb_CN_028.voiceText: It's time to teach you a lesson.

char_195_glassb_CN_029.voiceText: Why do they fight... even though they may lose their lives? What do they gain from that?

char_195_glassb_CN_030.voiceText: You want to praise us? Do it now, then!

char_195_glassb_CN_031.voiceText: Those enemies who fled... they probably won't be back again.

char_195_glassb_CN_032.voiceText: It seems our efforts were not enough...

char_195_glassb_CN_033.voiceText: Seems like a locked room where interesting things happen.

char_195_glassb_CN_036.voiceText: It's too noisy here, I'd rather return to your office and read there, Doctor.

char_196_sunbr_CN_001.voiceText: Hey, Doctor! You hungry? I heard your stomach growling from a mile away! It sounded like thunder!

char_196_sunbr_CN_002.voiceText: My shield? I can lift it easily! Here we... go! There, look! Relax, I'm not gonna drop it or anything, so don't run away!

char_196_sunbr_CN_003.voiceText: Those baddies wreaking havoc in our city... unforgivable! I'll smash them with my frying pan!

char_196_sunbr_CN_004.voiceText: Zima said she'll protect me, but I don't need to be babysat! I kept everyone safe with my shield tons of times on our way to this place! What? This isn't a shield, it's a vault door? No it isnnnn't! I can't believe even you're calling it that!

char_196_sunbr_CN_005.voiceText: Doctor, you wanna have a taste of my cooking? Hehehe, soon you'll be able to. I asked Closure if I could take up duty in theSupport Unit's cafeteria!

char_196_sunbr_CN_006.voiceText: Tadaaah! Here comes Gum's specialty: bacon and eggs! So, do you like it? Ehehehe! I can't control how rare it gets on the battlefield, but it normally turns out perfect!

char_196_sunbr_CN_007.voiceText: Me and the other 4 haven't always been a group, you know.

char_196_sunbr_CN_008.voiceText: Why am I always so cheery? Actually... after the things I've seen... how could I possibly be cheery... But I want my friends to forget about all that awful stuff, and I need to smile a whole bunch to make that happen!

char_196_sunbr_CN_009.voiceText: I... I miss my parents, and I do want to find them. I think about it all the time... but if I leave now, I don't think I can accomplish anything by myself... so... Doctor, could you please teach me to fight? I don't want to be known as the girl who spends all her time in the kitchen!

char_196_sunbr_CN_010.voiceText: Are you sleeping, Doctor? In that case it won't be considered slacking off if I sit around and read a bit, right?

char_196_sunbr_CN_011.voiceText: My name's Gummy! You must be the Doctor. Thank you and everyone from Rhodes Island for helping us! I don't have any special skills, but I'll do what I can as good as I can!

char_196_sunbr_CN_012.voiceText: I can feel my power surging! I might even be able to lift you up, Doctor!

char_196_sunbr_CN_013.voiceText: I'll become a three-star chef in Rhodes Island after the promotion, right? Haha, just kidding!

char_196_sunbr_CN_014.voiceText: I want to do much, much more besides cooking! I don't know if I'm strong enough to do everything you want me to, but I'll give it my all!

char_196_sunbr_CN_018.voiceText: Huh?! You're making me the leader?!

char_196_sunbr_CN_019.voiceText: You just wait for our return, Doctor!

char_196_sunbr_CN_029.voiceText: The enemy should just surrender! With the Doctor on our side, they'll never beat us!

char_196_sunbr_CN_030.voiceText: I don't want to do this... but if we don't fight, the enemy will hurt us!

char_196_sunbr_CN_031.voiceText: Yay! We won! I'm so happy!

char_196_sunbr_CN_032.voiceText: Ughh... I'll try to treat everyone's injuries... Doctor? Is the Doctor okay?!

char_196_sunbr_CN_033.voiceText: Wow, what a big room! It can fit so many people!

char_196_sunbr_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor! I know my food tastes great, but don't eat too much of it! You'll get fat!

char_196_sunbr_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, you want something to eat?

char_147_shining_CN_001.voiceText: Greetings, Doctor... Is there anything you'd like to discuss?

char_147_shining_CN_002.voiceText: You look quite pale. You say your... chest hurts? Don't overwork yourself, please get some rest immediately. Don't be afraid, I'm right beside you. Everything is okay...

char_147_shining_CN_003.voiceText: You've seen my healing Arts somewhere before? You must be imagining things. That's almost certainly the case...

char_147_shining_CN_004.voiceText: The Confessor...? How do you know his name? Sorry, this is a topic I don't wish to discuss...

char_147_shining_CN_005.voiceText: We Sarkaz combined our inherent Arts affinity with the power of Originium to develop new healing Arts, which we've been using for quite some time to tend to refugees.

char_147_shining_CN_006.voiceText: Now? We have nothing left now. The war bereaved us of all hope.

char_147_shining_CN_007.voiceText: My relation with Nearl? Certainly... She's a travel companion, and someone I trust with my own life.

char_147_shining_CN_008.voiceText: In order to bring salvation to those in pain, one must be ready to make the ultimate sacrifice. That's the kind of person Nearl is.

char_147_shining_CN_009.voiceText: Once upon a time, I dedicated my life to following someone who shone so brightly in my eyes. A conspiracy took that person away from me, but this time... I'll make sure my light source continues to shine on forevermore. Even if I die...

char_147_shining_CN_010.voiceText: ...This silence reminds me of those days in my hometown.

char_147_shining_CN_011.voiceText: I am Shining, roaming medic. You say you've seen me before? Perhaps we've passed by each other during our journeys.

char_147_shining_CN_012.voiceText: Power that merely heals wounds... is not enough.

char_147_shining_CN_013.voiceText: I can't save everyone just by being a medic.

char_147_shining_CN_014.voiceText: That's right. I cannot be just a medicI will live on as a defender. That's always been my goal. Doctor, please be a witness to this oath of mine.

char_147_shining_CN_018.voiceText: This is a battle for our own sakes, right?

char_147_shining_CN_020.voiceText: I hope this war will lead to salvation...

char_147_shining_CN_023.voiceText: Our choice is between prosperity or destruction.

char_147_shining_CN_027.voiceText: I'm sad that I must do this...

char_147_shining_CN_029.voiceText: The stronger the enemy, the more motivated we are, and the higher our morale.

char_147_shining_CN_030.voiceText: No matter how many sins one commits, they all turn to ashes when their life ends.

char_147_shining_CN_031.voiceText: Even if we return someday, there is no salvation for anyone here.

char_147_shining_CN_032.voiceText: Victory and loss... these are mere insignificant moments in the endless cycle.

char_147_shining_CN_033.voiceText: I don't mind as long as I have a quiet place to be alone.

char_147_shining_CN_036.voiceText: It's been a while since I've been this calm. I can even hear your heartbeat.

char_147_shining_CN_042.voiceText: How are you feeling today, Doctor?

char_148_nearl_CN_001.voiceText: Salutations, Doctor. May the light be with you.

char_148_nearl_CN_002.voiceText: I request you send me to the most dangerous place available. My shield shall protect everyone.

char_148_nearl_CN_003.voiceText: The title of "Knight" should be a symbol of honor. And yet now, it's been reduced to a mere commodity...

char_148_nearl_CN_004.voiceText: As long as the light continues to guide me, I will not bow before cruelty nor kneel before violence.

char_148_nearl_CN_005.voiceText: I'm grateful as always for your service, Doctor.

char_148_nearl_CN_006.voiceText: The Kazimierzian chivalric spirit should have been the force of salvation for all who suffer in this world. But now, it's nothing more than a rotten legacy, used to the advantage of the rich. Nothing can be more shameful than that.

char_148_nearl_CN_007.voiceText: Shining, too, is a beam of light that guides me forward. She carries the hope that I've always been seeking.

char_148_nearl_CN_008.voiceText: Something flickered in Shining's eyes when she heard the name Rhodes Island. I had no idea what it meant...

char_148_nearl_CN_009.voiceText: In this time and age where the world is plagued by Oripathy, may the ray of hope from Rhodes Island light the way.

char_148_nearl_CN_010.voiceText: Let us embrace this momentary respite.

char_148_nearl_CN_011.voiceText: Margaret Nearl, Kazimierzian Knight... nay, Rhodes Island Operator. I will defend your life and your honor with my shield.

char_148_nearl_CN_012.voiceText: Thank you for granting me power.

char_148_nearl_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you, Doctor. These new powers shall bring relief to those who suffer. This I shall engrave upon my heart.

char_148_nearl_CN_014.voiceText: Shining once said that dawn is still far away. But I believe that, one day, we will revive the dying glory with our very own hands.

char_148_nearl_CN_017.voiceText: I shall protect them from all harm.

char_148_nearl_CN_018.voiceText: I shall not blemish Rhodes Island's name.

char_148_nearl_CN_022.voiceText: I shall do everything within my power for you.

char_148_nearl_CN_029.voiceText: A true knight will not bend to the threat of violence. Now, repent for your sins, in front of my warhammer.

char_148_nearl_CN_030.voiceText: Let's go forward. One day, we will

char_148_nearl_CN_031.voiceText: A true knight will not chase after one who's lost their will to fight. Everyone deserves a chance to choose their life path once more.

char_148_nearl_CN_032.voiceText: We must not give up now.

char_148_nearl_CN_034.voiceText: I sense an intru- Oh, Doctor?!

char_148_nearl_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, umm... may I enter your office? I've heard you have a vast collection of literature.

char_179_cgbird_CN_001.voiceText: I apologize... It's my job to attend to you, but my body simply won't move like I want it to...

char_179_cgbird_CN_002.voiceText: I breathed in some Originium toxin once... it damaged my memory and the nervous system in my lower extremities... at least that was what Dr. Kal'tsit told me. So I often wonder... what was my life like before then?

char_179_cgbird_CN_003.voiceText: This little blue bird often comes over and chats with me. Sometimes, I dream about turning into a bird myself... flying free in the skies, without a care...

char_179_cgbird_CN_004.voiceText: Once upon a time, I was imprisoned in an empty room. The only time I ever saw someone else was when they needed my healing powers...

char_179_cgbird_CN_005.voiceText: With this staff in my hand, I can heal people as much as I want. Is this... really an ability I was born with?

char_179_cgbird_CN_006.voiceText: Shining told me that the sins we carry... the crime of starting the war, as Demons... will one day catch up to us and we will have to face our punishment. Those people who imprisoned me said the same thing. But...

char_179_cgbird_CN_007.voiceText: Amiya... I feel a sense of deja vu whenever I see her. Perhaps we met sometime in the past?

char_179_cgbird_CN_008.voiceText: The memories I have are mere fragments. My people... Originium... my mission, the rebellion, the war... but tell me, why are you in one of my memories too?

char_179_cgbird_CN_009.voiceText: Why am I like this? Why did I have to become what I am? Doctor, will you help me find the answers?

char_179_cgbird_CN_010.voiceText: Do you too dream of flying freely through the skies like a bird?

char_179_cgbird_CN_011.voiceText: Liz... that's my real name. Everything else is a just cloudy, indistinct memories...

char_179_cgbird_CN_012.voiceText: Why is there a need for me to grow stronger?

char_179_cgbird_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? I see. It sounds like something to rejoice over. But... I apologize, I don't feel any joy within me...

char_179_cgbird_CN_014.voiceText: Thank you for personally informing me of my promotion, Doctor. But... to me, it doesn't matter as much as the story of the world outside that this little bird is telling me right now.

char_179_cgbird_CN_018.voiceText: I shall do anything you command me to.

char_179_cgbird_CN_019.voiceText: I need only do as the manual said, yes?

char_179_cgbird_CN_020.voiceText: The battlefield... a place where lives are taken...

char_179_cgbird_CN_024.voiceText: It's not my wish to take lives.

char_179_cgbird_CN_025.voiceText: My power is all yours now.

char_179_cgbird_CN_029.voiceText: No matter how difficult the battle gets, I...

char_179_cgbird_CN_030.voiceText: To fight to the very end... that's our destiny.

char_179_cgbird_CN_031.voiceText: Perhaps they've already escaped this cage called fate...

char_179_cgbird_CN_033.voiceText: Rooms... They too are a type of cage.

char_179_cgbird_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor... is this... what is known as "intimacy"?

char_112_siege_CN_001.voiceText: You're still not done assigning tasks? I'll wait a bit longer then.

char_112_siege_CN_003.voiceText: Our meals used to be pretty nice in the past... but the quality's gone downhill since we joined Indra's group.

char_112_siege_CN_004.voiceText: I had a dream... a dream where the sun rises, and in the distance beyond the horizon... there was my hometown. The place I'll probably never get to return to ever again.

char_112_siege_CN_005.voiceText: Before I knew it, I'd become accustomed to this nomadic life... It's really strange. My past self never imagined this is how I'd end up.

char_112_siege_CN_006.voiceText: Gawain and company? I wouldn't say they ran into me, it's more like they picked me up from the streets.

char_112_siege_CN_007.voiceText: I used to stand side by side with Indra and her team when we fought on the streets of Victoria... Looking back at it, I guess that's a rather fond memory to me.

char_112_siege_CN_008.voiceText: Stay on your guard! I know you're already on high alert, but something outside our control could always happen when there's so few of us.

char_112_siege_CN_009.voiceText: If we're ever driven into a corner, then... I have a plan B ready. Should that happen, Doctor, you can be my... You know what, never mind.

char_112_siege_CN_010.voiceText: Oh, you fell asleep... I wonder if you ever dream of your hometown, too.

char_112_siege_CN_011.voiceText: I've passed the strength test, right? So assign me some missions to domy hammer is getting bored! My codename? They call me the Siege. Curious name, but it's got a nice ring to it.

char_112_siege_CN_014.voiceText: Another promotion? All right, thanks... Life is strange like that, you know? Once upon a time, I was the one assigning new ranks to people.

char_112_siege_CN_017.voiceText: Do we really HAVE to fight this battle?

char_112_siege_CN_018.voiceText: You'd better get used to my combat style.

char_112_siege_CN_019.voiceText: For want of a nail... the kingdom was lost.

char_112_siege_CN_020.voiceText: Run while you can. Better to be a coward with a pulse than a martyr with a grave.

char_112_siege_CN_023.voiceText: What a pain in my ass.

char_112_siege_CN_024.voiceText: We'll take them out all at once.

char_112_siege_CN_025.voiceText: Not just anyone can wield my weapon.

char_112_siege_CN_027.voiceText: A warrior must be ready to face death on the battlefield!

char_112_siege_CN_028.voiceText: Your lives are in my control.

char_112_siege_CN_029.voiceText: Your false bravado will do nothing to stop my assault.

char_112_siege_CN_030.voiceText: Those who refuse to surrender don't deserve mercy.

char_112_siege_CN_032.voiceText: I'm... really tired... for some reason. Sorry...

char_112_siege_CN_033.voiceText: Mind if I catch some z's in here?

char_112_siege_CN_036.voiceText: It's too noisy out there for my tastes... I like the silence of your office, though. Let me stay here for a bit, will you?

char_155_tiger_CN_001.voiceText: If you see any enemies, just scream. I'll keep ya safe.

char_155_tiger_CN_002.voiceText: Where's that kid gone off to? Y'know, her... that really tanned shorty who's always trailing our Master... "Morgan" is her nam- Oi! Stop right there!

char_155_tiger_CN_003.voiceText: You scratch my back, I'll scratch yours, let's keep it real. Meaning: if you treat me with respect, I'll do the same for you.

char_155_tiger_CN_004.voiceText: Seems our Master really digs your place. Not every day that happens since we basically never stay in one place for very long.

char_155_tiger_CN_005.voiceText: Whether it's work or whatever else, you've gotta have guts!

char_155_tiger_CN_006.voiceText: Whoa, whoa, chew before you swallow, mate! HEY! SOMEONE BRING US MORE FOOD! This girl's got an empty belly to fill!

char_155_tiger_CN_007.voiceText: That idiot Morgan... she may seem like a slacker most of the time, but she's a great tactician, you know. Gets the job done. Though she likes messing things up a lot too. Tsk...

char_155_tiger_CN_008.voiceText: Doesn't she look brilliant with her hammer in one hand? I'm more curious how she'd look if she were holding a sword, though.

char_155_tiger_CN_009.voiceText: Out with it! Don't beat around the bush, just say it: who do you want dealt with?

char_155_tiger_CN_010.voiceText: Hmph, look at you spacing out like an idiot... Your own bloody fault if a tiger bites you.

char_155_tiger_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Indra. I don't have any of those weird crazy powersI let my fists do the talking. Nice to meet ya!

char_155_tiger_CN_013.voiceText: Promotions are great, almost as great as fighting is!

char_155_tiger_CN_014.voiceText: Don't be afraid. I'll protect ya.

char_155_tiger_CN_029.voiceText: I haven't been this excited in a while!

char_155_tiger_CN_030.voiceText: Not exciting enough. Need more bloodshed!

char_155_tiger_CN_031.voiceText: Tch, some of them fled. Bunch of cowards.

char_155_tiger_CN_032.voiceText: Not bad... I'll get you back for this!

char_155_tiger_CN_033.voiceText: What's up with this room? It's so much narrower than what I'm used to.

char_155_tiger_CN_034.voiceText: Oi! You got a bleedin' death wish?

char_155_tiger_CN_036.voiceText: Come, lemme hug you! Yes, hug you!

char_101_sora_CN_001.voiceText: Heya, Doctor! So, what are you up to? Looks like fun!

char_101_sora_CN_002.voiceText: Are there any karaoke venues at Rhodes Island? It would be great if we had a place to sing the night away when we don't have battles to fight!

char_101_sora_CN_003.voiceText: My duty as an idol was to make my fans happy with my songs and performances. But I'm an Operator now... what should my duty be, then?

char_101_sora_CN_004.voiceText: Doctor, anything I can help with? Don't you underestimate meI'm considered quite physically capable at Penguin Logistics!

char_101_sora_CN_005.voiceText: Yup, my special skill is singing! Let's see, I can do a cappella, lead vocals, choir singing, pop music, and I can even rap, yo! Though I guess that's not a very useful skill for an Operator... If only I had a more practical skill...

char_101_sora_CN_006.voiceText: Ears...? Uh, I can't tell you... even if you ask Texas, she's not gonna tell you! I'll explain if I get the chance someday...

char_101_sora_CN_007.voiceText: You know, Texas actually saved my life and taught me so much I never knew. Which is why... I want to stay by her side whenever I have the chance... I'm uhh, trying to show my gratitude for her, that's all!

char_101_sora_CN_008.voiceText: You think I look upset? Um... it's because... Exusiai went on a mission with Texas today, right? If only I were as skilled as Exusiai, I could...

char_101_sora_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor! Could you teach me to use weapons? My songs have no practical use except for support and encouragement. If I could fight with weapons... Huh? You're not good at fighting either?!

char_101_sora_CN_010.voiceText: ...Texas, are you listening to my songs?

char_101_sora_CN_011.voiceText: Hiiii! I'm the loveable idol from Monster Siren Records: Sora! Oops, sorry, introducing myself like this at Rhodes Island must be kinda weird. Hmm

char_101_sora_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? You mean like debuting as a trainee idol?

char_101_sora_CN_014.voiceText: I feel as excited as I did during my first live performance! I'm just so happy that you trust me this much, Doctor! It's like all my hard work has paid off! ...Huh? My ears? What about them?

char_101_sora_CN_017.voiceText: As a member of the squad, I'll start by learning the very basics.

char_101_sora_CN_018.voiceText: The leader? You mean like being the lead singer?

char_101_sora_CN_019.voiceText: Singing on the battlefield... now that's something new!

char_101_sora_CN_020.voiceText: If only my songs could put an end to all this fighting...

char_101_sora_CN_024.voiceText: All right, let's make some noise!

char_101_sora_CN_025.voiceText: Come on, we can do it!

char_101_sora_CN_029.voiceText: I heard your cheering loud and clear, everyone! Thank you!

char_101_sora_CN_030.voiceText: Awesome! A smashing victory! Texas, were you watching me?

char_101_sora_CN_032.voiceText: I'm sorry... my performance wasn't good enough...

char_101_sora_CN_033.voiceText: This place is much bigger than the dorms at Penguin Logistics!

char_101_sora_CN_042.voiceText: I hope you have a fantastic day, Doctor!

char_103_angel_CN_001.voiceText: Leader! Give us something to do~

char_103_angel_CN_002.voiceText: Leader! Let's throw a party! We can play some hip-hop and eat apple pie! The best life is the party life! No party, no life!

char_103_angel_CN_003.voiceText: Locked and loaded, ready for action! What's the objective today, Leader?

char_103_angel_CN_004.voiceText: Some people believe that money can buy everything. But that saying doesn't apply to me! If I want someone to rest in pieces, no amount of money can save them~

char_103_angel_CN_005.voiceText: My first wish: to receive eight new guns! We angels all have our own guns for defense, but owning just one gun is so lame, right?

char_103_angel_CN_006.voiceText: My second wish... find someone to help me turn off this light over my head!

char_103_angel_CN_007.voiceText: The only reason Texas can live without a care and with all that swag is that she's got me watching over her. That's the obvious truth, right?

char_103_angel_CN_008.voiceText: If you ever run into an angel with black horns oozing ominous vibes, please tell her for me: I've never forgotten her.

char_103_angel_CN_009.voiceText: Us Penguin Logistics girls ain't so bad, right? Wanna come be our boss? Ehehe, just kidding.

char_103_angel_CN_010.voiceText: ...Lord, is this someone we gotta save too?

char_103_angel_CN_011.voiceText: Our slogan is "Long live the Penguin Empire". Are you our client? You can call me Exusiai. I'm nothing like that Lupo ice queen. I'm always down for some fun!

char_103_angel_CN_014.voiceText: Leader... No, savior, I pledge to this gun in my hand to protect you until the very end of this world.

char_103_angel_CN_017.voiceText: Squad combat? I'm very familiar with that.

char_103_angel_CN_018.voiceText: No one makes a better leader than me! You're very sensible.

char_103_angel_CN_019.voiceText: Let's go! Take them all by storm!

char_103_angel_CN_020.voiceText: I already called dibs on the most lucrative real estate in Hell, and you guys all get a share. Rest easy!

char_103_angel_CN_029.voiceText: Wonderful! This is the chance of a lifetime. Charge on!

char_103_angel_CN_030.voiceText: May my hail of bullets bring you eternal peace.

char_103_angel_CN_031.voiceText: News of victory is the sweetest melody to my ears. All right, let's grab some drinks to celebrate when we get back!

char_103_angel_CN_032.voiceText: Even a well-crafted gun will jam sometimes. Life is no different, so don't worry about it~

char_103_angel_CN_036.voiceText: Leader, wanna try out my weapon?

char_201_moeshd_CN_001.voiceText: This here Croissant guarantees yer safety no matter where ya headin', Baws! Oh, 'n payment's upfront! 'Member that!

char_201_moeshd_CN_002.voiceText: Make a buncha money by workin' yer butt off! We can't be livin' in no poverty, after all!

char_201_moeshd_CN_003.voiceText: Yer kiddin'! All yer folks done got such shiny gear on 'em! Lemme have a touch too!

char_201_moeshd_CN_004.voiceText: Boy, I really love orderin' new gear! Feels like I bought 'nuff stuff to fill the whole depot! This what they call a "shoppin' addiction"?

char_201_moeshd_CN_005.voiceText: Every month there's more 'n more bills to pay... 'n that's why I sell some stuff I find on the side! Everythin' I got is cheap 'n high quality!

char_201_moeshd_CN_006.voiceText: If we've gotta transport stuff, might as well pick the easy-to-use and yummy-yummy stuff!

char_201_moeshd_CN_007.voiceText: Baws, Baws! Found this here heckin' tasty thing lyin' around, ya want a bite? Ya ask me, the only thing second to gud gear is gud food!

char_201_moeshd_CN_008.voiceText: Baws, c'mere for a sec, will ya? Take a look at my wares! From fancy clothes 'n everyday items to office supplies and gear, ya name it, I've got it! Buy in bulk 'n ya get a discount!

char_201_moeshd_CN_009.voiceText: Baws, ya deserve a huge thanks! Thanks to yer work referrals, I can buy all the stuff I ever wanted! Yer the best, Baws! I love ya!

char_201_moeshd_CN_010.voiceText: Aw shucks, this gon' be 'nother frugal month...

char_201_moeshd_CN_011.voiceText: My name's Croissant, and by golly yer in luck, Baws! Ya won't find many as good at their trade as I am! I'm strong, last forever, 'n if ya hire me right now, ya get a 20% discount!

char_201_moeshd_CN_012.voiceText: I reckon I'll get more work if I get stronger!

char_201_moeshd_CN_013.voiceText: Thanks much for helpin' me get my hands on better work, Baws!

char_201_moeshd_CN_014.voiceText: Baws, Baws, I made good use of that there bonus ya gave me! Check it out, I done gotten new gear to protect ya better from now on!

char_201_moeshd_CN_018.voiceText: Listen, y'all! Let's do this here mission flawlessly!

char_201_moeshd_CN_019.voiceText: We'll be back with the best results ya ever seen!

char_201_moeshd_CN_020.voiceText: Look at that, the enemy's comin' to donate their gear to us!

char_201_moeshd_CN_021.voiceText: What can I do ya for?

char_201_moeshd_CN_022.voiceText: Time to try this here new gear!

char_201_moeshd_CN_028.voiceText: That ain't gon' work on me!

char_201_moeshd_CN_029.voiceText: Ya reckon the enemy dropped a treasure chest or somesuch?

char_201_moeshd_CN_031.voiceText: Dagnabbit... the enemy got away! My reputation's gon' suffer...

char_201_moeshd_CN_032.voiceText: Aw, shucks... My wallet's gon' take a hit from this loss...

char_201_moeshd_CN_033.voiceText: Ya got any treasure chests hidin' 'round here?

char_201_moeshd_CN_036.voiceText: Baws, Baws, got any cool stuff on hand? C'mon, I wanna see!

char_118_yuki_CN_002.voiceText: Princess Fumizuki is my Master, and you're my employer.

char_118_yuki_CN_003.voiceText: My hobby? Standing on the coast, watching the snow fall.

char_118_yuki_CN_006.voiceText: My weapon? A shuriken, the Silver Wind, made by Eastern Heavy Industries.

char_118_yuki_CN_011.voiceText: I am Shirayuki. Princess Fumizuki told me to assist Madam Ch'en and follow all your orders.

char_118_yuki_CN_014.voiceText: I hope my skills will be of use to you.

char_118_yuki_CN_020.voiceText: A snowstorm will bury this battlefield.

char_118_yuki_CN_029.voiceText: The enemy dies, I advance. I advance, the enemy dies.

char_118_yuki_CN_030.voiceText: My advance and the enemy's demise are as one.

char_118_yuki_CN_031.voiceText: The enemy has fallen. Total victory.

char_118_yuki_CN_036.voiceText: You took care of me. I will always remember that.

char_136_hsguma_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, be at ease. I will keep you safe.

char_136_hsguma_CN_002.voiceText: There have been many new recruits lately, many new faces. You must be on guard.

char_136_hsguma_CN_003.voiceText: No matter what happens, don't forget to use the emergency communication channel. I'll be right there if you call me.

char_136_hsguma_CN_004.voiceText: I sound cold when I talk, you mean? I'm working, after all. I'm much less serious during my off time.

char_136_hsguma_CN_005.voiceText: I seem... reserved? That is how I conduct myself at work, so you'll have to forgive me. During my free time, I am nothing like this, I assure you.

char_136_hsguma_CN_006.voiceText: Rhodes Island doesn't only need combat Operators. It also needs experts in the fields of education, public relations, and more.

char_136_hsguma_CN_007.voiceText: This shield has a name: Hannya. I brought it from my hometown. Its "father" and mine were old friends. Back in the Guard Department, my superiors would always mock my choice of weapon, but together we've proven to them that a shield can be a good weapon, and so can I.

char_136_hsguma_CN_008.voiceText: My Hannya is stained with the blood of many a Lungmen gangster. I thought people would despise me for it, but in fact the ones who looked down upon me began treating me with much more respect after they saw my impressive kill record. Maybe they're simply intimidated by my size? What do you think?

char_136_hsguma_CN_009.voiceText: Have one more glass? ...Oh, you've had enough? You don't have to worry about getting drunk, you know... I can carry you back to your room if you get drunk. What? That simply makes you even more worried, you say? Come on, did you have to say that?

char_136_hsguma_CN_010.voiceText: Hm? Heh. Nothing. Just guarding you, Doctor.

char_136_hsguma_CN_011.voiceText: Hoshiguma, Defender Operator. I will be your shield, your blade, your fortress. Very glad to meet you, Doctor.

char_136_hsguma_CN_012.voiceText: This was made possible by your guidance, Doctor.

char_136_hsguma_CN_014.voiceText: No one can decide where I will go next, and no one can stop me once I make up my mind. And nowI've made up my mind to follow all your orders, Doctor.

char_136_hsguma_CN_018.voiceText: Protecting Rhodes Island is my responsibility too.

char_136_hsguma_CN_019.voiceText: I hope everyone could return safely.

char_136_hsguma_CN_020.voiceText: All who have a reason to fight must also be willing to die for their cause!

char_136_hsguma_CN_023.voiceText: I will not take even one step backward.

char_136_hsguma_CN_025.voiceText: My Hannya will crush you into smithereens.

char_136_hsguma_CN_026.voiceText: Anyone who wants to hurt my friends must answer to this shield.

char_136_hsguma_CN_028.voiceText: Hannya, unleash the rage your father poured into you!

char_136_hsguma_CN_029.voiceText: The harder the journey is, the more character it builds.

char_136_hsguma_CN_030.voiceText: Hurting my friends in front of my very eyes... that's something I cannot condone!

char_136_hsguma_CN_031.voiceText: Are you hurt? I'm sorry, I have failed in my duties.

char_136_hsguma_CN_032.voiceText: Retreat now! I'll take up the rear!

char_136_hsguma_CN_033.voiceText: With my size... it's kind of hard to get through the door.

char_136_hsguma_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, you could at least take a moment to relax while we're on a break.

char_106_franka_CN_001.voiceText: We're changing shifts right now, Doctor. Just ignore me and get on with your work.

char_106_franka_CN_002.voiceText: Back in BSW, I was appointed as a BPRS... you know, Biochemical Protection Response Staff. You can probably imagine what it was like... bulky hazmat suit and all that...

char_106_franka_CN_003.voiceText: Hmm? You think I'm a clean freak? Well, Doctor, I see you're unexpectedly direct! I admire your courage.

char_106_franka_CN_004.voiceText: Some of the Operators' rooms are in dire need of cleaning. For example, the one belonging to that high-and-mighty teacher's pet. What do you think?

char_106_franka_CN_005.voiceText: You want to see the intricate pattern on my sword up close? Sure, hold it tight, then. Don't let goit'll heat up to 2,500 degrees Celcius in 3 seconds! Haha, just kidding! Don't be scared!

char_106_franka_CN_006.voiceText: Stay clear of that room full of chemical haze, toxins and harmful radiation... that's right, I mean Dr. Kal'tsit's lab.

char_106_franka_CN_007.voiceText: You're asking me for advice regarding the prevention of biochemical contamination? Well, for example... always brush your teeth after eating?

char_106_franka_CN_008.voiceText: Liskarm's been looking so flashy since she got her promotion. It's like she's saying "Shoot me here!"

char_106_franka_CN_009.voiceText: Good golly, if this is how free life is at Rhodes Island then I might just quit my job at BSW. Liskarm would be upset, though.

char_106_franka_CN_010.voiceText: There's a mosquito on your arm, Doctor.

char_106_franka_CN_011.voiceText: I'm chemical specialist operator, Franka, here to do my bit to help minimize the pollution wrought by Originium.

char_106_franka_CN_012.voiceText: Techniques like these could be used in all kinds of situations!

char_106_franka_CN_013.voiceText: Wooow, you're giving me a promotion? I'm having a lot more fun here than at BSW.

char_106_franka_CN_014.voiceText: *Giggle*, you want to see my sword at its most glorious? Too bad, Doctoryou're not qualified yet! If you work at it, maybe one day you'll gain the privilege!

char_106_franka_CN_018.voiceText: The best thing about training capable subordinates is that I get to let them handle all the annoying stuff for me.

char_106_franka_CN_020.voiceText: Too bad... these people have already been contaminated. In that case...

char_106_franka_CN_023.voiceText: Offense isn't what I trained for, but hey...

char_106_franka_CN_024.voiceText: Heavily armored enemies are SO scary...! Hah, just kidding!

char_106_franka_CN_029.voiceText: Obsession with power is a fool's game.

char_106_franka_CN_030.voiceText: That was perfect from start to finish. Well done.

char_106_franka_CN_032.voiceText: What's the point of staying here and being all upset? Fall back now.

char_106_franka_CN_033.voiceText: Say, do you have any tea?

char_106_franka_CN_036.voiceText: Want to hear about my time at BSW?

char_107_liskam_CN_002.voiceText: Take all missions seriously: that's the guiding rule for us security professionals.

char_107_liskam_CN_003.voiceText: I'm actually not that good at dealing with people like Franka. I'm not even sure how we became partners in the first place...

char_107_liskam_CN_004.voiceText: There's a strict elimination process before one can qualify for BSW. I'm short, have no outstanding Arts talents, and I'm not from any particularly prestigious bloodline. No one believed that I would be chosen... not even myself, once upon a time.

char_107_liskam_CN_005.voiceText: BSW is a top security contractor and a great fit for me, I think. It's just that Rhodes Island would grant me more freedom.

char_107_liskam_CN_006.voiceText: Isn't it amazing that I got this far? I feel like a real dragon... uh, ahem, forget what I said... anyway, I'm okay with whatever as long as it's helpful for our side in battle!

char_107_liskam_CN_007.voiceText: Thank you, Doctor, for trusting me this much.

char_107_liskam_CN_008.voiceText: People who truly know me always say I'm more easygoing than I seem. Do you think so too, Doctor?

char_107_liskam_CN_009.voiceText: Franka is telling you about our time at BSW again? Aw, come on... don't believe everything she says!

char_107_liskam_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, we're still at work right now...

char_107_liskam_CN_011.voiceText: Defender Liskarm, waiting for your orders. I've participated in multiple special operationsfor example personal protection of VIPs, assaulting fortified positions, rescuing hostages, and clearing out threats. Right now, you are my mission, so I will protect you with everything I have.

char_107_liskam_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you for appointing me to this position, Doctor.

char_107_liskam_CN_014.voiceText: Thank you, Doctor! I will devote all I have into defending Rhodes Island as your trusted Operator.

char_107_liskam_CN_018.voiceText: Understood. I will ask my team members to strictly follow the guidelines and procedures of Rhodes Island.

char_107_liskam_CN_029.voiceText: This is nothing. Franka and I have been through much more intense battles.

char_107_liskam_CN_030.voiceText: All clear. All targets taken down.

char_107_liskam_CN_031.voiceText: All green. The area has been swept.

char_107_liskam_CN_032.voiceText: Emergency squad, retreat with the injured Operators! Everyone who can still fight, follow me and hold back the enemies!

char_107_liskam_CN_033.voiceText: Is this room protected against electrical discharge?

char_107_liskam_CN_034.voiceText: Watch out so you don't get shocked.

char_107_liskam_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, is Franka's treatment still in progress? By the way, you need to rest after your work is done.

char_117_myrrh_CN_001.voiceText: Pardon, but that report you submitted to Dr. Kal'tsit... we could barely read the last few lines. Please don't submit sloppy reports done late at night...

char_117_myrrh_CN_002.voiceText: Wow, there are so many things in here I've never seen before... Oh, sorry, I shouldn't have looked around without your permission... sorry...

char_117_myrrh_CN_003.voiceText: I know my herbs are rather bitter, but I'd like to point out how effective they are...

char_117_myrrh_CN_004.voiceText: Um, Doctor... is Harmonia still not getting any better? ... I see... I'll pay her a visit as soon as I finish work.

char_117_myrrh_CN_005.voiceText: I know my herbs aren't popular because they're bitter... but I don't know how to make them taste better... Oh, you mean I should ask around for tips? B-but... I'm not that good at small talk... I'll do my best, though!

char_117_myrrh_CN_006.voiceText: Harmonia and I would explore all sorts of places together when we were kids. Yeah, we grew up in the city ruins and were really curious about the world outside...

char_117_myrrh_CN_007.voiceText: Harmonia is my oldest friend... and my best friend, too. It's my fault that she got sick in the first place. She may be bedridden now because of Oripathy... but I'll find a cure and bring her back to her old self one day, I promise!

char_117_myrrh_CN_008.voiceText: Ms. Perfumer suggested that I add some spices into my herbs and now they taste much better! I'm so glad I managed to summon the courage to ask her for advice...

char_117_myrrh_CN_009.voiceText: Harmonia says I'm in higher spirits these days. Do you think so too? It's all thanks to you and your timely advice. I wouldn't know what to do without you...

char_117_myrrh_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor... oh, are you asleep? Yay! Now I can look around the office to my heart's content.

char_117_myrrh_CN_011.voiceText: Uh, I'm Myrrh, a herbalist. Dr. Kal'tsit gave me this title... she said myrrh symbolizes the ephemerality of life and wanted me to keep this in mind.

char_117_myrrh_CN_012.voiceText: Thank you so much! This way I'll be able to concoct even better medicine.

char_117_myrrh_CN_013.voiceText: This is called a... promotion? Is that it...? Um, I don't really know much about stuff like that...

char_117_myrrh_CN_014.voiceText: I used to explore secret places and abandoned buildings just like this with Harmonia. The more dangerous the place was, the rarer the ingredients we could find.

char_117_myrrh_CN_017.voiceText: Uh... I'll try my best not to drag everyone down...

char_117_myrrh_CN_018.voiceText: I'll start by doing my best to make eye contact...

char_117_myrrh_CN_019.voiceText: Ah, Doctor, I'm ready to go.

char_117_myrrh_CN_020.voiceText: I'll do my best to make sure no one gets hurt...!

char_117_myrrh_CN_027.voiceText: Here's the medicine. Please, take it!

char_117_myrrh_CN_029.voiceText: We won? Really? Even against those really tough opponents? Wow... you're so cool, Doctor!

char_117_myrrh_CN_030.voiceText: So... was my medicine effective this time? ...Uh, forget it, I'll ask when we get back...

char_117_myrrh_CN_031.voiceText: I had so much to do in so little time... what a relief I didn't mess up too badly...

char_117_myrrh_CN_032.voiceText: The bottles... the bottles are all shattered...

char_117_myrrh_CN_033.voiceText: Uh... I can still smell herbs on my clothes...

char_117_myrrh_CN_036.voiceText: Uh, Doctor... I made some herb soup good for soothing the body and calming the mind. It's just... a bit bitter...

char_193_frostl_CN_001.voiceText: Want to listen to some music? I'll lend you my headphones.

char_193_frostl_CN_002.voiceText: Sorry, please keep your distance from me.

char_193_frostl_CN_003.voiceText: I never imagined that I'd have the chance to become a rescue worker.

char_193_frostl_CN_004.voiceText: I began wielding this axe before I even learned to read.

char_193_frostl_CN_005.voiceText: The songs I like are probably all outdated. Only good for humming to myself when I'm alone.

char_193_frostl_CN_006.voiceText: Don't blinkyou have but one moment to witness this epic battle move.

char_193_frostl_CN_007.voiceText: Want something to drink? My treat. You should relax a bit after work, you know.

char_193_frostl_CN_008.voiceText: I only realized how precious life is after the people around me died one by one. Ironic, huh? I think so, too.

char_193_frostl_CN_009.voiceText: As a mercenary, I just do my job. As for the purpose of my mission and what consequences it'll leave, I don't have a say in any of that. So, from now on, you're in charge of deciding what I'm responsible for.

char_193_frostl_CN_011.voiceText: Frostleaf, former mercenary. From now on, I'm an Operator, and you're my employer. Assign me to any job you want, I can do pretty much anything.

char_193_frostl_CN_013.voiceText: Things are on the right track now.

char_193_frostl_CN_014.voiceText: Whew... not bad. Feeling fulfilled for the first time in a while.

char_193_frostl_CN_018.voiceText: Everyone, go your own way and do your own job.

char_193_frostl_CN_019.voiceText: Perfect, I happen to need some exercise.

char_193_frostl_CN_025.voiceText: My body fluids are not the only thing that's chilling.

char_193_frostl_CN_026.voiceText: Reach further, my rays of light!

char_193_frostl_CN_029.voiceText: I've been through countless battles... seen the carnage, witnessed the silent nothingness at the end.

char_193_frostl_CN_030.voiceText: I remember every enemy I fought. Not a single one of them escaped from my hands.

char_193_frostl_CN_033.voiceText: I'd like... a more private space.

char_193_frostl_CN_036.voiceText: Let's go grab a drink, yeah?

char_129_bluep_CN_001.voiceText: Hey, Doctor. You're glowing today. To see you so well... that's all I could ever hope for.

char_129_bluep_CN_002.voiceText: I prepared an antidote that could nullify the effects of any common poison. I'd like you to take one dose before every battle. Is that okay with you?

char_129_bluep_CN_003.voiceText: Actually, the toxin in my body is an ingredient for some high-quality medicine... that's why Dr. Kal'tsit needs me at her lab a lot.

char_129_bluep_CN_004.voiceText: Hm, why do you keep staring at me? Oh, because my eye color is so rare? Is that a compliment, Doctor?

char_129_bluep_CN_005.voiceText: I'm the one the enemies fear the most. After all, anyone would much rather kill me before I could torture them to death with my poison, right? What really worries me is if my allies might think the same and consider killing me too...

char_129_bluep_CN_006.voiceText: Why am I staring at this cake, you ask? Actually... I baked it for everyone, but no one wanted it... Would you like to try it, Doctor?

char_129_bluep_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, you're always wearing the same outfit. How about I choose some new clothes for you? I pride myself on having pretty good taste! Oh... it's a uniform? So you can't change it? Okay...

char_129_bluep_CN_008.voiceText: I'm "toxic"... so people prefer to stay away from me. But now I have you, Doctor. I'm really happy! Really!

char_129_bluep_CN_009.voiceText: I'm not really that different from everyone else. I may be "toxic," but nothing bad will happen if you touch me. If you could prove this to everyone by touching me yourself, then... maybe everyone will be nicer to me? Doctor, can you... touch my hand in front of everyone else?

char_129_bluep_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor? Oh, are you sleeping? Gotta find a blanket, don't want Doctor to catch a cold...

char_129_bluep_CN_011.voiceText: Nice to meet you, I'm Blue Poison. I'm sure Dr. Kal'tsit must have told you about me. As for how you'd like to use my powers, it's up to you to decide.

char_129_bluep_CN_012.voiceText: I think I hear the sound of poisonous liquid boiling. How very exciting.

char_129_bluep_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you so much... I'm so glad that I get to contribute in all these battles. It's like a dream come true.

char_129_bluep_CN_014.voiceText: Instead of holding back, trying to hide my "toxic" identity... it's much better to accept myself for what I am and try to change my fate myself. This may be just an insignificant thing... but you're the one who helped me understand that... so, thank you, thank you so much.

char_129_bluep_CN_017.voiceText: Great. I'm good at assisting in attacks.

char_129_bluep_CN_018.voiceText: I'd be much better off as support staff. Or else the poisonous liquid inside me might harm you, Doctor...

char_129_bluep_CN_019.voiceText: Everyone, there's no need to stand so far from me...

char_129_bluep_CN_020.voiceText: I prepared a "gift" for y'all. Like it?

char_129_bluep_CN_022.voiceText: Please don't be scared of me.

char_129_bluep_CN_023.voiceText: Don't worry, my poison is not contagious.

char_129_bluep_CN_025.voiceText: My toxins will gradually burn your veins away...

char_129_bluep_CN_027.voiceText: Honey to me, poison to you.

char_129_bluep_CN_029.voiceText: Wiping out conspiracies and evil guys with "poison"... doesn't that seem ironic to you?

char_129_bluep_CN_030.voiceText: I've got a way to melt away all these remains in an instant. Want me to show you?

char_129_bluep_CN_031.voiceText: Good, finished before my clothes got dirty.

char_129_bluep_CN_032.voiceText: How laughable. Felt like I killed myself with my own poison...

char_129_bluep_CN_033.voiceText: Resting when rest is due is helpful for focusing on your work.

char_129_bluep_CN_036.voiceText: D-did you just touch me? C-can you do that again? Please?

char_143_ghost_CN_001.voiceText: Good day. Please allow me a moment of prayer... before I resume my work for the day...

char_143_ghost_CN_002.voiceText: O benevolent angels in Heaven, hear my prayer: please watch over my dreams and protect my soul from the cursed beings of the night...

char_143_ghost_CN_003.voiceText: Ahahahah... Cutting... Cutting things is such fun... Yes, some things were not supposed to be in one piece... Some things were never meant to be in anything but pieces! Ahahahahah...!

char_143_ghost_CN_005.voiceText: Ahah... Why will you not look into my eyes...? It's meaningless to avoid my gaze... because I already know exactly what your heart desires...

char_143_ghost_CN_006.voiceText: I have always, always wanted to bring you to a special place... A place where secrets are imparted...

char_143_ghost_CN_007.voiceText: Wh-what did you do to me...? Why was I made to drink that strange medicine? Who is it that brought me to this place? PLEASE ANSWER ME!

char_143_ghost_CN_008.voiceText: What He said unto me is no falsehood... Dissecting them, dismembering them, disemboweling them... it all grants them salvation...!

char_143_ghost_CN_009.voiceText: We see many things in our dreams that we cannot comprehend... Those things you see are His despairful tidings... And I am His messenger, here to convey this exhortation to you... Ahah...

char_143_ghost_CN_010.voiceText: Hearken... Hear the whispers of His Omnipotence echoing from the depths...

char_143_ghost_CN_011.voiceText: Ahahah... I am Specter, that is what the spirits call me... That kind doctor informed me that I may only receive further treatment by serving Rhodes Island... Yes, of course, my powers are yours to command.

char_143_ghost_CN_013.voiceText: I have no right to go against your will...

char_143_ghost_CN_014.voiceText: Will this position be a new source of joy for me...? Or... will working for you become my life's joy...?

char_143_ghost_CN_017.voiceText: My brothers and sisters, I hope that you are well...

char_143_ghost_CN_018.voiceText: I shall do as you command.

char_143_ghost_CN_019.voiceText: This will be a path paved with sacrifices.

char_143_ghost_CN_020.voiceText: All these lost souls on the battlefield... I offer them to you.

char_143_ghost_CN_021.voiceText: I have waited eagerly for this.

char_143_ghost_CN_022.voiceText: Please let me know the results.

char_143_ghost_CN_023.voiceText: I come from the deep abyss...

char_143_ghost_CN_024.voiceText: You must be the one who woke me.

char_143_ghost_CN_027.voiceText: I care not for you valueless ones!

char_143_ghost_CN_029.voiceText: I have conquered all trials you gave me... Were you watching me?

char_143_ghost_CN_030.voiceText: Please guide these lost souls to peaceful enlightenment...!

char_143_ghost_CN_031.voiceText: None of you shall leave this place!

char_143_ghost_CN_032.voiceText: They shall pay for their sacrilege... They shall pay...

char_143_ghost_CN_033.voiceText: May I ask you to assign me to a room where I can see the night sky?

char_143_ghost_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor... How can you make me so maddeningly happy? Just who are you...?

char_143_ghost_CN_042.voiceText: Who's there... Ah, it's you, Doctor... Ahah...

char_181_flower_CN_001.voiceText: You'd better listen to me, Doctor!

char_181_flower_CN_002.voiceText: This fragrance... how was it? Do you feel all healed? I got the inspiration from Melantha's samples.

char_181_flower_CN_003.voiceText: Thanks for building a greenhouse for my flowers. I think it'll be a good place for everyone to rest.

char_181_flower_CN_004.voiceText: Oh, are you awake? You feel all refreshed, right? My aromatherapy is definitely working. I'm really confident in it!

char_181_flower_CN_005.voiceText: Narcissus, rabbitear iris, kalanchoe, boronia... I always carry seeds of all sorts of flowers on me.

char_181_flower_CN_006.voiceText: Oh, you mean this little one? It's still a baby, but quite helpful for concocting all sorts of things.

char_181_flower_CN_007.voiceText: The society of ants is maintained based on smells. The relationship between perfumers and their clients is the same.

char_181_flower_CN_008.voiceText: You seem to visit the greenhouse a lot these days. Oh, there's some pollen here on your sleeve. Let me wipe it off for you...

char_181_flower_CN_009.voiceText: You seem to have been sleeping for quite a while. What did you dream about, I wonder?

char_181_flower_CN_010.voiceText: Oh, Doctor? Hm, the lavender was much more effective than I imagined!

char_181_flower_CN_011.voiceText: Nice to meet you, Doctor. I'm Lena, a perfumer. Interesting job, right? Did you know it existed?

char_181_flower_CN_012.voiceText: Please check and tell me how I did.

char_181_flower_CN_013.voiceText: The promotion... are you here to tell me about it? Aw, sorry, Doctor... give me a sec... your collar... it's wrinkled, so I smoothed it out. That's all.

char_181_flower_CN_014.voiceText: Fighting when you could have just talked it out... I don't like that kind of unnecessary violence. But I'll still do my best to get used to it for you, Doctor.

char_181_flower_CN_018.voiceText: No matter as a perfumer or healer, I promise to fulfill all your expectations.

char_181_flower_CN_020.voiceText: What kind of battle would it end up being, I wonder...

char_181_flower_CN_027.voiceText: How do you like this smell?

char_181_flower_CN_029.voiceText: I've always believed that victory will be ours as long as you're the one giving orders.

char_181_flower_CN_031.voiceText: Good job, everyone. Get some rest.

char_181_flower_CN_032.voiceText: Too bad we didn't win, but I will not be discouraged because of it.

char_181_flower_CN_033.voiceText: I belong at your side, after all.

char_109_fmout_CN_001.voiceText: Well, Doctor, your tarot card for today is...

char_109_fmout_CN_002.voiceText: Would you like to learn more about your future?

char_109_fmout_CN_003.voiceText: Never forget that the confluences of unknown forces may very well devour us.

char_109_fmout_CN_004.voiceText: Tarot cards aren't divine, all-seeing tools. Instead, we use them for guidance when we feel lost.

char_109_fmout_CN_005.voiceText: Destiny is like the earth beneath our feetno one can escape it.

char_109_fmout_CN_006.voiceText: Humans might never be able to live without the earth... but we can change it. Our actions belie endless possibilities.

char_109_fmout_CN_007.voiceText: There are countless topics for which you can consult the tarot. One of the most common is luck. To change your luck, you must be brave enough to change your fate.

char_109_fmout_CN_008.voiceText: We have a ritual among diviners that's all the rage these days. We call it the "Hand of Fate." Would you like to try it?

char_109_fmout_CN_009.voiceText: It's taboo in the industry to do readings concerning death. But I don't believe death is the endit's the beginning of something new.

char_109_fmout_CN_010.voiceText: Dreams can often enlighten you in strange ways. If you have an enlightening dream like that, you'd best remember every detail, Doctor.

char_109_fmout_CN_011.voiceText: Following the guidance of the arcana, I've finally managed to cross paths with you, Doctor.

char_109_fmout_CN_013.voiceText: I'd already foreseen this promotion in my crystal ball. Haha, just kidding!

char_109_fmout_CN_014.voiceText: You want to know... your destiny, Doctor? Too bad, I can't help you. My mission is not to show you the secrets not meant for human eyes.

char_109_fmout_CN_017.voiceText: Wait a minute, let me predict the results of this battle.

char_109_fmout_CN_018.voiceText: Well then, let me pray for everyone.

char_109_fmout_CN_019.voiceText: Fate is a fickle thing... only the victorious will forever be revered.

char_109_fmout_CN_020.voiceText: I can see the outcome. Victory belongs to Rhodes Island.

char_109_fmout_CN_024.voiceText: Do not attempt to go against your fate.

char_109_fmout_CN_029.voiceText: Does fate have us in a chokehold... or shall we launch the ultimate counterattack against it?

char_109_fmout_CN_030.voiceText: I have moved all of them to the graveyard.

char_109_fmout_CN_032.voiceText: No way... this wasn't the result I saw in the cards...

char_109_fmout_CN_033.voiceText: Bad omens seem to lurk inside this room. May I help you deal with them using my powers?

char_109_fmout_CN_036.voiceText: Want me to do a reading on your future? All right, please give me a minute.

char_109_fmout_CN_042.voiceText: You're blessed by the winds of luck, Doctor.

char_126_shotst_CN_001.voiceText: I sense something familiar. Where are we?

char_126_shotst_CN_002.voiceText: Do you feel the wind from Kazimierz?

char_126_shotst_CN_003.voiceText: Rhodes Island is very different from the places I used to live. There's nowhere to start a campfire here... too bad. Maybe on the deck? I'd like to create a space where everyone can chat and get close to each other.

char_126_shotst_CN_004.voiceText: This mission signup system... How does it even work? I'm really bad at electronics...

char_126_shotst_CN_005.voiceText: There's been lots of new faces at Rhodes Island. I'll gladly lend a hand to help them adjust to the environment.

char_126_shotst_CN_006.voiceText: That Kazimierzian knight... yep, that's right, I already know her. Used to be a shy bookworm. I wonder what made her change this much.

char_126_shotst_CN_007.voiceText: Shh... look who I found! A wild Doctor appeared... gotta catch me one! Oh, did I scare you? Haha...

char_126_shotst_CN_008.voiceText: I sometimes remember those good old days in my hometown in the forest. We had lots of different competitions every year... fun times, fun times. I wonder what my hometown is like now.

char_126_shotst_CN_009.voiceText: I'll always have your back, Doctor.

char_126_shotst_CN_010.voiceText: So you can fall asleep without a care, just like that? Cute.

char_126_shotst_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, I'm Meteor, the archer from the woods. Do you need an Operator who excels in long-distance support?

char_126_shotst_CN_012.voiceText: Archery requires constant practice. No slacking off!

char_126_shotst_CN_013.voiceText: I'm very honored to receive this promotion.

char_126_shotst_CN_014.voiceText: Thank you, Doctor, for approving my skills. I'll continue to do my best to serve you.

char_126_shotst_CN_017.voiceText: Leave the long-distance assisting to me.

char_126_shotst_CN_020.voiceText: Time to show them what we can do.

char_126_shotst_CN_022.voiceText: I've been waiting for a while.

char_126_shotst_CN_023.voiceText: The wind is blowing in the right direction.

char_126_shotst_CN_029.voiceText: No matter how difficult the trials, we'll be able to handle them as long as we work together as one.

char_126_shotst_CN_031.voiceText: All injured members, please stay put, don't move. I'll be right there.

char_126_shotst_CN_032.voiceText: I'm sorry... I didn't want it to end up like this...

char_126_shotst_CN_033.voiceText: It's hard to get used to such a small room after all.

char_126_shotst_CN_036.voiceText: Being at your side feels like basking in the spring sunshine. So warm, so comfy.

char_127_estell_CN_001.voiceText: Uh... w-where should I stand? O-oh, you want me to sit? Then... w-where should I sit?

char_127_estell_CN_002.voiceText: That little bird is my friend. But it's always disappearing on me these days... maybe it doesn't like me anymore...

char_127_estell_CN_003.voiceText: I don't seem like an Operator at all, right? You probably won't feel too proud to tell anybody that I working for you. But don't worry, I won't go around saying I'm with Rhodes Island.

char_127_estell_CN_004.voiceText: You can definitely tell there's no way I could have a typical hairstyle... I have to let my hair down like this. It's... not very appropriate, is it?

char_127_estell_CN_005.voiceText: My mutant horns... they're really stand out, don't they? I thought I was already used to the staring... but actually, it's still a bit embarrassing for me...

char_127_estell_CN_006.voiceText: The friends I made in the wilderness... they're all coming to Rhodes Island too. So... I feel less lonely! I'll do my best to fight hard and protect everyone.

char_127_estell_CN_007.voiceText: Actually, when I was little, my dream was to... to become a princess... silly, huh? Laugh all you want, it's... it's okay...

char_127_estell_CN_008.voiceText: The bad guys always call me "freak"... but... yeah, I'm a freak, but a freak can still protect you and everyone else, right?

char_127_estell_CN_009.voiceText: Um... that really energetic doctor... she's an Archosaurian too, huh? I do want to talk to her... but I'm still a bit scared...

char_127_estell_CN_010.voiceText: No one's staring at me now, right? Ah, finally...

char_127_estell_CN_011.voiceText: H-hello... Uh... s-sorry, my horns... I accidentally broke your office door with my horns...

char_127_estell_CN_012.voiceText: Powers stronger than what I already have... can I really control them...?

char_127_estell_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion? What's that?... I don't really get it, but I think it means that you... that I've been helpful, right?

char_127_estell_CN_014.voiceText: Thank you, Doctor, for giving a bit more confidence... what should I do? Who am I doing all this hard work for? I think I know the answer now... you showed me what I needed to see.

char_127_estell_CN_018.voiceText: Wahh... me? R-really? Is that really okay?

char_127_estell_CN_019.voiceText: Uh, everyone... it's... it's time to attack! I-is this how I'm supposed to give orders?

char_127_estell_CN_020.voiceText: I... I won't let the bad guys win!

char_127_estell_CN_023.voiceText: If I'm in charge of this section... I should be able to pull in lots of enemies!

char_127_estell_CN_024.voiceText: T-to intimidate the enemy... I... I'm capable of that, right?

char_127_estell_CN_027.voiceText: I won't let you escape this easily!

char_127_estell_CN_029.voiceText: I can do better... yes, even better!

char_127_estell_CN_030.voiceText: Are you proud of what we've achieved, Doctor?

char_127_estell_CN_032.voiceText: I didn't do anything useful after all...

char_127_estell_CN_033.voiceText: Wow, this place... it's so spacious! I love it!

char_127_estell_CN_036.voiceText: You're always so kind to me... I... I'm so happy!

char_141_nights_CN_001.voiceText: Didn't notice me behind you, eh? It's only natural. We Felines are known for being silent prowlers!

char_141_nights_CN_002.voiceText: Hey, don't touch my hat... it's crazy, you know! If it tells you too many secrets, Doctor, you'll be in trouble~

char_141_nights_CN_003.voiceText: Oh, so Rhodes Island takes in escaped prisoners too? Interesting. Do you guys want the map I have on me? Or do you want some prison break tips?

char_141_nights_CN_004.voiceText: We thieves have our own principles and standards too... I think. Right?

char_141_nights_CN_005.voiceText: In time, the black haze will strike all the prisons, unleashing countless Catastrophes... Meow? Hey, don't worry, I'm just talking to myself.

char_141_nights_CN_006.voiceText: Let's go! Don't worry, I have friends everywhere, eyes everywhere.

char_141_nights_CN_007.voiceText: Curiosity can kill a cat, you know.

char_141_nights_CN_008.voiceText: I'm in a good mood right now, so here's a riddle for you. "How is a raven like a writing desk?"

char_141_nights_CN_009.voiceText: Thanks for this new identity. But... did you see 'em? My secrets... Oh, you did?

char_141_nights_CN_010.voiceText: ...Doctor's sleeping too, huh? Time get to work then, then...

char_141_nights_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, I'm Haze. I like relaxing work environments and employers who know not to bother me with questions.

char_141_nights_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion? What's that? Does it taste good?

char_141_nights_CN_014.voiceText: Finally, I'm out of those cumbersome shackles... but now there are new chains on me. Guess that's the destiny of a thief.

char_141_nights_CN_017.voiceText: Just give me freedom and I'll be happy.

char_141_nights_CN_018.voiceText: Why do we need a leader? Why can't everyone just decide what's best for themselves?

char_141_nights_CN_019.voiceText: Meow... Ah, smells like sweet, sweet freedom!

char_141_nights_CN_027.voiceText: You think you're all that, huh?

char_141_nights_CN_029.voiceText: Cats don't take orders from anyone!

char_141_nights_CN_030.voiceText: Perfect victory? Whatever, as long as we won!

char_141_nights_CN_031.voiceText: You let a lot of enemies get away, you know? That kinda sucks~

char_141_nights_CN_032.voiceText: I'm no stranger to fleeing, but this is just too embarrassing...

char_141_nights_CN_036.voiceText: Meow? This ain't enough. As long as it's something that I don't have, I want it all!

char_145_prove_CN_001.voiceText: If you need your room cleaned, you can always tell me to do it, Doctor!

char_145_prove_CN_002.voiceText: You seem really interested in my tail, huh? You say it's furry and looks cute? Well, wanna touch it? No one else has a tail like this, you know!

char_145_prove_CN_003.voiceText: Water is precious in the wild. Rhodes Island is in no danger of having a drought right now, but you still shouldn't waste water!

char_145_prove_CN_004.voiceText: It's my duty to search for and rescue those injured in natural Catastrophes. I rarely find any survivors though...

char_145_prove_CN_005.voiceText: Retrieving beacons, exploring mineral deposits, and recycling... after that, my job is done!

char_145_prove_CN_006.voiceText: Mr. Grape is my buddy! It's really handy, it can be used for so many things! As for where it came from... Uh, yeah, hmm... where did we first meet? I can't remember!

char_145_prove_CN_007.voiceText: W-what's that red one doing...? I... can't stop trembling... uh... Doctor, can you lend me your arm? I'd feel much safer that way...

char_145_prove_CN_008.voiceText: Those who do Catastrophe relief work often develop all kinds of mutations. As for me... what mutation do I have? Well, it's better not to ask. The more you know, the more dangerous it gets for you, Doctor!

char_145_prove_CN_009.voiceText: Catastrophe relief workers in the wilderness... usually die out there. No need to worry about me, though! I'm already very happy to have a chance to rest at Rhodes Island.

char_145_prove_CN_010.voiceText: You can't fall asleep here... it leaves you open to enemy attacks!

char_145_prove_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Provence, your average disaster relief worker. Hmm, why are you staring at me like that? Interested in my tail?

char_145_prove_CN_012.voiceText: So... does this bring me closer to what you imagined I should be?

char_145_prove_CN_014.voiceText: I sense a storm approaching Rhodes Island. But don't worry, I'm an expert at Catastrophe prevention!

char_145_prove_CN_017.voiceText: Who will I be teaming up with this time?

char_145_prove_CN_019.voiceText: My job is to bring everyone home safely.

char_145_prove_CN_020.voiceText: I despise natural Catastrophes and enemies all the same!

char_145_prove_CN_023.voiceText: Let's start by firing a warning shot...

char_145_prove_CN_024.voiceText: Arrows loaded. I'm ready to go!

char_145_prove_CN_025.voiceText: I already warned y'all! Catastrophe relief starts... now!

char_145_prove_CN_028.voiceText: The wilderness has its own rules.

char_145_prove_CN_029.voiceText: Compared to natural Catastrophes, these enemies are really powerless.

char_145_prove_CN_030.voiceText: Disaster assessment report: we received zero damage!

char_145_prove_CN_031.voiceText: Everyone worked hard. Let's not be discouraged even if we suffered some damage!

char_145_prove_CN_032.voiceText: Aw... my assessment was off. Consider this a shameful moment in my career!

char_145_prove_CN_033.voiceText: It'd be nice to have a room to rest in!

char_183_skgoat_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, I've picked out the Originium from the pile of other ores according to your orders. Any other requests?

char_183_skgoat_CN_002.voiceText: Oripathy is really troublesome. I can't even go on operations without the okay from Dr. Kal'tsit. And patients will lose some years of their lives, you say? Yeah, that's true, but I'm okay with that.

char_183_skgoat_CN_003.voiceText: This tuning fork? It's actually a wand. It's not only a weapon but also useful for geological surveying. I find it really handy.

char_183_skgoat_CN_004.voiceText: Without Rhodes Island, I'd probably still be a full-time geological researcher. And without you people... I'd probably already be dead.

char_183_skgoat_CN_005.voiceText: Oh? I have dark circles under my eyes? Aw, I knew it...

char_183_skgoat_CN_006.voiceText: What's that behind me, you ask? Well... ah, never mind, it's really hard to explain. I'll tell you when we have more time.

char_183_skgoat_CN_007.voiceText: Some rocks talk to me, you know... and they talk a lot! Some of them even squabble... so much that I lose sleep over it. You think I'm kidding? Do I look like I'm kidding?

char_183_skgoat_CN_008.voiceText: Provence is as careless as always. She needs to be careful or she'll end up like me, seriously ill. You'd better give her a good talking-to.

char_183_skgoat_CN_009.voiceText: Look at this! Look at this! This surface... it couldn't have been formed without pressure in the earth's crust since 350 thousand years ago. Isn't it wonderful? You know, Doctor, those people who refuse to believe geological studies are truly fools.

char_183_skgoat_CN_010.voiceText: Doctoroh, you're sleeping? You must be tired from all the hard work.

char_183_skgoat_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Earthspirit, a geology scholar and Caster, reporting in. I work eight hours each day. Make me work any more and you'll have to pay me extra.

char_183_skgoat_CN_012.voiceText: Hm, is this academic data or something else?

char_183_skgoat_CN_013.voiceText: Methods of scientific research must continue to be improved on.

char_183_skgoat_CN_014.voiceText: Forgive me for my bluntness, but do remember that I only receive the salary for one person, so you can't make me do the work of more than one person even if you promote me.

char_183_skgoat_CN_018.voiceText: I hope this squad could work well in all kinds of extreme environments.

char_183_skgoat_CN_019.voiceText: Don't worry, we'll be right back.

char_183_skgoat_CN_020.voiceText: We can't let them misuse the Originium like this.

char_183_skgoat_CN_028.voiceText: You shouldn't have set foot on this land.

char_183_skgoat_CN_029.voiceText: What the enemies are doing... will only bring disaster.

char_183_skgoat_CN_030.voiceText: All enemies have been dealt with.

char_183_skgoat_CN_033.voiceText: This environment is quite suitable for research.

char_183_skgoat_CN_036.voiceText: This piece of ore... for me? Really? But... it's expensive, right?

char_183_skgoat_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, time to get to work.

char_187_ccheal_CN_001.voiceText: You deserve to rest well in your off time! But you gotta get your treatment first.

char_187_ccheal_CN_002.voiceText: Huh? You want me to be gentle and caring? That's a nurse's duty. I'm a physician, healing is my duty. I'm not interested in anything else.

char_187_ccheal_CN_003.voiceText: For some reason, Dr. Kal'tsit has been reminding me to be nice to my patients ever since I arrived here.

char_187_ccheal_CN_004.voiceText: A doctor's biggest concern is usually to protect themselves from the diseases they're often in contact with. My biggest concern, on the other hand... is that my patients are all afraid of me.

char_187_ccheal_CN_005.voiceText: You're here for treatment, so listen to me closely! Look at me! Hands up! Don't move!

char_187_ccheal_CN_006.voiceText: A doctor and a soldier... one saves lives and one takes lives. People think we're polar opposites, but to me we're one and the sameboth are mere sacrifices.

char_187_ccheal_CN_007.voiceText: Huh? I never hurt anyone. I was just trying to be friendly. See? Like this... I initiate physical contact to get closer to other people.

char_187_ccheal_CN_008.voiceText: I kinda miss my hometown now... I picked this career path myself, but I never imagined that this is how I'd end up. I chose the path less taken... and it made all the difference.

char_187_ccheal_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor... you and I are both travelers on a lonely road. I guess that's why we understand each other so well.

char_187_ccheal_CN_010.voiceText: Oh, you... you're asleep, huh? How cute.

char_187_ccheal_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Medic Operator Gavial. First things first... do not judge me by my appearance. Got it?

char_187_ccheal_CN_012.voiceText: Tch, I thought we were gonna have combat class.

char_187_ccheal_CN_013.voiceText: Everyone is terrified of my treatments... you're the only one who accepts me for what I am. Thank you...

char_187_ccheal_CN_014.voiceText: All right, no more fooling around. I'll be serious from now on.

char_187_ccheal_CN_017.voiceText: You guys go ahead. Leave the rear to me.

char_187_ccheal_CN_018.voiceText: All right, get in line, everyone!

char_187_ccheal_CN_022.voiceText: What would you like me to do?

char_187_ccheal_CN_024.voiceText: Everyone who needs healing, come over!

char_187_ccheal_CN_025.voiceText: You need treatment, right? Then come closer!

char_187_ccheal_CN_026.voiceText: What do you think you're doing?

char_187_ccheal_CN_029.voiceText: Meh, those enemies... not much of a threat.

char_187_ccheal_CN_030.voiceText: Taking out those fools... piece of cake. I regret not whacking them a few more times with this cane.

char_187_ccheal_CN_031.voiceText: Have you guys never taken emergency response training courses?

char_187_ccheal_CN_032.voiceText: Darn it... I'm not giving up yet!

char_187_ccheal_CN_033.voiceText: Let's see if there are any interesting people here!

char_187_ccheal_CN_036.voiceText: You want me to be obedient and listen? No way!

char_241_panda_CN_001.voiceText: So... I have to just stand here and not do anything? Bo-ring.

char_241_panda_CN_002.voiceText: These gauntlets aren't that heavy. See? Even I can carry them around easily, and it's not like I'm particularly strong.

char_241_panda_CN_003.voiceText: You remember fighting by my side before? I don't remember... fighting for justice is my job, after all.

char_241_panda_CN_004.voiceText: Ha, that boxer called Beehunter... she's really something! Finally an opponent worth giving my all. And she's got a great honey collection too. Wanna visit her with me next time? You gotta learn how to box first, though.

char_241_panda_CN_005.voiceText: Yep, I'm reading a movie magazine. That's right, the "hot kung-fu actor" mentioned in this article is ME! Huh? You don't believe me? Come on, look! This is my face, right? Why would I lie about this?

char_241_panda_CN_006.voiceText: Do I regret forgoing my previous life? Well, sometimes, of course. This world is rather harsh on the Infected. Lots of places I'm not allowed to go. It sucks.

char_241_panda_CN_007.voiceText: There's a street full of food stalls in the neighboring city. And... a candy shop over there? And a theme park? Aww, Doctor, can I get a day off? I wanna visit all these places!

char_241_panda_CN_008.voiceText: Am I satisfied with life at Rhodes Island, you ask? Hm, to be honest... it's even more fun than in the movies! I got cool opponents to practice fighting with and delicious food... and by working, I'm doing good in the world! Isn't that perfect?

char_241_panda_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, look! What do you think about this script? Oh, who's gonna act in it, you ask? Well, the main characters are you and I! There's this scene where we leap from the roof of a thirty-floor-high building and glide away into the sunset. Isn't that cool? Hey! Come back! Wait!

char_241_panda_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor is napping, huh? Guess I'll slack off for a bit too. Mmm, this couch is so fluffy!

char_241_panda_CN_011.voiceText: You've seen my face before, you say? Of course, you must have seen one of my movies! But I'm no longer a movie star now. I'm Feater and I'm here to follow all your orders!

char_241_panda_CN_012.voiceText: It's over? Come on, let's watch a bit further. The fun part's just begun!

char_241_panda_CN_014.voiceText: This is the perfect opportunity to show you the skills of a true boxer.

char_241_panda_CN_018.voiceText: Huh? Leader? I'm not sure I'd be good at that...

char_241_panda_CN_020.voiceText: I'm Feater. Nice to meet you.

char_241_panda_CN_026.voiceText: This is a classic scene in one of my movies!

char_241_panda_CN_028.voiceText: Some movie stars are real kung-fu masters too!

char_241_panda_CN_030.voiceText: It's over already? I haven't even warmed up yet.

char_241_panda_CN_031.voiceText: Hey, it's no biggie. Everyone gets injured once in a while.

char_241_panda_CN_032.voiceText: Aw... I just wanna go home and sleep...

char_241_panda_CN_036.voiceText: Hey, Doctor, want my autograph? I'll take a two-shot with you too!

char_180_amgoat_CN_001.voiceText: Professor, I already finished all the Catastrophe studies notes. Do you have any more?

char_180_amgoat_CN_002.voiceText: Huh? What? Why do I call you "Professor", you mean? Well, you're an expert in disaster studies, so you're like my teacher, right? Aren't we supposed to call our teachers "Professor"?

char_180_amgoat_CN_003.voiceText: What? Say that again? Oh, you're wondering why I'm hard of hearing? Well, it was because I got infected with oripathy back when I was doing research near a volcano...

char_180_amgoat_CN_004.voiceText: Besides completing the tasks you give me, I have to go to Dr. Kal'tsit regularly for checkups. The doctor said my symptoms are pretty serious...

char_180_amgoat_CN_005.voiceText: I have to work hard to finish the research my parents had started! I want to prove that their work was meaningful and maybe even change the world!

char_180_amgoat_CN_006.voiceText: My parents... They've passed on. A pyroclastic flow hit them when they were conducting studies near a volcano... I have to pick up where they left off and finish their research, no matter what!

char_180_amgoat_CN_007.voiceText: My playmates? I'm pretty friendly with Mousse and some others, so I'm not lonely at all! If possible, I'd love to start a book club with them too. Can we hold meetings in your office, Professor?

char_180_amgoat_CN_008.voiceText: Dr. Kal'tsit told me... I'm not only losing my hearing but also my vision. Oripathy is really relentless, huh?

char_180_amgoat_CN_009.voiceText: How could I tell you were behind me, you ask? I could feel your warmth, of course! My eyesight and hearing might not be what they used to be, but my other senses are still very sharp. Can't bring me down this easily, you know!

char_180_amgoat_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Eyjafjalla, whose main career before joining Rhodes Island was volcanology. I'm a bit hard of hearing due to oripathy. I hope I won't be much trouble to you, Professor.
