char_164_nightm_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, don't you get tired of it, from time to time? Your work, life, feelings, everything... What would you say to just forgetting all of it, all at once? With my power, things like that can be arranged...

char_164_nightm_CN_010.voiceText: Your sleeping face is so cute, it makes me want to...

char_164_nightm_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Nightmare... Aah, that's a code name. My real name is Gloria. But, if you don't mind, I'd rather you call me that... I think my code name... is kind of scary...

char_164_nightm_CN_012.voiceText: You're making me stronger... but why...?

char_164_nightm_CN_013.voiceText: I came here as a patient, to get treatment for my disease. But now am I to understand that doctor wants me to fight for you?

char_164_nightm_CN_014.voiceText: Don't you think I'm only barely qualified for this promotion? It doesn't matter, I'm just lucky to be alive at this point. So whatever you want to do, we can do it.

char_164_nightm_CN_019.voiceText: What sorts of incredible powers will you be using? I can't wait to see~

char_164_nightm_CN_020.voiceText: So these are our enemies, huh? Looks fun.

char_164_nightm_CN_021.voiceText: Um, is there anything to eat?

char_164_nightm_CN_024.voiceText: Been a while since the last time I was on the battlefield.

char_164_nightm_CN_030.voiceText: Well, sorry, but this is the end I prepared for you.

char_164_nightm_CN_031.voiceText: We won. What more do you want?

char_164_nightm_CN_033.voiceText: I'll be fine in the corner...

char_164_nightm_CN_036.voiceText: D-did I do something bad again...? Just, please let me apologize. I'm so, sooo sorry...

char_220_grani_CN_001.voiceText: Reporting in, Dr. {@nickname}! Patrol completed. Nothing out of the ordinary!

char_220_grani_CN_002.voiceText: I'm starving. That battle really took a lot out of me... Huh? You got me something to eat? Just for me? A-apple pie! Thanks a lot! It looks great!

char_220_grani_CN_003.voiceText: Everybody here at Rhodes Island calls me "Tiny," but it really doesn't bother me. The boys back on the force always teased me the same way. Hey! Don't pat my head! Or my ears! Or face for that matter!

char_220_grani_CN_004.voiceText: {@nickname}, I might not make it to training on Wednesdays or Fridays... Right, I need to be out there doing my part to keep the peace, catching the bad guys! Huh? I have an important mission on Friday?!

char_220_grani_CN_005.voiceText: Rhodes Island has lots of strong Operators, but there's no one who can match my speed!

char_220_grani_CN_006.voiceText: Where has the time gone? We've been working together so long now. {@nickname}, I will never forget everything we've been through. But we can't stop now! We have to keep striving for that bright future, don't we?

char_220_grani_CN_007.voiceText: I just bumped into Skadi in the hallway... {@nickname}, you think she's cold and distant, don't you? She's actually very kind. Really!

char_220_grani_CN_008.voiceText: Compared to everyone else, I'm pretty ordinary. I don't have any superpowers, or spectacular achievements to brag about... But I don't need magic or claws to make the world a better place. I can do that with my own two hands! Of course, we still have to eat well!

char_220_grani_CN_009.voiceText: {@nickname}, you always worry so much about your people, but you never remember to take care of yourself. You can't do that! No matter what dangers you may face, I promise I'll be there to hold your hand! Definitely, you have my word!

char_220_grani_CN_010.voiceText: Hmm? Why do you smell so good, {@nickname}? You're definitely hiding something tasty, aren't you?!

char_220_grani_CN_011.voiceText: Mounted Police Officer Grani has heard your cry for help! Fear not. From this point forward, I will protect you!

char_220_grani_CN_012.voiceText: I see. That's another thing I should watch out for. Uh huh!

char_220_grani_CN_013.voiceText: An elite promotion medal? For me? Thank you, {@nickname}! I'll hang it up with my police medal!

char_220_grani_CN_014.voiceText: From the time I finished my first mission right up to this very day, my lance has been here to support me. As long as I grip it tight, my heart will have the courage it needs to protect the people and their dreams.

char_220_grani_CN_017.voiceText: Shall I go scout the battlefield?

char_220_grani_CN_018.voiceText: You're making me the captain? Okay. I'll protect the whole squad!

char_220_grani_CN_019.voiceText: All right, let's bring home a victory!

char_220_grani_CN_025.voiceText: My lance will clear a path!

char_220_grani_CN_027.voiceText: In battle, someone must come out on top.

char_220_grani_CN_028.voiceText: My battlefield extends well above the ground!

char_220_grani_CN_029.voiceText: If you look to harm those under my protection, you'll have to go through me first!

char_220_grani_CN_030.voiceText: Nice! That was an excellent fight! You all did splendidly!

char_220_grani_CN_031.voiceText: {@nickname}, please stay close to me. There may still be some enemies around.

char_220_grani_CN_032.voiceText: Damn it... I can't let myself fall here!

char_220_grani_CN_036.voiceText: If we get the chance, I hope we can see the world together, {@nickname}.

char_263_skadi_CN_001.voiceText: I advise you to keep at least two meters away from me, for your own good. And of course you shouldn't speak to me either... I wouldn't want you to suffer on my account.

char_263_skadi_CN_002.voiceText: You've read my file? Terrible, isn't it? Indeed, if you stay near me, the same misfortune will befall you, and that's trouble for me too.

char_263_skadi_CN_003.voiceText: My hair is long and beautiful? Well, thank you... Would you like to touch it? It should be quite soft. I'm confident of that.

char_263_skadi_CN_004.voiceText: Could that be...? That woman, they call her Specter now, do they? Why is she dressed as a nun? Amnesia? That's awful... Dr. {@nickname}, you have to help her. She can't be allowed to forget her true function.

char_263_skadi_CN_005.voiceText: Oh you, how are you so tenacious? Then I suppose I have no choice but to defend you with all my might.

char_263_skadi_CN_006.voiceText: Down beneath the vast blue sea, below the white waves that lap endlessly at the earth, lies all that I once held dear. I fear that one day misfortune will once again take someone important to me. That is why I fled. I don't want anyone I care about... to suffer on my account.

char_263_skadi_CN_007.voiceText: Lovely, another easy day! No giant tentacles coiling up my friends, no blood crazed monsters hiding in the shadows... Just a straight fight on the battlefield. That's what I call easy!

char_263_skadi_CN_008.voiceText: According to legend, my people have fought against the calamities for aeons. Perhaps we kept them from making landfall and terrorizing you city folk as well... So, how about buying me a drink, as a thank you?

char_263_skadi_CN_009.voiceText: When you've made the long journey through the dark up to the water's surface, opened your eyes and had them filled with the glimmering light of a billion stars as the eternal undulation of the ocean waves caress your cheek, lapped the salty taste of your tears that remind you of your salty home, can you imagine what that tiny bathtub here at Rhodes Island might be like for me...? I'll have to show you my home someday.

char_263_skadi_CN_010.voiceText: You fell asleep? Well then, Dr. {@nickname}, have yourself a pleasant, dry dream.

char_263_skadi_CN_011.voiceText: I am Skadi, bounty hunter. Are you really hiring me? I cannot say what calamities I may bring with me.

char_263_skadi_CN_012.voiceText: So this is how you fight. Rush in with "woosh," knock them down with a "pow," and finish them with a "thud." Very good. I'll keep it in mind.

char_263_skadi_CN_013.voiceText: So this is the promotion Rhodes Island folks are always going on about? Not bad. Feels like I've actually become stronger, maybe.

char_263_skadi_CN_014.voiceText: Your thirst for power really does trouble me... But if you do indeed have the strength of will, then prepare yourself well, and we will stand together against the infinite darkness.

char_263_skadi_CN_017.voiceText: I am quite skilled at teamwork too, however...

char_263_skadi_CN_018.voiceText: You're placing their lives in my hands?

char_263_skadi_CN_019.voiceText: Where's the sport when all the enemies are human?

char_263_skadi_CN_020.voiceText: You are nothing compared to the calamities I fought against.

char_263_skadi_CN_023.voiceText: I'll show you the dance of the depths.

char_263_skadi_CN_025.voiceText: Who knows what lurks within the kelp forest?

char_263_skadi_CN_026.voiceText: This sword has a terrifying past.

char_263_skadi_CN_027.voiceText: Sing me a song, oh torturous nightmare.

char_263_skadi_CN_028.voiceText: Don't blink, for you may miss the misery of your death.

char_263_skadi_CN_030.voiceText: The words and thoughts of our enemies mean nothing to me. All I care about is how to defeat them.

char_263_skadi_CN_031.voiceText: Not as good as you used to be? It's only fair you get less of the take.

char_263_skadi_CN_032.voiceText: Such simple misfortunes are only the beginning.

char_263_skadi_CN_033.voiceText: Put me in a room by myself please.

char_263_skadi_CN_036.voiceText: When you're this close... I-I really can't guarantee your safety!

char_284_spot_CN_001.voiceText: I get that work is a kind of trap, but still we gotta jump right into it.

char_284_spot_CN_002.voiceText: I don't talk much 'cause I don't want to. Not 'cause I'm full of myself.

char_284_spot_CN_003.voiceText: What did Midnight do this time? Did he finally end up in Medical after hitting on one too many ladies in the hallway? No? Too bad.

char_284_spot_CN_004.voiceText: Got something, Doctor? I could probably lend a hand. But I'd rather it not eat up too much of my time. I got a lot of comics to read.

char_284_spot_CN_005.voiceText: I know I speak a little too bluntly sometimes, but I always get my work done. It's not like I got professional pride or anything, I just can't respect somebody who doesn't finish his work.

char_284_spot_CN_007.voiceText: Rhodes Island is a strange place. The people here just say whatever they're thinking, and somebody's always there to help when someone needs it.

char_284_spot_CN_008.voiceText: On Op Reserve Team A6, if I'm not spending all day getting scowled at, I'm dealing with a lack of self control, or anarcissisticpersonality disorder, or a ticking time bomb. But I do think I can trust them. They work hard, even if they don't show it.

char_284_spot_CN_009.voiceText: I used to live free and easy like everyone else at Rhodes Island, but my family thought I was a freak. This place may be a freakshow, but at least everyone's happy, and that's pretty good.

char_284_spot_CN_010.voiceText: Can I go back to my room now?

char_284_spot_CN_011.voiceText: Hi, I'm Spot from Operation Reserve Team A6. My job is to protect the other clowns on my team, I guess.

char_284_spot_CN_012.voiceText: I've seen this battle before. Nice one.

char_284_spot_CN_013.voiceText: I'm gonna work twice as hard. I'll bump it up from a 0.1 to a 0.2, I think.

char_284_spot_CN_017.voiceText: I really don't care about the whole mission background. I just keep my mouth shut and get it done.

char_284_spot_CN_018.voiceText: I was just going back to the dormitory.

char_284_spot_CN_020.voiceText: It would save us a lot of time if you just gave up.

char_284_spot_CN_026.voiceText: I don't think it's gonna hurt my teammates.

char_284_spot_CN_028.voiceText: I'm sick of holding this shield.

char_284_spot_CN_029.voiceText: Fun times? Wanna do it again?

char_284_spot_CN_030.voiceText: With hard work, even an idiot can get the job done.

char_284_spot_CN_031.voiceText: We definitely can't give that a perfect score.

char_284_spot_CN_032.voiceText: Don't sweat it. You did fine.

char_284_spot_CN_036.voiceText: If you keep petting me like that, my hair's gonna get tangled.

char_281_popka_CN_001.voiceText: Ummm... Nice to see you again, Doctor. It makes me happy... hehe...

char_281_popka_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor, need a break? I made you some tea, and Miss Orchid made cookies. Here you go, Doctor... Feel better!

char_281_popka_CN_003.voiceText: Why is everyone in Team A6 always fighting...? If they keep arguing all the time, they can't be friends... Fighting is bad. I'll have to teach them that...

char_281_popka_CN_004.voiceText: The gear on my chainsaw that makes the "vrrrr" sound is kinda loose... That's weird. I don't remember using it lately...?

char_281_popka_CN_005.voiceText: Doctor, is Team A6 finally getting along...? Ermm... I really hope they are... As long as they don't fight, I can stay here with you...

char_281_popka_CN_007.voiceText: I don't know why, but I sometimes get these gaps in my memory. Then when I ask my teammates in A6, they just smile and tell me nothing happened at all...

char_281_popka_CN_008.voiceText: Um, Doc-Doctor, did I just pass out...? Um, why is everyone lying on the floor? Miss Catapult? Mr. Midnight? Mr. Spot? Why are you all slashed up? Why is Miss Orchid like that...?

char_281_popka_CN_009.voiceText: I have a special ability? And it's super strong? When I want to stop my friends from fighting, I use my power, and lose control, and then forget everything that happened...? Wow, okay, I get it now. Right! I can't let this power go to waste!

char_281_popka_CN_010.voiceText: Aaaah! I broke the cup... Errmm... I'm in trouble when the Doctor wakes up...

char_281_popka_CN_011.voiceText: Popukar from Operation Reserve Team A6, reporting in. Um, my teammates in A6 are always arguing. I'm sure you worry about them, Doctor... But I know what to do...

char_281_popka_CN_012.voiceText: Hey, Doctor, is the girl in the video... me?

char_281_popka_CN_013.voiceText: I'm so happy I don't even know what to say...! Thank you, Doctor...! Thank you so much!

char_281_popka_CN_017.voiceText: My name is Popukar... Nice to meet you...

char_281_popka_CN_018.voiceText: Ummm... I really don't know anything about tactics or strategies or anything...

char_281_popka_CN_019.voiceText: Miss Catapult, um, it's time to deploy!

char_281_popka_CN_020.voiceText: Miss Orchid, don't worry... I'll can do it.

char_281_popka_CN_029.voiceText: Mr. Midnight, come back here... Miss Orchid is watching you...

char_281_popka_CN_031.voiceText: Errrmm... Doctor, here, I made tea... Doctor, are you tired?

char_281_popka_CN_032.voiceText: Oww... It hurts... They hit me...

char_281_popka_CN_033.voiceText: Please don't leave me here alone...

char_281_popka_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, are you getting along with everyone today...?

char_308_swire_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, we can't waste even a single minute of our precious lives! I mean, a minute be the difference in losing millions of dollars, you know? Huh? Coffee? I'll take it with a packet of sugar and lots of milk foam. Thanks!

char_308_swire_CN_002.voiceText: They say Rhodes Island is a criminal organization, full of infected people dirtying up the hallways. But that couldn't be further from the truth. Rhodes Island's Operators are giving their lives to make everything better for everyone, just like the Lungmen police!

char_308_swire_CN_003.voiceText: Hey, do you think we could redesign the look of the instructor's office? We could at least add a bit of flavor to it like a handmade rug or some atomistic art. It's just so bland now. Dobermann says she doesn't care, but it's really killing my enthusiasm...

char_308_swire_CN_004.voiceText: Ahhh, that awful Ch'en isn't here, is she? Back when we were in L.G.D. together, she gave me dirty looks every time we bumped into each other. It made me wonder if I'd really done something wrong! It made me think... maybe... I should take over the L.G.D. myself!

char_308_swire_CN_005.voiceText: Exercise, study, training, opposition research, and market forces... You need them all!

char_308_swire_CN_006.voiceText: My family let me leave behind the family business for a while. But it's clear to me that the future of Lungmen needs both a stable public sector and security apparatus, as well as a healthy business and financial system. On either side, I'm ready to be of service to Lungmen!

char_308_swire_CN_007.voiceText: The Lungmen bureaucracy is complicated. Keeping the peace, protecting the people, directing traffic, negotiating trade... Agh, it's absolutely backbreaking. But as long as what we do is good for Lungmen, I'll be, hehe, very pleased.

char_308_swire_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, why is Rhodes Island's training course so short...? Insufficient capital? Unacceptable, I'm requesting an immediate transfer to the business office! It's-it's not that I like business, it's just that if you need me to do it, I'm... more than capable!

char_308_swire_CN_009.voiceText: You know, Doctor, Lungmen could use someone as talented as you. So, well... If you're not enjoying this line of work, there's plenty of opportunities in the banking and management sectors! I-I can get you a job! Oh? You'd rather we work with Rhodes Island? ...Fine!

char_308_swire_CN_010.voiceText: Uughh... I'm exhausted... Two shifts in a row is just... Ung... zzz... zzz...

char_308_swire_CN_011.voiceText: I am Senior Superintendent of the Lungmen Police Department, Swire. I'll be joining Rhodes Island as a training consultant. Dr. {@nickname}, I'm looking forward to working with you for the future of Lungmen!

char_308_swire_CN_012.voiceText: Hmm, so those tactics work pretty well like this huh!

char_308_swire_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? But it doesn't do anything for me back in Lungmen, does it? Well, anyway, if you insist, I... I guess I have to accept!

char_308_swire_CN_014.voiceText: Maybe it's that you want to use me to improve your relationship with Lungmen. Or it could be you just need my talents. I guess it could be something else you want... I don't know exactly what it is, and I can't promise I can give it. But I'll follow you to the end.

char_308_swire_CN_017.voiceText: You finally need my wisdom, huh!

char_308_swire_CN_018.voiceText: Follow my orders to the letter!

char_308_swire_CN_019.voiceText: Wipe them out in one fell swoop! It's cheaper that way!

char_308_swire_CN_020.voiceText: Let's finish this quickly. My time is far too precious!

char_308_swire_CN_024.voiceText: You may be my rival, but you get a lesson too!

char_308_swire_CN_029.voiceText: Fantastic! In battle as in business: high risk, high return!

char_308_swire_CN_030.voiceText: Capital is all mergers and acquisitions! Victory is all investigation and arrest!

char_308_swire_CN_031.voiceText: That was terrible! Awful! You can do better, can't you? We'll do it together. Don't give up!

char_308_swire_CN_032.voiceText: How could this have happened? How could I... How could I have screwed that up!

char_308_swire_CN_033.voiceText: Not bad... Wait, this room needs some renovation!

char_308_swire_CN_036.voiceText: How... How about we have dinner together? M-my treat!

char_253_greyy_CN_001.voiceText: Hi, Doctor... Um, if you need anything, please tell me... Um, do you still remember my code name...?

char_253_greyy_CN_002.voiceText: Doc-Doctor, hi... Um, I just checked the Medical Department's power grid, and taking some files around while I'm at it... No, nobody's forcing me! I mean, they take such good care of me, it's the least I can do for them...

char_253_greyy_CN_003.voiceText: I decided to learn electric Arts just so my friends back in the slums could have some light, just so the nights would be a little less miserable... That pitch black, it's really scary. And the kinds of people who live in the dark, they can be scary too...

char_253_greyy_CN_004.voiceText: These Originium generators here at Rhodes Island are amazing... You know, if we had anything like them back home, we'd have enough power we wouldn't need to live in the dark all the time, like it was normal.

char_253_greyy_CN_005.voiceText: My mother taught me the basics of Arts. She told me I use Arts just like she did when she was younger, but I'm also as sickly as she was... If she were still alive, I'd hope she could come with me to Rhodes Island...

char_253_greyy_CN_006.voiceText: Before your training, Doctor, all I could do with my Arts was light up one little room. But now that little spark has turned into something that can help people everywhere...! Doctor, thank you so much!

char_253_greyy_CN_007.voiceText: Huh? A current anomaly in Miss Mayer's storeroom? W-why is it her again... What? Dr. Kal'tsit wants more cables for her lab? And another outage in Ifrit's room? Wah aahhh... Doctor, help meee...

char_253_greyy_CN_008.voiceText: Zzz... Wha? Doctor...? Ah! Sorry! I wasn't napping! I, erm, I was... Oh, is this Medical?

char_253_greyy_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, are you going out again...? Okay, I know. I'll wait here for you... Um, Doctor, please hurry back...

char_253_greyy_CN_010.voiceText: Whoa...! Aaaugh... Static electricity. Gave me a jolt...

char_253_greyy_CN_011.voiceText: H-Hi. My name is Greyy. I'm kind of an electrician... Erm, th-thanks for taking me on...!

char_253_greyy_CN_012.voiceText: C-could you pause it for a minute? I-I'm taking notes...

char_253_greyy_CN_013.voiceText: It's a promotion? Okay, I'll take it to... Huh? It's, it's for me...? Huh?

char_253_greyy_CN_014.voiceText: Heh heh. Doctor, let me light the way for you! Um, am I getting too full of myself...? But I actually mean it...!

char_253_greyy_CN_018.voiceText: I'm the Cap-Captain...? Um, it's what the Doctor wants...!

char_253_greyy_CN_019.voiceText: Let me handle the logistical support...!

char_253_greyy_CN_022.voiceText: I-I should be able to do it...!

char_253_greyy_CN_024.voiceText: I-I have to watch where I step.

char_253_greyy_CN_026.voiceText: I won't let them get hurt...!

char_253_greyy_CN_028.voiceText: An electric shock c-can really hurt...!

char_253_greyy_CN_029.voiceText: Doc-Doctor, good job...! Can we go home now...?

char_253_greyy_CN_031.voiceText: Doctor, the ones who ran off... We won't see them again, will we?

char_253_greyy_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, you're really tall... I-I wonder when I'll get to be that tall...

char_010_chen_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, your safety will be my responsibility from now on.

char_010_chen_CN_002.voiceText: I've always had my suspicions about Rhodes Island. Still do.

char_010_chen_CN_003.voiceText: Why are you staring at me? Nothing better to do?

char_010_chen_CN_005.voiceText: I know every nook and cranny of Lungmen. The docks, the neon signs, the winding paths, I can see them all clear as day in my mind. I'll never forget them.

char_010_chen_CN_006.voiceText: Things have been deteriorating around here lately. I'll be on guard, but I still don't want you doing anything stupid.

char_010_chen_CN_007.voiceText: Maybe one day my efforts will be appreciated, but until then...

char_010_chen_CN_008.voiceText: Amiya trusts you completely. When I see you two together, it makes me wonder, what if I had someone like that by my side...

char_010_chen_CN_009.voiceText: I've... I've never been able to put that much faith in anyone, not even...

char_010_chen_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor? You fell asleep? Hmph. How careless.

char_010_chen_CN_011.voiceText: I am the leader of L.G.D.'s Special Inspector Group, Ch'en. I have my own reasons, but I'll be joining you for a while. Seeing as we're already well acquainted from our prior work together, I'll ask you to take me to the office now.

char_010_chen_CN_012.voiceText: It's all in the service of more efficient operations.

char_010_chen_CN_013.voiceText: Another promotion? I'm used to it by now.

char_010_chen_CN_014.voiceText: Roger. Just give me all the missions your usual Operators can't handle.

char_010_chen_CN_018.voiceText: Listen up! We'll be much more efficient if we work together.

char_010_chen_CN_029.voiceText: Such evil must be stopped, and by any means necessary.

char_010_chen_CN_030.voiceText: You have the courage to challenge me? I have to wonder why.

char_010_chen_CN_031.voiceText: The wounded wait here for a medivac. The rest of you Operators, stay on guard.

char_010_chen_CN_033.voiceText: So these are Rhodes Island's internal operations? Bigger than I expected.

char_010_chen_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, you're in a good mood. Is it because that operation went well? Me too. How about that.

char_298_susuro_CN_001.voiceText: Time for a break, Doctor. Have you been at it since the last round? Take a break now, please.

char_298_susuro_CN_002.voiceText: It is my duty to perform regular check-ups on Oripathy patients. Some are personable enough, but a few are hard to communicate with. It's not the first time, though, so worry not, they will understand how vital a doctor is to them.

char_298_susuro_CN_003.voiceText: Do you know everything an amnesia patient should know? Don't work yourself into the ground. Work and relaxation are equally important!

char_298_susuro_CN_004.voiceText: You always have patients who ignore the doctor's orders, but in battle, a doctor can't ignore a cry for help.

char_298_susuro_CN_005.voiceText: The cruelty of war and disasters have often spurred the development of medicine, so doctors must be at the forefront of pain and suffering. As long as I can help my patients get their lives back, I'm ready to face that fact.

char_298_susuro_CN_006.voiceText: The time I've worked with you has been, uh... some of my happiest! Come on, Doctor, you know I'm not good with words, so don't play dumb!

char_298_susuro_CN_007.voiceText: Here's a pen. How did I know you wanted it? Well, I've been working with you for a while now, isn't it natural I picked up on it?

char_298_susuro_CN_008.voiceText: I'm still far below the level of Doctors Silence and Shining, but I'm not afraid of how hard it may be for me. How can I measure up to your confidence in me otherwise?

char_298_susuro_CN_009.voiceText: The sun is indeed warm on the deck, and the breeze is cozy as well... No, I'm not slacking off. Even a doctor needs to relax, right? Why don't you tell me what's bothering you? You can even whisper it.

char_298_susuro_CN_010.voiceText: Who designed this meal plan? It's simply horrifying!

char_298_susuro_CN_011.voiceText: Sussurro, Medic, reporting in and reminding you to follow your doctor's orders, no matter how much you have on your plate.

char_298_susuro_CN_012.voiceText: I must make more copies of these battle notes for Myrrh and company.

char_298_susuro_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion ceremony, while everyone stares at me? I don't have to make any embarrassing speeches, do I? No, no, I'm not nervous at all, really...

char_298_susuro_CN_014.voiceText: For this promotion, I have to thank the entire hard-working Medical Unit behind me and the guidance of the Doctor. I'm very, very grateful to you all!

char_298_susuro_CN_017.voiceText: Don't worry, I'll watch over them.

char_298_susuro_CN_018.voiceText: Hold everything! You must complete all pre-battle physical exam to deploy!

char_298_susuro_CN_019.voiceText: Attention, medics, please follow all standard procedures in a battle.

char_298_susuro_CN_020.voiceText: Safety first, and do not touch anything that may be suspicious or infected!

char_298_susuro_CN_022.voiceText: Louder! It's hard to hear over the battle!

char_298_susuro_CN_023.voiceText: Look over here for a doctor!

char_298_susuro_CN_025.voiceText: Don't worry, you'll be okay in no time!

char_298_susuro_CN_026.voiceText: Don't concern yourself with fighting, you're still wounded!

char_298_susuro_CN_028.voiceText: Scream if you're in pain, don't hold it in!

char_298_susuro_CN_029.voiceText: Finally, the battle's over. You should take a break too. I imagine commanding the mission would take a toll on your body.

char_298_susuro_CN_030.voiceText: No casualty on our side. The Doctor's leadership is indeed unparalleled.

char_298_susuro_CN_031.voiceText: Will the enemy return? There are still wounded unable to move here.

char_298_susuro_CN_032.voiceText: Make way, make way! Stop crowding! Wounded coming through!

char_298_susuro_CN_033.voiceText: Promise you'll rest when it's time to, okay?

char_298_susuro_CN_036.voiceText: Phew. I need a drink after work! Mind handing me a juice, Doctor? Thanks!

char_151_myrtle_CN_001.voiceText: Hey, Doctor. I'm hear to hang!

char_151_myrtle_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor, don't look down on me just 'cause I'm little. Back where I'm from, all the kids looked up to me.

char_151_myrtle_CN_003.voiceText: Durin used the name of our race as her codename because she's so lazy, but isn't it kind of dumb how calling me "Myrtle of Durin" made me sound like I belong to her or something?

char_151_myrtle_CN_004.voiceText: I understand how all the machines here work, but it still feels weird using them. Some have a lot of different parts, yet some are surprisingly simple.

char_151_myrtle_CN_005.voiceText: The banner? Good eyes, Doctor. It is indeed the tablecloth from my home. I sneaked it out with me because it couldn't get dirty. My father is probably mad right now!

char_151_myrtle_CN_006.voiceText: Is my apple really that great? They're popular in my hometown. You can study or play it if you want, Doctor, just won't ruin it.

char_151_myrtle_CN_007.voiceText: There are still many things I'm not used to on land, but I love the many delicious food. The cafe on Rhodes Island is my favorite!

char_151_myrtle_CN_008.voiceText: I must solemnly point out the fact, Doctor, that I am a full-grown adult! And I'm tall by Durin standards! Tell everyone to not pat me on the head and offer me candy!

char_151_myrtle_CN_009.voiceText: Say, Doctor, are you interested in my hometown? I can take you there! But it's quite far, so wait till I'm in the mood.

char_151_myrtle_CN_010.voiceText: Are you taking a break? You can use my banner for cover.

char_151_myrtle_CN_011.voiceText: Reporting! You're the Doctor, I presume? You may call me Myrtle, Myrtle of Durin. Durin said I could get a job here, so do you have anything for me? I may be small, but I'm tough!

char_151_myrtle_CN_013.voiceText: Oh, did I get promoted? Does that mean I can visit places I couldn't before?

char_151_myrtle_CN_014.voiceText: Didn't I tell you I'm tough? It's true!

char_151_myrtle_CN_017.voiceText: There's a mission? Me, I wanna go!

char_151_myrtle_CN_018.voiceText: Don't everyone stray too far from me.

char_151_myrtle_CN_020.voiceText: Do not worry, people, you got me!

char_151_myrtle_CN_025.voiceText: I have to get serious now!

char_151_myrtle_CN_027.voiceText: We're counting on you again today, little apple.

char_151_myrtle_CN_029.voiceText: Phew, I'm exhausted! I wanna go to lie down, Doctor.

char_151_myrtle_CN_030.voiceText: Flawless victory! I was pretty good, wasn't I, Doctor?

char_151_myrtle_CN_031.voiceText: We won, Doctor, and that's what counts!

char_151_myrtle_CN_036.voiceText: Why can't the cafe open 24 hours?

char_151_myrtle_CN_042.voiceText: Any more fun things to do, Doctor?

char_274_astesi_CN_001.voiceText: The work schedule is out for you to follow.

char_274_astesi_CN_002.voiceText: How to make an astrolabe is a secret, but as you said, anything can be had for a price. And you will know the secret if the price is right.

char_274_astesi_CN_003.voiceText: Observing the stars everyday makes my neck sore. Wonder if the medics would have any suggestions for that... What, Warfarin is the physician on duty today? Uh, I'll check again another day.

char_274_astesi_CN_004.voiceText: Astrology is divining the future from celestial alignments. It's not quite augury, but with same result. So, would you like to try? It's free.

char_274_astesi_CN_005.voiceText: Convergent DNA among blood relatives Hmm, resonance and concurrency within Originium formation Now this is some occult stuff. I cant make heads or tails of it Doctor, would you be able to take some time to explain this report to me?

char_274_astesi_CN_006.voiceText: Ever since my Oripathic infection, the stars have diminished their responses to me. I must find a way to reverse it before I lose all my power. Can you help me, Doctor?

char_274_astesi_CN_007.voiceText: You want to know more about the organization I'm with? Sorry, I took an oath not to divulge anything, and it's not for public knowledge, anyway. If you're curious, just think of it as a completely neutral community.

char_274_astesi_CN_008.voiceText: Sometimes, I envy Sta... No, she's Astgenne now. She has everything I'm missing. That must be it, Doctor. We relied on each other because we complement each other, that's why we're sisters.

char_274_astesi_CN_009.voiceText: The night is over and the stars are about to fade. If this is the end of everything, I should start doing something meaningful. Such as? Well, do you mind me waking you up every morning, Doctor?

char_274_astesi_CN_010.voiceText: Tea is ready. Time to relax.

char_274_astesi_CN_011.voiceText: Astesia, astrologer, reporting for guard duty. I'm yours to command, Doctor.

char_274_astesi_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion medal? It's exquisite, I shall keep it safe.

char_274_astesi_CN_014.voiceText: Stars are witnesses to the past.

char_274_astesi_CN_018.voiceText: Let me be the guiding star for all.

char_274_astesi_CN_019.voiceText: I know there's no turning back.

char_274_astesi_CN_020.voiceText: The stars will light our way.

char_274_astesi_CN_023.voiceText: Don't panic, Astesia. Do it like you usually do.

char_274_astesi_CN_026.voiceText: Lend me your wings, birds among the stars!

char_274_astesi_CN_027.voiceText: It is futile for you to struggle.

char_274_astesi_CN_028.voiceText: The light of stars shall be my blade!

char_274_astesi_CN_029.voiceText: This is "our" power, unreproducible even by the stars...

char_274_astesi_CN_030.voiceText: Fantastic effort, Doctor. You should turn in early.

char_274_astesi_CN_031.voiceText: Will the result improve if I put in more effort?

char_274_astesi_CN_032.voiceText: I'm very tired, but it's not time to quit yet...

char_274_astesi_CN_033.voiceText: Let me see... No, how the furniture are arranged won't attract any unwanted spirits.

char_274_astesi_CN_036.voiceText: Why, is there something on my face?

char_326_glacus_CN_001.voiceText: I'll be quiet modifying the Raythean Franker close by... I won't disturb you, I promise.

char_326_glacus_CN_002.voiceText: Why does everyone always keep their distance from Blue Poison? Am I missing something...? All right.

char_326_glacus_CN_003.voiceText: Anything you would like to say, Doctor? No? Well, anyway, I'm here.

char_326_glacus_CN_004.voiceText: No one in a hot dorm is going to have any appetite... Oh, it's a family thing, I'm not actually complaining.

char_326_glacus_CN_005.voiceText: Why would I leave home to come here if I can't even run free?

char_326_glacus_CN_006.voiceText: While Vulcan doesn't appreciate "old things" like me, I still feel we have different fundamental philosophies.

char_326_glacus_CN_007.voiceText: So, Doctor, Blue Poison said I always seem to be hiding something. Do I? Occasionally? No way...

char_326_glacus_CN_008.voiceText: It's not I don't want to talk, it's just that I seldom had the right to in the past, so I got used to not speaking up! Hope you won't take it the wrong way, {@nickname}.

char_326_glacus_CN_009.voiceText: Two memories stand out to me. One is the wide-open, splendid scenery I saw the first time I ran with the child. For the other, I'll say right here, right now on Rhodes Island.

char_326_glacus_CN_010.voiceText: Hey, when did the Doctor fall asleep...?

char_326_glacus_CN_011.voiceText: Operator Glaucus reporting. May I go back to my room now?

char_326_glacus_CN_012.voiceText: Huh? Yes, I see. Got it.

char_326_glacus_CN_013.voiceText: I named the weapon, actually. Maybe that's what I really think... What, did they just announce my name for promotion?

char_326_glacus_CN_014.voiceText: Trust...? Well, I don't know how to show it, but I'll keep trying.

char_326_glacus_CN_017.voiceText: Have the members followed the proper landing procedure?

char_326_glacus_CN_018.voiceText: What? I'm the captain? Did I agree without realizing it?

char_326_glacus_CN_019.voiceText: What interesting thing will we pick up this time?

char_326_glacus_CN_022.voiceText: Fully charged and ready to go.

char_326_glacus_CN_024.voiceText: Don't worry, it's a successful landing.

char_326_glacus_CN_029.voiceText: Enemy silent. Please check damage on yourself.

char_326_glacus_CN_030.voiceText: All units silent, EMP field canceled. Nice work, everyone.

char_326_glacus_CN_031.voiceText: Did some enemy escape? Aren't we pursuing?

char_326_glacus_CN_032.voiceText: EMP field is canceled. Call for backup, quickly!

char_326_glacus_CN_033.voiceText: No problem, as soon as I find that screw first...

char_326_glacus_CN_036.voiceText: Mind taking a walk with me, Doctor?

char_348_ceylon_CN_001.voiceText: I'll be writing reports or reading nearby, just call when you need me.

char_348_ceylon_CN_002.voiceText: I believe you reap what you sow, and have always followed that principle.

char_348_ceylon_CN_003.voiceText: Wait, I didnt know Oripathy could take on this characteristic! This needs to be investigated immediately! Doctor, if youd excuse me Hmm, I wonder if there are any suitable subjects in Rhodes Islands

char_348_ceylon_CN_004.voiceText: The day is not complete without tea. Would you like a cup too, Doctor? I have the best tea leaves in all Victoria.

char_348_ceylon_CN_005.voiceText: I've been with Schwarz since childhood. I know everything about her, including her past before we met. But I'm not giving that up so easily.

char_348_ceylon_CN_006.voiceText: If I could find a cure for Schwarz, wouldn't that mean I could cure other infected too? Worry not, Doctor, I'm not that selfish. But please also know that Schwarz is dearest to my heart.

char_348_ceylon_CN_007.voiceText: Originium research is still a vastly unexplored territory, Doctor. But I just want to find a cure, which is why I longed for Rhodes Island ever since I heard about it.

char_348_ceylon_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, did you know, I hate those who would discriminate against Schwarz because of her infection. But, there are no people like that here at Rhodes Island. No-one here will reject her, and I can further my medical knowledge Im really glad that I came here.

char_348_ceylon_CN_009.voiceText: Regardless of how good a leader is, there's still a chance she could be blinded by selfish interest, so you must watch out for that, Doctor. But as long as I'm around, I'll put you back on the right path anytime you stray.

char_348_ceylon_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, its not good to sleep while sitting up Mm, I guess its fine. Let me at least get a blanket for you.

char_348_ceylon_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, I'm Ceylon, graduate of the Victoria National University with a major in Originium research. I start my internship on Rhodes Island today with Dr. Kal'tsit's approval. Nice to meet you, Doctor.

char_348_ceylon_CN_012.voiceText: An excellent application of Originium. Rhodes Island sure lives up to its reputation!

char_348_ceylon_CN_013.voiceText: So I'm officially recognized by Rhodes Island? Thank you, Doctor, I'll work even harder!

char_348_ceylon_CN_014.voiceText: Rhodes Island does boast amazing Originium research! I will cure Schwarz one day if I keep working here! Please help me too, Doctor!

char_348_ceylon_CN_017.voiceText: A mission? Perfect time to try out my new Originium ability.

char_348_ceylon_CN_018.voiceText: Relax, I'm a pretty good commander.

char_348_ceylon_CN_019.voiceText: I wonder if we'll find rare materials along the way?

char_348_ceylon_CN_020.voiceText: Don't panic, handle it with composure.

char_348_ceylon_CN_023.voiceText: Leave the support work to me.

char_348_ceylon_CN_027.voiceText: This move should be better for the present situation.

char_348_ceylon_CN_029.voiceText: Phew Hehe, it feels like I just finished a difficult experiment. I might be tired, but I feel a sense of accomplishment.

char_348_ceylon_CN_030.voiceText: The enemy should be gone now, so I'm going to look around the perimeter.

char_348_ceylon_CN_031.voiceText: They wouldn't have gotten away if I were Schwarz...

char_348_ceylon_CN_032.voiceText: Don't just stand there, Doctor, give me a hand with the wounded!

char_348_ceylon_CN_033.voiceText: Maybe talk to the other doctors on base.

char_348_ceylon_CN_034.voiceText: Wait, my hair is getting messed up!

char_348_ceylon_CN_036.voiceText: Don't tell me the Doctor dozed off in the chair again...

char_348_ceylon_CN_042.voiceText: How are you, Doctor? Care for some tea with me?

char_340_shwaz_CN_001.voiceText: I made an itinerary. You can confirm with me anytime.

char_340_shwaz_CN_002.voiceText: When it's time to shed blood, do not send Lady Ceylon to do it, send someone who lives amongst the shadows.

char_340_shwaz_CN_003.voiceText: I won't tell you any of Lady Ceylon's secrets. Of course, I won't tell anyone your secrets either.

char_340_shwaz_CN_004.voiceText: I'm a bodyguard and it's my duty to protect you, Doctor, not to be your chat buddy. If you want to talk, find someone else and stop turning to me like Lady Ceylon does.

char_340_shwaz_CN_005.voiceText: My expertise? Killing and protecting people. Oh, and making tea. Don't be so shocked. After all, Lady Ceylon is... Anyway, I'm good at that.

char_340_shwaz_CN_006.voiceText: Based on the danger involved in the missions to date, Doctor, I believe, in addition to my protection, you should learn self-defense. Otherwise, even I can't guarantee your safety.

char_340_shwaz_CN_007.voiceText: There's no turning back once you got blood on your hands, Doctor. I don't want you to go down that road, so leave the dirty stuff to me.

char_340_shwaz_CN_008.voiceText: You want to hear my revenge story? You won't be able to sleep at night, Doctor. But I do have this strange urge to tell you. Why don't we hit the bar, because it's a long story

char_340_shwaz_CN_009.voiceText: Sinners always get what they deserve, I know that. But let's say I'd be more than just a killer had I met Lady Ceylon and you sooner. It's still not too late for me? Do you really mean that, Doctor?

char_340_shwaz_CN_010.voiceText: Falls asleep just like that? Can't keep a guard up at all, just like her.

char_340_shwaz_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Schwarz, Lady Ceylon's personal bodyguard, here to join Rhodes Island with her. If at all possible, please send me with her on any missions.

char_340_shwaz_CN_012.voiceText: Rhodes Island is teeming with monsters. I can only hope to learn to battle like them.

char_340_shwaz_CN_013.voiceText: Now I understand why Rhodes Island wanted me. You're looking for something a hundred times crazier than anything I ever did.

char_340_shwaz_CN_014.voiceText: Reawaken my past? Sounds good. Maybe you can absolve the evil we did in battle. Please, cleanse me.

char_340_shwaz_CN_028.voiceText: Lady Ceylon may be merciful, but I am not.

char_340_shwaz_CN_029.voiceText: You should lead this dangerous mission from someplace as far away from the battlefield as possible, Doctor.

char_340_shwaz_CN_030.voiceText: We got everyone, per your order.

char_340_shwaz_CN_031.voiceText: The perimeter is secured. What's next?

char_340_shwaz_CN_032.voiceText: Come, Doctor, I'll ensure your safety.

char_340_shwaz_CN_034.voiceText: Watch out for accidental discharge, Doctor.

char_340_shwaz_CN_042.voiceText: Don't let your guard down, even on base, Doctor.

char_188_helage_CN_001.voiceText: It takes prolonged suffering to quench the flames of war, while it takes naught but an accidental spark to ignite them.

char_188_helage_CN_002.voiceText: The fall of Chernobog dealt a devastating blow to Azazel, our clinic. I must rebuild it for the children; it was their home. It matters not where it is rebuilt, as long as it is. One needs no reason to take great pains for their family.

char_188_helage_CN_003.voiceText: Rhodes Island is in a respectable position, but the Infected of Ursus face prospects far worse than anyone could imagine. They must be ready to resort to violence in order to survive, for there is no concept of good or evil in that place.

char_188_helage_CN_004.voiceText: "All Ursusians should be proud of their nation and emperor." I, too, fought for Ursus once, but now I have lost all my patriotism. Time has robbed me of too much.

char_188_helage_CN_005.voiceText: Life in the military has taught me two things: First, have faith in your fellow soldiers; second, have faith in them, but do not trust them. This dilemma has always plagued our lands, and none can escape it.

char_188_helage_CN_006.voiceText: Dr. {@nickname}, a limitless future awaits you, just as it does for those children. Though I can neither let go of yesterday nor look forward to tomorrow, I shall fight for you till my last drop of blood, so you may be part of that future.

char_188_helage_CN_007.voiceText: I am fine with Ursus as my enemy. Once I swore my utmost loyalty to it, but that was returned with everlasting disillusionment and shame. For the children's sake, I will never falter, much less surrender.

char_188_helage_CN_008.voiceText: Once there was a long battle. When I finally broke into the enemy headquarters, I was too late... All I could do for my dying friend was to take his pocket watch and sword. The enemy lost their commander, whose death brought Ursus a brief victory. But I emerged from the battle feeling defeated.

char_188_helage_CN_009.voiceText: The photograph inside my pocket watch? Hahahah, so you saw it... This is Neon from when she was little. Isn't she adorable? She's not so quiet anymore, but she loves herself now, and that's all that matters... Live free, {@nickname}, that's my wish, even if it is trite.

char_188_helage_CN_010.voiceText: Don't lose focus. You must be alert at all times on Rhodes Island.

char_188_helage_CN_011.voiceText: Hellagur, a infected mercenary. I will work with Rhodes Island in order to rebuild my Azazel Clinic and protect my family. But be advised, I have no medical skills.

char_188_helage_CN_012.voiceText: Battlefields may change, but not the cruelty.

char_188_helage_CN_013.voiceText: I'm used to it as a soldier, but I find it fascinating as an infected. Thank you for the ribbon, Dr. {@nickname}.

char_188_helage_CN_014.voiceText: War will never truly be over, but I believe even this land will end eventually. Maybe you can end our suffering one day, Dr. {@nickname}. Now, give me my order!

char_188_helage_CN_017.voiceText: Only butchers thirst for blood. We're merely paying a price for survival.

char_188_helage_CN_018.voiceText: I'll demand them follow orders to Ursus soldier standards!

char_188_helage_CN_019.voiceText: I don't mind losing my life if it could end it all.

char_188_helage_CN_020.voiceText: You have never seen a real war, pathetic runts.

char_188_helage_CN_021.voiceText: I was born to fight battles.

char_188_helage_CN_022.voiceText: It's a thin line between life and death.

char_188_helage_CN_023.voiceText: Killing the enemy is the last resort.

char_188_helage_CN_024.voiceText: I truly have no way of leaving here, I know.

char_188_helage_CN_025.voiceText: Wield blade as whip to flay flesh.

char_188_helage_CN_026.voiceText: Wield whip as spear to sunder weapons.

char_188_helage_CN_027.voiceText: Wield spear as blade to slice through armor!

char_188_helage_CN_028.voiceText: Your owner didn't sacrifice in vain, Decapitator...

char_188_helage_CN_029.voiceText: The price for leaving strife behind is to be embroiled in more strife.

char_188_helage_CN_030.voiceText: Don't look, I'm about to end their misery.

char_188_helage_CN_031.voiceText: Don't be careless. Every letdown is a chance for the enemy to turn the table.

char_188_helage_CN_032.voiceText: Failure is not shameful since lessons can be learned.

char_188_helage_CN_033.voiceText: I truly wish to find a shelter for the children.

char_188_helage_CN_036.voiceText: You want candy? I got some left, but beware of cavities.

char_260_durnar_CN_001.voiceText: Hey, how about getting someone more literate for this job? It's beyond a soldier like me who only knows how to follow orders!

char_260_durnar_CN_002.voiceText: Life is tough enough already. Relax with some butter, frosting and jam.

char_260_durnar_CN_003.voiceText: If Frostleaf wasn't still clutching her big axe, I would never have recognized her at all. Well, that was in a battle, and you could call us enemies then. But I'm relieved to see her living a good life at Rhodes Island.

char_260_durnar_CN_004.voiceText: Don't grab my weapon, Doctor! I just changed the Originium on that thing. It's dangerous when you hold it wrong... Look out! I, I'll take you to the infirmary...

char_260_durnar_CN_005.voiceText: For a Defender, our defensive ability is of paramount importance! I don't care whether it's organic Kevlar or ceramic padding, if it's the newest technology, just buy it!

char_260_durnar_CN_006.voiceText: Stories from my past? Don't have much to say. I mean, what kind of story could an ill-tempered soldier have? Merits and medals? That's nothing compared to the lives lost...

char_260_durnar_CN_007.voiceText: The recent recruits in the reserve are talented, but they're short on the little nuances of life. We were much better hiding cookies as rookies.

char_260_durnar_CN_008.voiceText: I've met with the logistic staff. From now on, they will write "Industrial Material" on the packaging of all snacks. Then it's up to you to sign off on it, Doctor.

char_260_durnar_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor? Oh, pardon me. I still can't get past certain things. If my former commander was anything like you, maybe... something like that wouldn't have happened.

char_260_durnar_CN_010.voiceText: Want some pop rocks? I'm sure I have a flavor that you'll like.

char_260_durnar_CN_011.voiceText: Hard as rock and lethal as lightning... That's me, Dur-nar. Nice to meet you, Doctor.

char_260_durnar_CN_012.voiceText: Ah, shoot, I'm out of popcorn.

char_260_durnar_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? Good, good, do I get paid more too? Awesome!

char_260_durnar_CN_014.voiceText: The old me only knew to charge ahead and fight for myself. Now, I fight for everyone. Just give your orders, Doctor.

char_260_durnar_CN_017.voiceText: I'm ready. Where am I needed?

char_260_durnar_CN_018.voiceText: I have only one request: Safety first and don't ever forget it.

char_260_durnar_CN_019.voiceText: We're off! Oh, keep an eye out around you.

char_260_durnar_CN_020.voiceText: Geez, it still smells awful on a battlefield.

char_260_durnar_CN_023.voiceText: I'll leave the support to you.

char_260_durnar_CN_029.voiceText: Ever heard of the Medal of Glory? I feel that's tailor-made for you.

char_260_durnar_CN_030.voiceText: Not burying the dead? Okay, we're done here!

char_260_durnar_CN_031.voiceText: The enemy still haven't gone far. Should we give chase?

char_260_durnar_CN_032.voiceText: Take it easy, Doctor. It's not your fault...

char_260_durnar_CN_033.voiceText: Whoa, it must cost a lot for the lavish interior, I bet!

char_260_durnar_CN_036.voiceText: You must be drunk to want to hear me sing war songs. Okay, don't you regret it.

char_355_ethan_CN_001.voiceText: Yo, Doctor! Is it time for my shift? Hmm? I suddenly popped up out of nowhere? No way, I just left the office.

char_355_ethan_CN_002.voiceText: My last job was with Reunion. Haven't I said that a bunch of times? Hey, aren't I voluntarily helping you with background checks and whatnot? Look, I wasn't involved with anything back when I was with Reunion, so I don't even have any guilt I'd like to wash away.

char_355_ethan_CN_003.voiceText: If there's anything I really hated about Reunion, it was the food! Of course it was the food! The staple food for my team was a piece of blackened hardtack that was as tough as a rock. I had to throw it in a pot and simmer it into a stew before I could stomach that stuff.

char_355_ethan_CN_004.voiceText: You should have run into Reunion's "Wraith" ops a few times before, right? I used to work there. I was tasked with conducting investigations and whatnot, but I never really did anything. When I was bored, I took out bets on who would get discovered the least. When I think back on it, I was basically bullying people.

char_355_ethan_CN_005.voiceText: What did I do before joining the Reunion Movement? Well, I was always hiding from those Infected hunters, but because of my sneaky little power here, they never found me, haha.... But, no matter how much I hid, I couldn't really do anything to actually help the Infected.

char_355_ethan_CN_006.voiceText: In the beginning, I would hide in the underground. I used to want to help out the Infected people, but over time, I turned a little sour, I guess. Fortunately, I'm back to being sweet again. What do I mean by that? You're asking that again? Just give it a rest already.

char_355_ethan_CN_007.voiceText: Camouflage Arts are very complicated! First you gotta get to know the materials and get a feel for these gadgets. Memorize the shape of each wall crack and the color of the soil and wood. If you don't, you'll be exposed and they'll get you easy.

char_355_ethan_CN_008.voiceText: You were the only one in the office, but the snacks disappeared as soon as you turned your head? Umm, tell you what. I understand. I'll make sure to catch the culprit, mhm.

char_355_ethan_CN_009.voiceText: So, this is the layout of the mission location? Ah, I see. Wow, you're really something. Your strategies are always so effective, no wonder why Reunion got their asses handed to them every time. All right, I'll get going now!

char_355_ethan_CN_010.voiceText: Huh? I didn't lock the door?

char_355_ethan_CN_011.voiceText: You're asking where I am? I'm right in front of you! You can call me Ethan. You're asking me what happened just now? Haha, I can't answer that yet!

char_355_ethan_CN_012.voiceText: Where am I? But, I'm right here! Look at the security camera, top left on this screen. Top left corner!

char_355_ethan_CN_013.voiceText: Haha, I told you before right? You won't regret putting work into my hands.

char_355_ethan_CN_014.voiceText: Yo, Doctor. Make sure to remember the little guys, especially me. I could die in battle somewhere and nobody would even realize I'm gone. So please, I'm trusting you to remember where I am!

char_355_ethan_CN_017.voiceText: You said that wall just moved right in front of your eyes? Haha, you've gotta be exaggerating, right?

char_355_ethan_CN_018.voiceText: Eyyy! I'm the captain now, so you'd all better listen up!

char_355_ethan_CN_019.voiceText: Don't panic, even if you realize you're the only one left on the team!

char_355_ethan_CN_020.voiceText: Is it time to fight? Let me hide first!

char_355_ethan_CN_026.voiceText: Violence won't solve all your problems, but taking care of you isn't a problem either!

char_355_ethan_CN_029.voiceText: Are we done fighting? Ahh, I'm beat!

char_355_ethan_CN_030.voiceText: I worked pretty hard. You saw me, right? Right?

char_355_ethan_CN_031.voiceText: So what if they got away. Let 'em go.

char_355_ethan_CN_032.voiceText: You should go first, at least I can grab their legs.

char_355_ethan_CN_033.voiceText: Nice room you got here. Let's see what sticks out the most.

char_355_ethan_CN_036.voiceText: Hey, want to go take a stroll?

char_355_ethan_CN_042.voiceText: Hey Doctor, you look like you're in a nice mood. Did something good happen?

char_275_breeze_CN_001.voiceText: If you need help, I will gladly help out. Just remember to return the favor some time.

char_275_breeze_CN_002.voiceText: Verna... Err, I mean, Miss Siege, always gives me a feeling that I can't describe. Why is that...?

char_275_breeze_CN_003.voiceText: My dad? Oh my, you're asking me that even though you know I ran away from home? Doctor, are you perhaps socially awkward?

char_275_breeze_CN_004.voiceText: {@nickname}, be sure to try my dishes...did you taste the herbs? Oh my, why would I ever use the Doctor as my taste tester? Heehee...

char_275_breeze_CN_005.voiceText: I used to think that my parents were numb and stuffy so I ran away from home to look for a new life. After going far and wide and experiencing a lot, I think I'm beginning to understand how they felt. Haha, what do you think you're doing~

char_275_breeze_CN_006.voiceText: {@nickname}, do you see those scattered clouds over there? That's the direction of my hometown.

char_275_breeze_CN_007.voiceText: "Faith" is an interesting topic. Although I didn't have the chance to go to Laterano, I didn't expect to hear all about Laterano's deeds on Rhodes Island. Always thought it was too Hey, that energetic girl over there... was Laterano always such a lively place?

char_275_breeze_CN_008.voiceText: The boats in Toron need the lighthouse to make their way back to port, and Rhodes Island is the safe haven at the end of my last journey. So, {@nickname}, it's up to you you have to be able to do what I can't.

char_275_breeze_CN_009.voiceText: Right here, right now, is where Grace Arizona places her faith. Dr. {@nickname}, you hold my hopes in your hands, forever more.

char_275_breeze_CN_010.voiceText: ...You made a strange expression in your dream. Are you feeling uneasy, Doctor?

char_275_breeze_CN_011.voiceText: Breeze, a traveling scholar from Toron County. It is a pleasure to meet you, Doctor. I've had enough of formal etiquette, so this will be the last of it.

char_275_breeze_CN_012.voiceText: ...Stunning medical skills, thats Rhodes Island for you.

char_275_breeze_CN_013.voiceText: I shall bestow this blessing upon you for your gift, Doctor. Hmm? Your reaction was such a downer. This calls for a serious hand-kiss, you know. Hurry up and get to it!

char_275_breeze_CN_014.voiceText: Well, this time won't be as formal as the last. Are you looking forward to it? I will dedicate everything to Rhodes Island, a pledge that transcends my consciousness.

char_275_breeze_CN_017.voiceText: Leave the medical work to me.

char_275_breeze_CN_018.voiceText: Thank you for your trust. I will make sure to prioritize the safety of the Operators.

char_275_breeze_CN_020.voiceText: Those who seek to inflict harm on others have no right to ask for forgiveness.

char_275_breeze_CN_024.voiceText: Make sure to look after yourself.

char_275_breeze_CN_030.voiceText: Every victory creates a kindling that will flourish into an everlasting fire.

char_275_breeze_CN_031.voiceText: Keep your senses alert, for danger lurks ahead.

char_275_breeze_CN_032.voiceText: Why are you always fixated on hurting others...

char_275_breeze_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, would you like to hear the story of my hometown?

char_248_mgllan_CN_001.voiceText: I will stay with you until the next expedition, Doctor. If you need me at your side, please do not be afraid to call upon me boldly!

char_248_mgllan_CN_002.voiceText: Actually, I've known about you for a long time, Doctor! Well, Mayer and MuMu told me all about you, so I had to come to Rhodes Island to see what you are like in person... Oh, I also brought a small present for you! Here!

char_248_mgllan_CN_003.voiceText: This one? This is the pendant of the Great Emperor of Penguin Logistics. I used to see it many times when I went to Penguin Logistics. I always thought it was really cute. Every time, I used to rub it a whole lot! Doctor, you've never rubbed it before? You didn't dare? Why?!

char_248_mgllan_CN_004.voiceText: Is Iffy doing better these days? When I left Rhine Lab last time, I was really worried about her condition...

char_248_mgllan_CN_005.voiceText: Has Mayer made anything new recently? I haven't worked on any new equipment for a long time so I should do some research with her. Oh right, Doctor, let me let you in on a secret on what happens when you disturb Mayer... Oh no! You've already been bitten before?

char_248_mgllan_CN_006.voiceText: My drone and Meeboo, Sisyphus and Kirkika, are not controlled the same way. There is no limit to the types of uses they can have. However, there is currently a new system under development and it will soon be ready. Hehe, I'm looking forward to it.

char_248_mgllan_CN_007.voiceText: The Polar North? The dreams that are buried there are cold and cruel, but... in order to make my dreams a reality, I am willing to do anything it takes.

char_248_mgllan_CN_008.voiceText: "The tiny gardner, and the tiny flower, growing under the tile with no one to care for it..." This was Iffy's favorite story to read, perhaps due to how she can relate to it. However... she seems to have forgotten the book here. How odd.

char_248_mgllan_CN_009.voiceText: The Polar North...that place is both mysterious and beautiful. The towering cliffs, the lonely, snow-covered trees, and the source of the radiant snow all stretch to the end of the earth. Doctor, you should go with me. Let's head there together, okay?

char_248_mgllan_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor? Doctor you can't! If you fall asleep, you'll freeze to death!

char_248_mgllan_CN_011.voiceText: Rhine Lab Commissioner Magallan discovered a mysterous research ship? Woah, y-you're that doctor from Rhodes Island, Ahem... Would you like to join my expedition? It'll be very interesting!

char_248_mgllan_CN_013.voiceText: Update completed! Now the response speed of the device is twice as fast as before.

char_248_mgllan_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor, if you want to see the results of my research, then I must also demonstrate my strength! Hehehe, just so you know, I'm very strong, so don't be scared!

char_248_mgllan_CN_017.voiceText: Leave the exploration and support to me.

char_248_mgllan_CN_020.voiceText: Once the drone is commissioned, it can take off at any time.

char_248_mgllan_CN_025.voiceText: Is the target marked? Ok, the drone is launched!

char_248_mgllan_CN_026.voiceText: Now! Snow blindness is a terrible think, you know!

char_248_mgllan_CN_029.voiceText: Watch out, that's a blind spot! Huh, it's already over? As expected, Doctor, you're so reliable.

char_248_mgllan_CN_030.voiceText: There are no other hostile signals.

char_248_mgllan_CN_031.voiceText: There are still enemies nearby. Will you pursue them?

char_248_mgllan_CN_032.voiceText: We've been surrounded? Its my fault...

char_248_mgllan_CN_033.voiceText: Huh? Th-there are even heated floors?! Ahh~ this is bliss~

char_248_mgllan_CN_036.voiceText: Lets go, Lets go! Ice skating is not that scary with me here.

char_131_flameb_CN_001.voiceText: {@nickname}, today's battlefields are too fragile and juvenile compared to the ones of the past. It's enough to make one's weapons rust. And once a soldier's weapons rust, death soon follows.

char_131_flameb_CN_002.voiceText: Life is but a brief flicker before the vast maw of annihilation. Cherish the glimpse of the sunset on the deck while you still can, {@nickname}.

char_131_flameb_CN_003.voiceText: Practical exercises? I'm not interested. While Rhodes Island boasts many powerful warriors, squandering one's physical strength in a game is gratuitous. Only in the edge between life and death does the clashing of swords have any value.

char_131_flameb_CN_004.voiceText: I'm not concerned about the plight of the Infected? Don't misunderstand me - I only despise fighting in vain. No enemy worth spilling my blood over has appeared yet, and that's all there is to it.

char_131_flameb_CN_005.voiceText: Teamwork will rob one of the instincts that are liberated only through rampant slaughter. What "trust" and "strategizing" buy you are nothing but convenient illusions, and these illusions will one day take your life, {@nickname}.

char_131_flameb_CN_006.voiceText: This blade ran through two crown princes, and this other one slew three generals. In this chaotic world, anything can happen. I don't know who will claim my life one day, but when it happens, I sure hope it will be more exciting than when I killed these people.

char_131_flameb_CN_007.voiceText: Shining, huh? A pity, but she could have been a very worthy adversary. But after getting pulled into that situation with the "Sinners," she felt like her blade had been besmirched. Swordsmen who do not acknowledge their own weapon are not worth mentioning.

char_131_flameb_CN_008.voiceText: {@nickname}, you remember that battle, right? After killing all the ambushers, I lead the survivors and charged straight into the traitor's fortress. I was the only one who made it out alive. How'd that all start? Oh, you know the answer to that. I've seen you before, and my memory is very good.

char_131_flameb_CN_009.voiceText: {@nickname}, help me fetch those seeds in the cupboard, won't you? Thank you. Yes, I'm actually quite fond of flowers. No matter how brilliantly they blossom, their petals must wither and fall into the wind. When will the petals next wither, {@nickname}?

char_131_flameb_CN_011.voiceText: We meet again, {@nickname}. Don't worry, I understand the situation you're in now, and pose no threat to you. I shall be your blade, so use me as you see fit, Doctor.

char_131_flameb_CN_012.voiceText: The skills of a great warrior cannot be recorded.

char_131_flameb_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion? So you also care about these rituals.

char_131_flameb_CN_014.voiceText: I have no consciousness of what it's like to be Infected. Perhaps Rhodes Island can help me understand. I don't care, but you have your own considerations. I'll hear them out.

char_131_flameb_CN_017.voiceText: Ahh, I've longed for a hurricane of blood.

char_131_flameb_CN_018.voiceText: I've been a captain before, and it did not end well.

char_131_flameb_CN_019.voiceText: I will bathe in their blood.

char_131_flameb_CN_023.voiceText: So, who will be my next opponent?

char_131_flameb_CN_024.voiceText: Will it be you? Or maybe you?

char_131_flameb_CN_027.voiceText: Whose name will you cry as you pass?

char_131_flameb_CN_030.voiceText: A weak enemy proves nothing. Search for a worthier battlefield.

char_131_flameb_CN_031.voiceText: A dedicated opponent will prove to be a worthy adversary in the future, let them do just that.

char_131_flameb_CN_032.voiceText: You guys get out of here, destroying pursuing enemies has always been my duty.

char_131_flameb_CN_036.voiceText: I seem to have used up this whetstone...

char_279_excu_CN_001.voiceText: You can focus on your work, Doctor. The fragmentation mines are in place, such that none may interfere with your work or rest.

char_279_excu_CN_002.voiceText: I know not whose work this is, but I am well aware that there are those here at Rhodes Island who specialize in infiltration and assassination. They are hidden here on this vessel. My mind is just playing tricks on me? Nonsense, Doctor. My mind never plays tricks on me.

char_279_excu_CN_003.voiceText: I serve the Laterano Notarial Hall, so I rarely live in Laterano. Even if you live in other city-states, all rights and privileges of Laterano citizens still depend on the support of the Hall. For example, in my case, my work has more to do with the condemned than with the living.

char_279_excu_CN_004.voiceText: The control system is denying you access? Please allow me to check it. Mm, it appears to be a front-end crash caused by inputting an erroneous command. It has nothing to do with the framework and is easily solved. Please feel free to ask me if you have any similar issues in the future. I understand machines far better than I do people.

char_279_excu_CN_005.voiceText: There are many Sankta here at Rhodes Island who use a gun. I am not like them. They will not fire at others because of the restrictions in place, whereas I will not hesitate to fire upon citizens of other countries if need be. Of course, there is hardly a need for that, because my fists are more than sufficient to deal with most problems.

char_279_excu_CN_006.voiceText: Do not worry about the Notarial Hall. They are all reasonable people. Because the agreement I signed with Rhodes Island is in line with their protocols, they will never do anything to make your life more difficult. As a matter of fact, I think you are well suited for notarial work yourself. They always welcome foreign employees.

char_279_excu_CN_007.voiceText: I have a distant relative who had great musical talent ever since she was a child. Contrary to what others expected, she was able to embark on this tumultous path. Fortunately, she seems to hate me very much because I cannot see the illusion she creates, nor understand what it means to people.

char_279_excu_CN_008.voiceText: Private disputes are more frequent than public conflicts, as chaos is the norm over order. Those who would open fire upon me at first glance outnumber those who would open their doors to me. But it matters not, for I can complete any commission, whether it is killing a living person on behalf of the dead, or creating a dead person on behalf of the living.

char_279_excu_CN_009.voiceText: Being treated as an aberration is normal to me, because I cannot understand other people, nor do I have any desire to deal with them. On the contrary, talking to you is quite interesting to me. Neither you nor the Notarial Hall has denied me because of the way I live, which puts me at ease. Thank you.

char_279_excu_CN_010.voiceText: Rest is required, Doctor. Please take it easy.

char_279_excu_CN_011.voiceText: Well met, Doctor of Rhodes Island. I am a Laterano citizen who signed a clean-up agreement with your company. Here is my certificate. Am I required to give my name? If you insist, you may call me Executor.

char_279_excu_CN_012.voiceText: There is value in referencing these battles.

char_279_excu_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you. I have already prepared all the ammunition I need for the next battle. If the situation worsens, please allow me to use heavier firepower. Promotion? I have already thanked you for that.

char_279_excu_CN_014.voiceText: Another promotion? I understand, there must be another infiltration operation then. Perhaps you even need me to penetrate the heart of the enemy. I have no objections to that. Hmm? This is just about a promotion? Why's that?

char_279_excu_CN_017.voiceText: The law states that the executor must achieve his maximum potential.

char_279_excu_CN_018.voiceText: I am not good at working with others.

char_279_excu_CN_024.voiceText: The law is the only truth.

char_279_excu_CN_026.voiceText: I have taken care of the living and the dead.

char_279_excu_CN_028.voiceText: If necessary, I will break the taboo.

char_279_excu_CN_029.voiceText: Mission completed. All contracts successfully fulfilled.

char_279_excu_CN_031.voiceText: Mission completed. Some flaws in the completion.

char_279_excu_CN_033.voiceText: Do not worry about me. I have no need for a stable home.

char_279_excu_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, what do I need to do?

char_190_clour_CN_001.voiceText: Did you call me here for a new hunt? Oh, not quite...?

char_190_clour_CN_002.voiceText: This claw pendant? It's a symbol of my vengeance. Those Ursus mercenaries who harmed my companions treat these things as dogtags, so there's no mistaking them.

char_190_clour_CN_003.voiceText: I lost my left hand to a beast that I was hunting. Luckily, a mechanic helped make me a prosthetic limb so that I can draw my bowstring again.

char_190_clour_CN_004.voiceText: The old me wouldve turned anyone who dared to mock my scars into a pincushion, one arrow at a time! But now? Well, people like those arent worth the effort.

char_190_clour_CN_005.voiceText: If you're ever facing a difficult decision, let your instincts decide for you, and your body will not lie. This is the experience I've had as an expert hunter.

char_190_clour_CN_006.voiceText: I've been living alone ever since my companions passed away, so I'm still getting used to being surrounded by people... But since you've given me your trust and depend on me, I swear I'll return the favor.

char_190_clour_CN_007.voiceText: Ehh, it seems like a pebble got stuck in my prosthetic finger...? What a pain, looks like I'm going to have to find a mechanic to fix it up... N-no, I don't need your help, I can handle this by myself!

char_190_clour_CN_008.voiceText: You'll make sure I won't ever lose any more companions? Hmph. Big words, but let's see you back it up!

char_190_clour_CN_009.voiceText: The doctors here offered to get rid of my more recent scars, but I refused. I want to keep them, because they're a proof of my service here... You, you understand what I'm getting at?

char_190_clour_CN_010.voiceText: You're asleep? Can you fall asleep just about anywhere? Well, that's a trait that many of us hunters share...

char_190_clour_CN_011.voiceText: Vermeil, hunter. You won't regret giving work to me.

char_190_clour_CN_012.voiceText: Can I take another look at that?

char_190_clour_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you, but... are you sure you're fine with promoting someone like me?

char_190_clour_CN_014.voiceText: I don't really care about stuff like Oripathy or "the rest of my life." Right now, what could make me happier than being able to fight by your side on the battlefield?

char_190_clour_CN_018.voiceText: You want me to be the captain? Am I... really cut out for the job?

char_190_clour_CN_019.voiceText: The big game hunting is about to start!

char_190_clour_CN_020.voiceText: Those who have fallen in my trap, do you understand your current predicament?

char_190_clour_CN_023.voiceText: I can smell the prey in the wind.

char_190_clour_CN_025.voiceText: If you don't escape, you will only have one ending.

char_190_clour_CN_026.voiceText: Don't underestimate the people of the wilderness!

char_190_clour_CN_028.voiceText: This arrow will find your throat!

char_190_clour_CN_029.voiceText: A strong prey is still just prey.

char_190_clour_CN_030.voiceText: Impressive. If you were born in Siracusa, you would have definitely been an excellent hunter.

char_190_clour_CN_031.voiceText: The prey got away. I'll pursue it.

char_190_clour_CN_032.voiceText: We can't let things end like this...

char_190_clour_CN_033.voiceText: As long as there's four walls and a ceiling, it's more than enough for me.

char_190_clour_CN_036.voiceText: Today's plans? Helping out with missions, shooting arrows at enemies until I have no more arrows, then heading back to eat and sleep. Pretty simple.

char_213_mostma_CN_001.voiceText: Ahaha, aren't you the lucky one, Doctor? I don't have any work for the day, so I wouldn't mind keeping you company for a bit.

char_213_mostma_CN_002.voiceText: The marketplaces of Lungmen, the suburbs of Ursus, the ancient ruins of Victoria Doctor, this world holds countless beautiful sights, but very few people will ever seek them out.

char_213_mostma_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor, do you want to hear a story of my journeys? In that case, I'd recommend preparing some fine tea cakes before we sit down. Otherwise, even the most fascinating tales will turn bland.

char_213_mostma_CN_004.voiceText: I've witnessed the rise and fall of many organizations, but so far, Rhodes Island is the most interesting one I've seen. Will the epochs bend to your will, or finally swallow you whole? I'm dying to find out.

char_213_mostma_CN_005.voiceText: Doctor, concerning our next destination, I have a few recommendations for where we can get some good food. Interested?

char_213_mostma_CN_006.voiceText: Doctor, you seem to already know a thing or two about fallen angels. Unfortunately, I can't give you any more details than that. Even if I could share everything else with you one day, this would remain my solitary secret.

char_213_mostma_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, you don't need to concern yourself with how to have a good relationship with me. For me, friends, family, and love I have nothing against them, but I don't need them either. Heh, not like that's going to stop you from trying, right? Well, I don't really mind, so give it your best shot~

char_213_mostma_CN_008.voiceText: I'm back Huh? No way, Doctor, were you seriously waiting here for me the whole time? You even brought snacks Hah, all right. If you're going to go this far, I guess I can't turn you down. As thanks, I'll tell you about something interesting that happened on a delivery run.

char_213_mostma_CN_009.voiceText: I see now. When I thought of having a friend like you, the spark of joy I felt wasn't fake after all. Scrap what I said before, Doctor. Maybe I do need a bit of warmth in my life.

char_213_mostma_CN_011.voiceText: Hey there, Doctor. You might've heard from Emperor that I'm not bound by the contract between Penguin Logistics and Rhodes Island, and can therefore act independently. Having that said, I'll probably be staying here anyway when I'm not busy, so I'll see you around~

char_213_mostma_CN_012.voiceText: Let me see how Rhodes Island fights.

char_213_mostma_CN_013.voiceText: Doctor, relying on me isn't a very wise decision.

char_213_mostma_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor, you really want to see me go all out? Just for the record, I'd like to ask - I won't have to worry about paying for the collateral damage after this, right?

char_213_mostma_CN_018.voiceText: Hmm... Sorry, but why don't we let everyone do their own thing?

char_213_mostma_CN_019.voiceText: If this is the place I'll lead the way.

char_213_mostma_CN_025.voiceText: Seventy percent-ish should do the trick.

char_213_mostma_CN_026.voiceText: Isn't it about time to wrap things up?

char_213_mostma_CN_027.voiceText: I have nothing against you guys, but this is just a part of life.

char_213_mostma_CN_028.voiceText: What should we get to eat after this?

char_213_mostma_CN_029.voiceText: Some thrill-seeking every now and then isn't half bad either.

char_213_mostma_CN_030.voiceText: Hm? I thought I missed a few, but I guess that's a job well done.

char_213_mostma_CN_031.voiceText: For a transporter, the results of a battle don't really matter. Just surviving is enough of a victory.

char_213_mostma_CN_032.voiceText: I guess I don't get this whole "teamwork" thing after all...

char_213_mostma_CN_033.voiceText: Mind if I go wander around?

char_325_bison_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, do you need my help transporting anything?

char_325_bison_CN_002.voiceText: This noisy metal music sounds like Exusiai is throwing another one of her parties again. Doctor, should I go reprimand her?

char_325_bison_CN_003.voiceText: I'm quite good with manual labor. I also know a bit about company management as well. So, Doctor, is there anywhere I can be of use?

char_325_bison_CN_004.voiceText: My parents were the first generation to settle in Lungmen, so I'm actually a Lungmen native Doctor, if there's anything you'd like to learn about it, I wouldn't mind helping you out.

char_325_bison_CN_005.voiceText: Doctor, if you want to know how a real logistics company operates, it'd be best to just ask me directly. Penguin Logistics is more of an exception than the rule, and though I don't mean this in a bad way, they don't have any reference value whatsoever.

char_325_bison_CN_006.voiceText: What do I like to do outside of work? Other than just resting, I'll sometimes accompany Croissant on her shopping trips and make sure she doesn't waste too much money Doctor, do you also want to come along?

char_325_bison_CN_007.voiceText: I used to believe that for any company to survive in the long run, standardization and efficiency were of critical importance. That's why at first, I couldn't fathom how a company like Penguin Logistics could stay afloat.
