char_325_bison_CN_008.voiceText: After getting to know more about the people at Penguin Logistics and talking to them, I began to understand that the world is much broader than I had thought. There's nothing wrong with structure and rules, but they don't necessarily apply to everyone.

char_325_bison_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, perhaps you haven't realized this yourself, but the fact that you can unite so many people with very different personalities under one banner is no simple feat It'd be great if I could become more like you one day.

char_325_bison_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor You're taking a nap? I guess it can wait. Guess I'll start tidying up the place first.

char_325_bison_CN_011.voiceText: Pleased to meet you, Doctor. My name is Bison. According to the terms of our contract, I will now also be a member of Rhodes Island. I look forward to working with you.

char_325_bison_CN_012.voiceText: Thank you very much. I will make sure to learn from this.

char_325_bison_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you very much, Doctor. As long as I put my best foot forward, my hard work will be rewarded. This is what I believe.

char_325_bison_CN_014.voiceText: At Penguin Logistics and Rhodes Island, I saw a more expansive world than before Doctor, one day, I will also find my place in this world.

char_325_bison_CN_018.voiceText: On-site command? I have some experience with that.

char_325_bison_CN_019.voiceText: Yes, I've noted the mission location and objectives.

char_325_bison_CN_020.voiceText: Hah I won't be a burden on the others.

char_325_bison_CN_021.voiceText: What would you like me to do?

char_325_bison_CN_026.voiceText: Hang in there a bit longer? Understood.

char_325_bison_CN_027.voiceText: Don't worry, my shield still holds firm.

char_325_bison_CN_029.voiceText: Way to go, Doctor! You must be the kind of leader that every company wants to have if you wanted to change jobs.

char_325_bison_CN_030.voiceText: Wow, Doctor You really are amazing!

char_325_bison_CN_031.voiceText: The basic objectives of the mission have been accomplished. This should be good enough, right?

char_325_bison_CN_032.voiceText: Don't feel down, Doctor. We'll have another chance.

char_325_bison_CN_033.voiceText: So this is the inside of Rhodes Island It sure is big.

char_325_bison_CN_036.voiceText: Sora's new album is really good.

char_243_waaifu_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, where are you going? Shouldn't you be working? Lunch? Well then, I'm coming along. There's a few things I want to buy, and I can protect you too.

char_243_waaifu_CN_002.voiceText: Sorry, Doctor, Rhodes Island is just a part-time job for me. I have to study hard to make sure I have a nice, normal future ahead of me. I am committed to keeping in touch with everyday society.

char_243_waaifu_CN_003.voiceText: I color coded all the documents to be sent out, the backups have already been delivered, your schedule is right here. I bought your late night snack and put it in the refrigerator. Don't forget to heat it up. And last, oh, do you need me to change the light bulb in your office for you?

char_243_waaifu_CN_004.voiceText: Did I ever tell you about my other job? No? Well, I won't. Don't look at me like that, Doctor. There's just not much to say. If my other office worked a tenth as hard as Rhodes Island does, they'd monopolize Lungmen's entire investigations industry.

char_243_waaifu_CN_005.voiceText: You wonder where I learned martial arts? Well, I have my nasty old dad and his weird education to thank for that. Not that I resent kung fu. A hero must uphold justice. Martial arts are a part of me.

char_243_waaifu_CN_006.voiceText: Just like the human heart, martial arts have yin and yang, right and wrong. To right those wrongs, to defeat evil, to counter bad kung fu, these are all second nature to me. The world is dark, and someone must stand for justice.

char_243_waaifu_CN_007.voiceText: You think you just saw me? In downtown Lungmen? That may have been me. I just finished class. Hm? You saw me beat down some thugs who were harassing a passerby? And then slipped away before the police arrived? Must have been someone else. Heh heh. Definitely. That's enough about that.

char_243_waaifu_CN_008.voiceText: My rotten dad said he had to go find the true meaning of kung fu. I still don't know where he is. Please! What year does he think it is? Find some common sense and learn some responsibility before you get yourself killed. But at least I haven't forgotten what he taught me: "Martial arts have martial virtue, humans have human kindness."

char_243_waaifu_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, did any mail come for me? It did? Great. These are my grades... my very important grades! It's been straight A's for me, so far. If I don't work hard enough, I'll end up regretting all the things I wasn't strong enough to do.

char_243_waaifu_CN_010.voiceText: Falling asleep at a time like this... Oh well, I'll just finish your work for you.

char_243_waaifu_CN_011.voiceText: Is this Rhodes Island? Nice to meet you. I'm Waai Fu, your new part-timer. Please don't go easy on me. I can handle anything you ask of me.

char_243_waaifu_CN_012.voiceText: If I can fight like this here, I can definitely knock them out.

char_243_waaifu_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you very much. I won't let you down, Doctor.

char_243_waaifu_CN_014.voiceText: I often witness injustices in my life. If I ever find myself unable to stop them, I reflect on the moment, and force myself to get stronger. So, if ever you need me, don't hesitate to say so. I'll be there, with all my strength!

char_243_waaifu_CN_018.voiceText: I don't have much experience, but I won't turn down the responsibility.

char_243_waaifu_CN_019.voiceText: Fight evil with the fist of justice!

char_243_waaifu_CN_020.voiceText: Like cutting weeds and pulling roots!

char_243_waaifu_CN_025.voiceText: You have turned your backs on society!

char_243_waaifu_CN_026.voiceText: Pick on someone your own size!

char_243_waaifu_CN_027.voiceText: Behold, the power of the Song Do Bart Cham style!

char_243_waaifu_CN_028.voiceText: The mind directs, the fist executes!

char_243_waaifu_CN_029.voiceText: Foul intentions lead a foul life. Repent now. There is still time.

char_243_waaifu_CN_031.voiceText: That was not enough. I need to train more.

char_243_waaifu_CN_032.voiceText: Father... I'm still... not strong enough.

char_243_waaifu_CN_033.voiceText: At least it's better than some old, messy detective agency.

char_243_waaifu_CN_034.voiceText: An ambush...?! Doctor, don't sneak up on me like that. You'll end up in Medical.

char_243_waaifu_CN_036.voiceText: You want to go for a walk? I'll go with you. You'll be safe with me.

char_133_mm_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, even though I'm now your employee, if your conduct is even slightly shady, I won't stand by idly!

char_133_mm_CN_002.voiceText: Rhodes Island has a suspicious smell about it

char_133_mm_CN_003.voiceText: Careful observation is fundamental to all investigations! It might seem basic, but it always works!

char_133_mm_CN_004.voiceText: You, over there! Face me, and put your hands where I can see 'em! Ah, sorry I got the wrong person

char_133_mm_CN_005.voiceText: I always thought that penguin over there is super suspicious. Look, even though it dresses like that, it spends money like it's water or something. It's even wearing a gold necklace! You know how much detectives like me make that kind of lifestyle is simply unthinkable!

char_133_mm_CN_006.voiceText: Mmmm... so frustrating! How am I going to investigate that shady logistics company? ...Should I break in? Err, but those two guards give off fierce vibes that make my skin crawl No, no, I'm not scared or anything, I'll just have to use my head and come up with a plan!

char_133_mm_CN_007.voiceText: Why are you giving me this bean paste bun? I would neber eat shumfing libe ris on an inweshtigation, you musht watch too mush TV or(chewing) A real detective only eats donuts while on a mission!

char_133_mm_CN_008.voiceText: Three months, then three months after that. Then another three months after that. I've already been undercover for ten months! Chief, what the heck is going on? Hey! You scoundrels, stop eavesdropping on my call!

char_133_mm_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, that penguin seems to have noticed that I'm investigating it I'm starting to fear for my life!

char_133_mm_CN_010.voiceText: Wake up! Waaake uppp! Stop slacking off!

char_133_mm_CN_011.voiceText: I'm the Royal Detective, May. Please cooperate with my investigation! Eh? I've got the wrong address? Impossible! I have evidence that proves that penguin is hiding here!

char_133_mm_CN_012.voiceText: Don't I look super cool when I'm conducting my investigation?

char_133_mm_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you for the promotion Chief I'm so very grateful for Hey, wait, you aren't even my real boss!

char_133_mm_CN_014.voiceText: Elite team? Hey, I'm a Royal Detective! Why am I being promoted by some mercenary organization?!

char_133_mm_CN_017.voiceText: Be careful not to let any shady people onto the team.

char_133_mm_CN_018.voiceText: Hehehe! Leader? Nay, call me Inspector General!

char_133_mm_CN_019.voiceText: All troops, move out! All troops, moooove outttt!!

char_133_mm_CN_020.voiceText: You criminals! Behave and turn yourselves in!

char_133_mm_CN_023.voiceText: It's time to investigate the scene!

char_133_mm_CN_027.voiceText: Now you're going to get a taste of my taser!

char_133_mm_CN_028.voiceText: It won't hurt, it'll just give you a little buzz!

char_133_mm_CN_029.voiceText: For a master detective, there is no case that can't be solved!

char_133_mm_CN_030.voiceText: Take away all these suspects! Ugh Fine, I'll do it myself...

char_133_mm_CN_031.voiceText: Hmm I feel like we missed some of the clues?

char_133_mm_CN_033.voiceText: I have a hunch as to what will happen here!

char_133_mm_CN_034.voiceText: You and your villainous hand! I'll remember this!

char_133_mm_CN_036.voiceText: D-don't think you can wash away your crime just like that!

char_356_broca_CN_002.voiceText: That Amiya girl is one of this place's leaders? What a black-hearted organization Rhodes Island is.

char_356_broca_CN_003.voiceText: I have no intent on being a freeloader. If you need any manual labor done, just let me know.

char_356_broca_CN_004.voiceText: I have nothing against taking orders, but I don't like fighting without knowing why I'm doing it.

char_356_broca_CN_005.voiceText: My hobbies? I have no reason to tell you, do I? Good grief, stop making that face. You'll leave me alone if I tell you, right I like modifying various things.

char_356_broca_CN_006.voiceText: Back then, had it not been for Chiave and Aosta, I would've been dead in that alley. So, my life belongs to them. No matter what they want me to do, I will do it without hesitation.

char_356_broca_CN_007.voiceText: I don't hate you, but I find it difficult to fully trust you.

char_356_broca_CN_008.voiceText: Work hard, make money, and continue surviving. I used to think that was all there was to life. However, Aosta was right. In a country like Siracusa, something like that is nothing more than a pipe dream.

char_356_broca_CN_009.voiceText: I acknowledge your right to lead. However, Aosta once said that corruption begins to seep into an organization the moment you let your guard down. To prevent that from happening, I'll be keeping a close eye on you.

char_356_broca_CN_010.voiceText: Asleep? Good grief, what a carefree fellow Tch, where'd the blanket go

char_356_broca_CN_011.voiceText: Since Chiave decided for me to join you, I don't have much else to say. You can call me Broca. I will listen to your orders, but don't count on me to do anything extra. I have no love for large organizations like yours.

char_356_broca_CN_013.voiceText: A raise? Don't particularly need it.

char_356_broca_CN_014.voiceText: Maybe Aosta was right, maybe Rhodes Island is trustworthy. If that's the case, I

char_356_broca_CN_030.voiceText: They've all been taken care of.

char_356_broca_CN_031.voiceText: Need me to go after them?

char_356_broca_CN_032.voiceText: No need to panic. You did what you could. Even Aosta makes mistakes.

char_261_sddrag_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, here is the paperwork. It's strange to see me doing clerical work? The truth is I prefer this to fighting

char_261_sddrag_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor, look outside the window. Night a peaceful night. Up until now, every night was always filled with the red glow of flames and the stench of burning. But, a night like this is calming.

char_261_sddrag_CN_003.voiceText: A red-haired Vouivre girl has been staring at me for a while... Does she suspect my identity? But, she doesn't have any evidence. Mm, I won't let her find it.

char_261_sddrag_CN_004.voiceText: Is it time for my regular medical examination? U-understood But, I can't trust those other doctors. If I have to be examined, I want you to do it.

char_261_sddrag_CN_005.voiceText: You all have a lot of questions, but I can't answer any of them. This is for your sake, but this is also a warning Please keep that in mind.

char_261_sddrag_CN_006.voiceText: I am strong. I know well how terrifying my power is... but that brings me no joy. If you desire it though, I will fight.

char_261_sddrag_CN_007.voiceText: This spear I am not able to fully use its power. Despite that, I've still taken so many lives. Guilt? No, I feel none. Our lives are all equally worthless after all.

char_261_sddrag_CN_008.voiceText: I'm not worried about Oripathy. Without it, I would not have had a chance to be here. It'll take my life? That's fine. There are so many other things in this world that can as well, so why why are you so fixated about this particular one?

char_261_sddrag_CN_009.voiceText: I am a shadow, but that is fine. I am only able to stay here incognito because I am a shadow But, if someone with the same face as me ever finds you, don't fight that person... because you'll die. I don't want you to die.

char_261_sddrag_CN_010.voiceText: I will stand vigil for you, so... please rest at ease. Good night.

char_261_sddrag_CN_011.voiceText: You were the ones who saved me? My name? Just "Reed" is fine. Like the reeds by a pond. A nondescript existence.

char_261_sddrag_CN_012.voiceText: Your battles are very bitter. But, this way, many more may continue to live.

char_261_sddrag_CN_013.voiceText: Forward, soldiers of Dublin! I used to always force myself to say this, but in reality I've hated it

char_261_sddrag_CN_014.voiceText: You have a dream that calms my soul and I want to help you accomplish it. If I can call upon the flames of Dublin, I can become the flame that lights your way in the dark.

char_261_sddrag_CN_017.voiceText: The flames of war will char the wilderness.

char_261_sddrag_CN_018.voiceText: Because you said so, I will not neglect the lives of others.

char_261_sddrag_CN_019.voiceText: In that case, we shall go collect our harvest.

char_261_sddrag_CN_020.voiceText: Why are you as flammable as stalks of wheat?

char_261_sddrag_CN_022.voiceText: Nobody will see that I'm here, right?

char_261_sddrag_CN_025.voiceText: The living flame will purify your tainted forms.

char_261_sddrag_CN_029.voiceText: Endless battles, flames that never cease smoldering This is not what you truly desire, is it?

char_261_sddrag_CN_030.voiceText: For the sake of our future, I can bear anything

char_261_sddrag_CN_031.voiceText: There is nothing we can gain from the battlefield. Let's go. Hurry, let's go home

char_261_sddrag_CN_032.voiceText: No. I won't let anyone hurt you I swear it

char_261_sddrag_CN_033.voiceText: Can I have a separate room? I don't care how small it is

char_261_sddrag_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor won't my body temperature burn you?

char_017_huang_CN_001.voiceText: I'm telling you, I'm no good with paperwork. Are you sure you want me here in the office? I'd be better in the field; wouldn't you be happy too if I brought back some good results?

char_017_huang_CN_002.voiceText: I fight for the Infected. Anyone with eyes can clearly see our struggle, but too many people simply don't give a damn about our lives. But I do, a whole lot of 'em too. Got a lot of Operators here counting on me, and I don't plan to fall short of their expectations.

char_017_huang_CN_003.voiceText: You'd think I'm only working for Rhodes Island because I have nowhere better to be, right? Hardly. Put another way, I can't think of a better place to be than here. The pay's good, the medical treatment is cutting edge, and we've even got a cute little rabbit. How do you beat that?

char_017_huang_CN_004.voiceText: As one of Rhodes Island's core attackers, I have neither the firepower to blast open the battlefield with my Arts, nor the combat skills to take down a whole group of enemies by myself. But combine the two things I'm good at, and the effect is immediate. I suppose that's what a chemical reaction looks like.

char_017_huang_CN_005.voiceText: Amiya is one of the most talented warriors I've ever met. Her judgment is clear in any situation, and her Arts even terrify me when I see them. Doesn't it make you wonder how she got that kind of power at such a young age? Really. I wish she didn't.

char_017_huang_CN_006.voiceText: If you need my help, no need to be shy - just spit it out! Put your faith in me, and I put my faith in you. You command, I fight, simple as that! Right now, we're the best partners in Rhodes Island! Oh, but don't tell Amiya I said that just now.

char_017_huang_CN_007.voiceText: Before I even met you, many people told me about who you were before you lost your memories. Of course, it seems that you are no longer the same person they described, so should I treat you as two different people? The past you, and now, the current you. Haha!

char_017_huang_CN_008.voiceText: Dr. Kal'tsit said that one day, you will truly shoulder the responsibility that Rhodes Island has placed upon you. Dr. Kal'tsit saved my life, and I trusted her; She also told me to confirm what kind of person you are with my own eyes. I will, as long as Oripathy has not taken my life.

char_017_huang_CN_009.voiceText: Ah, Doctor, pass me the towel. Mhm, just finished today's training. I can't stay combat-ready if I don't get at least six hours of training in each day. All right, I've kept you waiting long enough. Where are we going this time? If that's the plan, I trust you'll cover the bill?

char_017_huang_CN_010.voiceText: Would I cause some misunderstanding if I carried the Doctor to the bedroom? Maybe I should just leave things as they are

char_017_huang_CN_011.voiceText: Rhodes Island Operator, Blaze, reporting in. Here, this is the authorization letter that Dr. Kal'tsit has already signed, so you can directly dispatch me. All righty, Doctor, let's show the other squads what we're capable of!

char_017_huang_CN_012.voiceText: I've seen many battles like this, but tougher times may be waiting for us ahead.

char_017_huang_CN_013.voiceText: Hah, don't you feel the air getting a bit hotter? No? Eh, gotta turn things up another notch then. And here I was trying to get you fired up

char_017_huang_CN_014.voiceText: Amiya, Dr. Kal'tsit, and now you as you currently are. The Operators of Rhodes Island have placed their trust in all of you, because you didn't give up on any of them. Fighting for the Infected is just, Doctor. Our fight is worth it.

char_017_huang_CN_017.voiceText: You gonna fight? Count me in!

char_017_huang_CN_018.voiceText: Uhh, the orders were uh, to get rid of all the enemies. See, I got this!

char_017_huang_CN_019.voiceText: As an assault operator, I have high standards, so you'd better keep up!

char_017_huang_CN_020.voiceText: It gets a little violent, but I like cutting steel and taking apart bunkers!

char_017_huang_CN_021.voiceText: It wasn't easy learning high-temperature gas dynamics!

char_017_huang_CN_022.voiceText: Let me show you what the other elite operators taught me about swinging a chainsaw!

char_017_huang_CN_024.voiceText: Do you hear the roar of this chainsaw?

char_017_huang_CN_025.voiceText: Don't worry if you see a little bit of fire somewhere, that's just a side effect!

char_017_huang_CN_026.voiceText: Surrender now if you don't want to get sawed in half!

char_017_huang_CN_027.voiceText: My blood's only going to make this place hotter!

char_017_huang_CN_028.voiceText: Fresh blood permeates my weapon, and spreads through the entire battlefield!

char_017_huang_CN_029.voiceText: No sacrifice is meaningless, and no victory comes without a cost.

char_017_huang_CN_030.voiceText: The rights of the Infected, will only be secured through the hands of the Infected.

char_017_huang_CN_031.voiceText: Let's work harder next time. We can always do better, right?

char_017_huang_CN_032.voiceText: Unfortunately, looks like luck wasn't on our side.

char_017_huang_CN_033.voiceText: Did Rhodes Island get any new facilities this time?

char_017_huang_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, when are we heading out on our mission?

char_367_swllow_CN_001.voiceText: That's fine. If I stick with you, I'll at least be able to escape that dusty cabin and catch some fresh air.

char_367_swllow_CN_002.voiceText: I don't shy away from sensitive topics regarding the Infected? That's correct, they're not like us, which should be obvious, but they're also like us in the sense that they have the right to seize hope. Therefore, there's no need for me to take extra care of them. That's equality, is it not?

char_367_swllow_CN_003.voiceText: Blaze is sometimes too reckless. I know she's strong, but What? You know how to deal with her? Tch Forget it, I'll ask Amiya how to handle her after we get back.

char_367_swllow_CN_004.voiceText: I'm just speaking objectively here, but if you don't want to be discriminated against, then you also shouldn't expect preferential treatment from others What, she went back to her room to cry? Look, I feel a little bad about it, but is someone like her really suited to be an Operator?

char_367_swllow_CN_005.voiceText: Rhodes Island is changing. Maybe you might not feel it, {@nickname}, since these changes are because of you, and not everyone is as disagreeable as I am. However, I do enjoy Rhodes Island's current direction.

char_367_swllow_CN_006.voiceText: I used to prefer choosing long-distance missions, as if trying to flee from Rhodes Island. Isn't that a bit ungrateful, considering Rhodes Island adopted me? As for right now? Haha, if there are still operators who like splattering blood everywhere, maybe I will apply to be sent somewhere else.

char_367_swllow_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, are you afraid? Of Catastrophes, Originite, Oripathy, and the Infected? Mm, even now, I'm still plagued by nightmares. But now, I have Amiya, as well as idiots like that Blaze. It seems that I'm not as afraid as I used to be.

char_367_swllow_CN_008.voiceText: Why are you called "Doctor?" No, I'm not trying to get you to remember anything, it's just that title makes me very wistful. Looking at all the Infected people around you makes me remember just a little bit of the past.

char_367_swllow_CN_009.voiceText: I've known this entire time. When my mother brought me to Rhodes Island, she had already gone crazy. I could not feel the pain of her turmoil, but I can relate with it, because I relied on that obsession to get me to where I am today. Only now, I've found a new direction... I want to find her, and I want to save her.

char_367_swllow_CN_010.voiceText: You shoulder the future of Rhodes Island, and those who hold up the bridge cannot be so lackadaisical.

char_367_swllow_CN_011.voiceText: So you're {@nickname}? Amiya told me about you. I'm GreyThroat; please don't disappoint me.

char_367_swllow_CN_012.voiceText: For efficiency's sake, speed up the playback. I can still see it clearly.

char_367_swllow_CN_013.voiceText: Even now, there are still a handful of Operators who I am on bad terms with. Hopefully my promotion will not be a cause of criticism?

char_367_swllow_CN_014.voiceText: Whether Infected or not, we all choose to step upon this land through our own free will, and so we must all work hard to survive, right?

char_367_swllow_CN_018.voiceText: Whether or not they'll listen to my orders is another matter.

char_367_swllow_CN_019.voiceText: A panoramic view of the battlefield.

char_367_swllow_CN_020.voiceText: I just have to rout them, right?

char_367_swllow_CN_026.voiceText: I see them. But they don't see me. Too bad.

char_367_swllow_CN_027.voiceText: The skills are enough to solve this situation.

char_367_swllow_CN_028.voiceText: Don't worry, there's nothing in their line of sight.

char_367_swllow_CN_029.voiceText: We won't see many victories like this, since our power is limited.

char_367_swllow_CN_030.voiceText: I have no talent to speak of, so as a crossbowman, I cannot allow an enemy to get within three meters of me.

char_367_swllow_CN_031.voiceText: The medics should stay behind to tend the wounded. I will chase after them, considering I'm used to working alone anyway.

char_367_swllow_CN_032.voiceText: Be aware of your surroundings; I'll ensure the safety of the retreat route.

char_367_swllow_CN_033.voiceText: Though I've been here for many years, I rarely go anywhere else

char_367_swllow_CN_036.voiceText: Aren't you afraid of upsetting the Operators who are Infected if you're always around me?

char_302_glaze_CN_001.voiceText: Any work to do today? If it's not urgent, just push everything back a bit.

char_302_glaze_CN_002.voiceText: I can detect nearby creatures with my Originium Arts, and this auxiliary device can further amplify the effect. Sounds great, huh? That's why the Garrison Team sent me to patrol the city, in case there were any students trying to skip school. They sure know how to put people to use.

char_302_glaze_CN_003.voiceText: Just to get this out of the way, this so-called secret of Laterano or whatever? I don't know a single thing about it. I just want to live a leisurely life. The less I know, the better off I'll be, wouldn't you agree?

char_302_glaze_CN_004.voiceText: Hmm? Isn't that person over there from the Notarial Hall? He wanted to make sure I'm "fulfilling my obligations?" Oh please, I pay my taxes on time every month. Anyway, whether or not that's true, give me a whisper if he's looking for me so I have time to go on a run.

char_302_glaze_CN_005.voiceText: I was bored earlier, so I headed down to the bridge to slack off Err, I meant, I wanted to take a look at the scenery, but everyone was looking at me like I was getting ready to off somebody. Hey, doesn't that mean people see me as a killer? Like I'd ever want a job like that, way too messy.

char_302_glaze_CN_006.voiceText: In the past, the top brass used to always harp on "protecting the glory of Laterano with your life," but I have no interest in that slogan, and I hate how static and immutable life was during that time. Working with you is way better, since you can give me something more practical.

char_302_glaze_CN_007.voiceText: My hair's a bit messy? Oh, seems like I forgot to tidied up after getting out of bed. After all, it's not like I have anything to do today What a pain in the butt. Anyway, come help me out, is my braid all crooked? It always feels a bit weird to me. You really should have a mirror in your office.

char_302_glaze_CN_008.voiceText: Hey, I have some cake for you. What do you usually do during break? You really should take a lap around the city and get some fresh air, don't you think? As for security, just grab an Operator that can go "pow pow" on any baddies near you, and you're set.

char_302_glaze_CN_009.voiceText: Wanna go watch a movie? Our work's just about done anyway. How about that romantic movie about the princess and the wanderer from afar? Wait, I need to hang up my do-not-disturb sign. Wouldn't want someone walking in.

char_302_glaze_CN_010.voiceText: Gotta take advantage of a time like this.

char_302_glaze_CN_011.voiceText: Ambriel, sniper, from Laterano... Introductions are a pain in the butt, so that's it. Here, I just opened this pack of chocolate. Break off a stick.

char_302_glaze_CN_012.voiceText: How long is this thing Is there no option to play all of these at once?

char_302_glaze_CN_013.voiceText: Thanks. Speaking of which, do these promotions come with a salary increase? There's something I've been looking at recently

char_302_glaze_CN_014.voiceText: Oh, thank you very much. I've been with Rhodes Island for quite some time now, right? Without realizing it, I've gotten a whole lot out of this, and made some good memories as well.

char_302_glaze_CN_017.voiceText: My teammates seem quite capable this time.

char_302_glaze_CN_018.voiceText: I'll say this up front. My tactics are a little unorthodox.

char_302_glaze_CN_020.voiceText: I hope we can wrap this mission up before dinner.

char_302_glaze_CN_022.voiceText: Let me finish this piece first.

char_302_glaze_CN_029.voiceText: As expected, Doctor, you're the only one who can consistently achieve results like this!

char_302_glaze_CN_030.voiceText: Not a single wasted shot - perfect.

char_302_glaze_CN_031.voiceText: Not the prettiest victory, but a win's a win, right?

char_302_glaze_CN_032.voiceText: The number of targets is still increasing, and they're about to launch an attack. Doctor, let's get out of here

char_302_glaze_CN_033.voiceText: Doctor, it's about time to replenish the cookies in the vending machine.

char_302_glaze_CN_036.voiceText: I heard that a new line of clothing just arrived in the Procurement Division? Hehe, Doctor, you simply must take me to see it.

char_2014_nian_CN_001.voiceText: Man, I'm so bored... Might just go shopping... You know what, yeah, we're doing it! Come on, put your shoes on. Yeah, we're both going out, that's why I said "we"!

char_2014_nian_CN_002.voiceText: That lame look of yours is grinding my gears... Here, have a toy to lighten up. You're busy with work? Who cares about some boring-ass work? Just one thing: don't lose sight of this little doll, or else it'll vanish in the blink of an eye.

char_2014_nian_CN_003.voiceText: Maaan, I'm so hungry... But as they say, gourmet food takes a gourmet cook to make. I've got a brother who's a great chef, and when our family all gets together, he can cook you something up in a jiffy if you just ask. Now that's what I call a good chef! Rhodes Island's food just tastes like crap compared to his.

char_2014_nian_CN_004.voiceText: Lungmen's a pretty chill place, but their cuisine? It's just got no kick to it! How can they eat that flavorless baby food? Listen up: spice is a way of life. Once you taste a little pleasant pain and feel that explosion of heat on your tongue, you'll realize just what you've been missing out on all this time.

char_2014_nian_CN_005.voiceText: My skills used to just be a regular part of my life, but as I'm easily influenced by my surroundings, I've wound up with a little penchant for getting into battles. I've grown used to the feeling of holding a weapon in my hand. Or rather, it just feels weird to NOT carry a weapon around. So it goes, I guess.

char_2014_nian_CN_006.voiceText: Rituals get passed down through generations not 'cause they have any inherent meaning, but because people find their own meaning in them. A performance has its rewards, and a wish has its fulfillment. And when one of my favorite stories is involved, you bet your ass I'm gonna participate.

char_2014_nian_CN_007.voiceText: People out of touch with reality will end up crushed beneath its cruel boot, sooner or later. You'd think that's common freakin' sense, but I've got several siblings who ignore reality for what it is. Their dull lives are only gonna get harder for 'em as time goes on.

char_2014_nian_CN_008.voiceText: Your dreams turn to a haze when you've lived as long as I have. But I've got better stuff to do than dream all day, and that's why l feel so alive. Sure, life is suffering, but seeing people carve something out for themselves is what I love. And as for you: think you got what it takes to be the anvil to my hammer?

char_2014_nian_CN_009.voiceText: Blacksmithing may just be a regular old occupation, but it was also always a part of early civilization. I'll keep metallurgy well and alive, even if everything else dies out. That's the future I chose for myself long ago. And you, you've made important choices before, haven'tcha? Don't ever go back on them. Stay true to your word, and everything will work out.

char_2014_nian_CN_010.voiceText: You're sleeping AGAIN? Wake up, sunshine! We're going shopping! C'mon, hurry up!

char_2014_nian_CN_011.voiceText: Anyone here? Heard from one of your guys that I can make a comfy living here! Something about free lodging and food, with plenty of free time left over... Hm? This area is for staff only? Don't be like that! You make it sound like I don't belong here!

char_2014_nian_CN_012.voiceText: Huh? What good do you think this stuff's gonna do me? Skills like these are only useful to people who value them.

char_2014_nian_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? That reminds me... I got something like that in the past once. Anyway, that's cool, I guess. You have my thanks!

char_2014_nian_CN_014.voiceText: People are like tools; you can classify 'em. And you, you're an interesting one... Or should I say "unusual"? I could forge you a good sword, but since you ain't gonna swing it, let alone fight in the first place, it'd just be a waste of metal.

char_2014_nian_CN_017.voiceText: Guess one thing's never gonna change with time: swords will inevitably clash between people.

char_2014_nian_CN_018.voiceText: Say what? Lead the team? Never led anyone before, but I guess I'll try.

char_2014_nian_CN_019.voiceText: A smith's gotta be ready to pay the debt owed by the weapons she forges.

char_2014_nian_CN_020.voiceText: My sword's gonna cleave your bodies and your values apart.

char_2014_nian_CN_021.voiceText: Well, well, you got orders for me?

char_2014_nian_CN_022.voiceText: A knife, a life; weapons are the basis for society.

char_2014_nian_CN_023.voiceText: "When 'tis a choice of life and death, why shouldst thou lay down thy arms?"

char_2014_nian_CN_024.voiceText: Let's just get this done with.

char_2014_nian_CN_025.voiceText: You dare strike my shield with your spear? That's gonna end with you in pieces!

char_2014_nian_CN_026.voiceText: My body burns at over 1,400 degrees!

char_2014_nian_CN_027.voiceText: "O virtuous King, who can lead our army if not you?"

char_2014_nian_CN_028.voiceText: Why do I gotta waste my precious time on the likes of you third-rate amateurs?

char_2014_nian_CN_029.voiceText: Niiice! I see some faint promise in you!

char_2014_nian_CN_030.voiceText: These small fry ain't even close to quelling my hunger.

char_2014_nian_CN_031.voiceText: Man, you sure messed up. What'd I tell you air bubbles weakening the iron?

char_2014_nian_CN_032.voiceText: We totally blew this one... If only these guys knew what I could do to them if I actually get serious.

char_2014_nian_CN_033.voiceText: Mind if I do some redecorating in here?

char_2014_nian_CN_036.voiceText: Hey, stand still! I'm trying to redecorate the place!

char_2014_nian_CN_042.voiceText: Yo, Doctor, you had lunch yet?

char_225_haak_CN_001.voiceText: Oh yeah, my dude, when you're callin' my name to get my attention, don't forget to stress the K at the end. Or else I might assume you're stammering or somethin'.

char_225_haak_CN_002.voiceText: Whoa, whoa, hold up! Is that vampire lady none other than "Mr. Blood"?! Man, we've still not settled that medical score we had a while back, and this is the perfect opportunity! I'll have to set up my experiment equipment later... Heheheheh!

char_225_haak_CN_003.voiceText: Lemme guess, Hung's still tellin' you to watch out around me, ain't he? Oh, just to "look after me," huh? Yeah, that sounds like him all right. But listen, my dude, I know your type. You're like me and just wanna do whatever you want, right? Then you can just ignore that guy and we can do whatever fun stuff we want instead.

char_225_haak_CN_004.voiceText: Yeah, I develop new drugs, do surgery, and nurture bacteria cultures, but those are all just fun hobbies to me. And don't call me a doctor, you got no reason to. I don't go 'round saving people's lives, y'know, I just "save" people by teaching them the value of their lives. All I can really do is prevent 'em from dying.

char_225_haak_CN_005.voiceText: The medical department guys are askin' for me? Tell 'em to stop. I don't dig those oh-so-professional physicians. They firmly believe that being a doctor's this noble job and are content with just saving lives... And everything comes crashing down when that faith of theirs is shattered. I've seen that happen time and time again. Honestly, it's kinda sad.

char_225_haak_CN_006.voiceText: Rhodes Island is pretty decent, or more accurately, it's just what I'd hoped. People are dyin' in the world right as we speak. There are doctors cooped up in labs, only workin' to cure diseases rather than prevent 'em. Hardly anyone gets it, but you people actually do. Keep up the good stuff!

char_225_haak_CN_007.voiceText: Me, a sociopath? You got it all wrong, my dude. Everyone's got their own hardships to deal with, and I know that. Nobody wants to suffer, but what's the point of medicine if the bastards causing suffering are still around? Is medicine gonna save those people who're being murdered? Doctors in suits are not the saviors that Terra needs, my dude.

char_225_haak_CN_008.voiceText: My pops was an amazing doctor, and he was all about saving people's lives. But his colleagues laughed at him, shunned him, and framed him for malpractice, and that's how he wound up racing down a nasty new path in life. But y'know, stuff like that ain't so unusual, really. I'll admit though, what happened to him really changed my own life.

char_225_haak_CN_009.voiceText: Have Waai Fu and Hung left? Really? Aight, I'm gonna hang out in your office for a while then. Y'know, if anyone can make the world a better place, it's gotta be people like them. You, meanwhile... Well, who knows, maybe you can be my right hand?

char_225_haak_CN_010.voiceText: What's up? Feelin' tired? Then how about testing this new compound I made? Free of charge, of course!

char_225_haak_CN_011.voiceText: So you're the Doctor, eh? Nice to meet'cha. My name's Aak. That's right, two A's with a K. Anyway, I'm here 'cause someone at the agency said Rhodes Island needed me. I'm just askin' to make sure here, but does the phrase "medical mishap" put you off?

char_225_haak_CN_012.voiceText: Huh... Does this mean I might get involved in combat scenarios like this? Surely not, right?

char_225_haak_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? That's almost too good to be true, man. Those agency guys really HAVE been exploiting me all along!

char_225_haak_CN_014.voiceText: Honestly, I dunno if I'm helpful or not. The way I see it, you've gotta be nice to be helpful, and I'm not blind to how people perceive me. But in any case, if you ever get sick, I've got you covered.

char_225_haak_CN_017.voiceText: We goin' on a mission? Let's do it.

char_225_haak_CN_018.voiceText: All right, team, gimme your thoughts on my new meds after this is done.

char_225_haak_CN_019.voiceText: Once I start an operation, there's no stoppin' it.

char_225_haak_CN_020.voiceText: Simmer down, guys. With me on your team, none of you's gonna die even if you want to.

char_225_haak_CN_021.voiceText: My treatment is not for the squeamish!

char_225_haak_CN_022.voiceText: The battlefield ain't for me, but I can't pass up on some fun treatment.

char_225_haak_CN_023.voiceText: Time for a clinical test of my new meds.

char_225_haak_CN_024.voiceText: You've gotta dose in moderation, 'else it's gonna hurt when you really need it.

char_225_haak_CN_025.voiceText: All lives are equal... With the exception of yours!

char_225_haak_CN_026.voiceText: Try my meds and you'll see how crazy they are.

char_225_haak_CN_027.voiceText: Looks like my meds have the ability to reform bad guys!

char_225_haak_CN_028.voiceText: Medicine is like Pandora's box: once you open it, there's no goin' back!

char_225_haak_CN_029.voiceText: I doubt I can make the world a better place on my own. But with your talent, we can at least stop it from gettin' any worse.

char_225_haak_CN_030.voiceText: Capturing our enemies and experimenting on 'em doesn't violate any ethics as long as nobody catches us doin' it. Relaaax.

char_225_haak_CN_031.voiceText: Aren't you a real humanitarian, just letting 'em get away like that?

char_225_haak_CN_032.voiceText: Don't worry, my dude. I can fix any injury as long as the patient's still breathing.

char_225_haak_CN_033.voiceText: Let's see here, which of these rooms is my new lab?

char_225_haak_CN_036.voiceText: Yo, my dude! Found any new experiment samples for me?

char_226_hmau_CN_001.voiceText: Hey, Doc. Have you eaten yet? You could have one of my cookies if you're hungry.

char_226_hmau_CN_002.voiceText: Doc, if Aak ever steps out of line, could you be lenient with him? He teases people a lot, but he's not a bad person. Also, if he ever gets under your skin, just tell me and I'll get him to tone it down.

char_226_hmau_CN_003.voiceText: Just call on me when you're hungry, Doc, and I'll make you a little something to eat. I may not be a chef, but Mr. Lee taught me how to cook a few recipes.

char_226_hmau_CN_004.voiceText: Say, Doc, do you give any lectures on machines here at Rhodes Island? I've got an interest in that stuff and was hoping I could learn something new.

char_226_hmau_CN_005.voiceText: Hahah, just between you and me, Doc, for the longest time I thought all detectives do the same stuff as Mr. Lee. You know, like investigating crime scenes, that sort of thing.

char_226_hmau_CN_006.voiceText: I'm sure you already know, but with the intellect and talent that Aak's got, he's destined for great things one day. But personally, all that matters to me is that he doesn't ever go back to his old way of doing things.

char_226_hmau_CN_007.voiceText: Me and Mr. Lee, well... How should I put it... I was a bit scared at first. He seemed like a guy who's got dark secrets, which had me on edge... But now after knowing him for so many years, I know that's definitely not the case.

char_226_hmau_CN_008.voiceText: If you need info on something or someone, just tell me and I'll ask Mr. Lee for you. Nothing in Lungmen happens without him knowing about it.

char_226_hmau_CN_009.voiceText: To be honest with you, I actually don't like getting into fights. I'd much rather we could all get along with each other. But I'm not a militant pacifist; there are things I'll fight to protect. Things like the agency, and now, Rhodes Island as well.

char_226_hmau_CN_010.voiceText: Do Phew, I just nearly woke the Doc up... Guess I'll take this opportunity to rest too.

char_226_hmau_CN_011.voiceText: You must be the doctor that Mr. Lee talked about. The name's Hung, it's a pleasure to meet you. My fields of expertise are security and repairing machinery. If you ever need a bodyguard for a public appearance, or if your TV or fridge break down, then be sure to give me a holler!

char_226_hmau_CN_012.voiceText: So this is what the elite of the elite are like... I've got to work just as hard.

char_226_hmau_CN_013.voiceText: Thanks, Doc! I'll be giving it 110% from here on out!

char_226_hmau_CN_014.voiceText: Doc, don't hesitate to give me all the work you need done. I'll admit I'm not an expert at many things, but I've got the build for physically intense tasks!

char_226_hmau_CN_019.voiceText: Stay close behind me so we don't get split up.

char_226_hmau_CN_020.voiceText: You can all rest easy, knowing I'm here!

char_226_hmau_CN_024.voiceText: I'm here to protect you all!

char_226_hmau_CN_025.voiceText: Don't think you're getting past us!

char_226_hmau_CN_026.voiceText: Is anyone in need of healing?

char_226_hmau_CN_027.voiceText: You're not hurting anyone on my watch!

char_226_hmau_CN_029.voiceText: *pant*... *pant*... Sorry, Doc, but could you give me a minute? My body's shaking.

char_226_hmau_CN_030.voiceText: You just stay here and rest, Doc. I'll clean up the battlefield.

char_226_hmau_CN_031.voiceText: Stay beside me, Doc. There are still enemies around.

char_226_hmau_CN_032.voiceText: Hurry, Doc, climb onto my back! I'm getting you out of here!

char_226_hmau_CN_034.voiceText: Are there any broken machines in here?

char_383_snsant_CN_001.voiceText: D-Doctor! Excuse me, but could you please move a little? You're stepping on a coin

char_383_snsant_CN_002.voiceText: My dream is to be praised sincerely by the entire world Ah, um, maybe just Lungmen Well, maybe I should start with Rhodes Island, or, um, just you! Yes, that is my dream for the time being

char_383_snsant_CN_003.voiceText: Ugh, I forgot to turn off the light when I left the office yesterday Hm? Rhodes Island has a power generation facility so there's no need to pay for electricity? Really? Does that I mean I get to eat dinner in the future?

char_383_snsant_CN_004.voiceText: This is the Originium ammunition that Jessica ordered Eh? D-Doctor! Isn't this dollar amount wrong? Or is this the currency of some small remote country? It's not? It's LMD? I, I, I, I, I see Don't worry, I was just a l-l-l-little s-surprised.

char_383_snsant_CN_005.voiceText: Oripathy Hm, even though it's a bit beyond my field of study, it does seem to be worth looking into But if I add another research project, I'll go from two meals a day to two days a meal Ugh

char_383_snsant_CN_006.voiceText: Frugality is a type of virtue, but for me, it's closer to a habit D-despite that, if you or my friends were in need, I'd gladly help out! I'm serious!

char_383_snsant_CN_007.voiceText: You'd like to take a look at my clawhook? That's maybe fine but whatever you do, don't push this button. And watch your thumb when you're holding the grip W-wait, you're not winding the rope correctly, and Ack! Sorry, don't mind me, you can keep looking at it...

char_383_snsant_CN_008.voiceText: After I become a great, world-famous scientist with lots of money, I swear I'll have three meals a day and dessert too, just like Jessica And then, with the money I'm not able to spend, I'd put it back into making Lungmen a better place. Um if a day like that ever comes.

char_383_snsant_CN_009.voiceText: Money is very important. Before I returned to Lungmen, I refused a large retention fee from the research institute, so my self-funded research project went under But it's more important to be home. I can always save up more money, and now I won't go dizzy from looking at all those large numbers!

char_383_snsant_CN_010.voiceText: Did you fall asleep? Just let me handle the rest, though I am a bit hungry.

char_383_snsant_CN_011.voiceText: Oww my head! Sorry Oh, y-you're the Doctor? It's a pleasure to meet you. My name is Snowsant. Sorry, I shouldn't be walking with my head down

char_383_snsant_CN_012.voiceText: Woah This isn't something you can learn with more effort

char_383_snsant_CN_013.voiceText: Ehh? A p-promotion? I feel a bit more pressure, but I'll be okay. This is the proof that I'm one step farther than when I first came.

char_383_snsant_CN_014.voiceText: "Heaven rewards the hard-working." Wouldn't you agree, Doctor?

char_383_snsant_CN_017.voiceText: It'll be all right, as long as I work just as hard as I did during training

char_383_snsant_CN_018.voiceText: You want m-me to be the squad leader? I really don't know anything about battle though

char_383_snsant_CN_019.voiceText: Clawhook inspection complete! Take a deep breath... I can do this!

char_383_snsant_CN_024.voiceText: This is my first time being so close to a battlefield

char_383_snsant_CN_026.voiceText: Stop moving around, it'll be easier this way!

char_383_snsant_CN_029.voiceText: As long as we work together, there's no obstacle we can't overcome!

char_383_snsant_CN_030.voiceText: What a flawless victory - not a bit of waste!

char_383_snsant_CN_031.voiceText: Some enemies got away, sh-should we chase after them?

char_383_snsant_CN_032.voiceText: I, I'll go salvage some damage parts, to at least reduce our losses

char_383_snsant_CN_033.voiceText: Woah, so this is what it's like inside Rhodes Island I'm so envious

char_2013_cerber_CN_001.voiceText: Hm? What should I do? Just put this stack of papers on this box?

char_2013_cerber_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor, are you working? Can I watch? Great! Sofa, here I come~

char_2013_cerber_CN_003.voiceText: I'm super strong. Forget one bad guy, I can take on a hundred at once. Uhh, maybe a hundred is a bit much... But ninety-nine is no problem! Mhm!

char_2013_cerber_CN_004.voiceText: I found a bunch of these little bottle things in some room, and the sauce inside tasted pretty good. Is it spicy? Yeah, seems to be a little hot, but it's also really tasty. Want some, Doctor?

char_2013_cerber_CN_005.voiceText: My den is right here. Doctor's den is above my head, and Vulcan's is to my left... Okay, got it! Repeat it? Mm, sure. My den is above my head, Doctor's is to my left, and Vulcan's is right here...

char_2013_cerber_CN_006.voiceText: So this is where I started from? Oh, oh, then where did I go before this? And where did you catch me? Can you find it all on this map?!

char_2013_cerber_CN_007.voiceText: So hungry... My tummy's been grumbling for so long. Can we head to the cafeteria?

char_2013_cerber_CN_008.voiceText: I don't know much about these Arts, but when other people try to use my weapons, they can't make all those cool sparkly things happen. But don't worry, as long as I'm here, the bad guys won't be able to hurt you. I know who the bad guys are.

char_2013_cerber_CN_009.voiceText: There's a whole bunch of bad guys out there, and my friends won't always be around. That's why the more weapons I have, the more power I have. Isn't that right? Hey, can you stuff another hammer back there? And a javelin too, those are super useful! Hm? No means no!

char_2013_cerber_CN_011.voiceText: You seem like you're a pretty nice person. "Doctor," was it? My name is Ceobe, but if that's too hard to say, you can just call me Kay! I'll be in your care!

char_2013_cerber_CN_013.voiceText: This little button is for me? Do I look good wearing it?

char_2013_cerber_CN_014.voiceText: One's not enough, two gets the job done, and three is for safety. As long as I bring the right weapons for the job, I'll take out the bad guys as they come.

char_2013_cerber_CN_019.voiceText: I wonder if there's gonna be anything tasty when I get back~

char_2013_cerber_CN_029.voiceText: With your brains, my job is super easy! You're the best, Doctor!

char_2013_cerber_CN_030.voiceText: All that's needed is a bang, bang! And that takes care of them!

char_2013_cerber_CN_031.voiceText: Are you hurt? Do you need help?

char_2013_cerber_CN_032.voiceText: Hurry, run! We won't be able to get away if we don't hurry up!

char_2013_cerber_CN_033.voiceText: This fluffy thing is gonna feel absolutely amazing~

char_2013_cerber_CN_036.voiceText: Hey, can you take me with you?

char_2013_cerber_CN_042.voiceText: Good morning, Doctor! Mhm, that's a proper greeting, right?

char_306_leizi_CN_001.voiceText: Look carefully. The files are sorted by type, then time limit prioritization, then finally, by distance from nearest to farthest. This is the most efficient organization method! ...Wait, I seem to have done all the paperwork on accident. This... is supposed to be your job, right?

char_306_leizi_CN_002.voiceText: I've checked all files related to the elite Operator, Blaze, and there are no records of her real name, or place and date of birth. Don't tell me you don't know; aren't you supposed to be one of the leaders here? You really don't know? Then... nevermind. Sorry, I shouldn't have accused you.

char_306_leizi_CN_003.voiceText: You don't need to be so cautious around me. Other than the case at hand, I'll treat everything else on the ship as if it never happened. But if there's another explosion in the hallway outside my room, I'll make the perpetrator's hair stand on end for two weeks!

char_306_leizi_CN_004.voiceText: "Assume the responsibilities for the post to which you are assigned." As one of the leaders of Rhodes Island, is it not your duty to... Huh? My hair's standing up again? Hold on! G-give me a moment to fix my look first! Weird, I thought I had discharged all the static electricity this morning...

char_306_leizi_CN_005.voiceText: Even today, I can vaguely recall the first time I saw you in Lungmen. You, Blaze, and Ch'en... are all holding onto countless secrets... and I will uncover them one by one. You're willing to exchange secrets? Wait, y-you... it's t-too early for that...!

char_306_leizi_CN_006.voiceText: Ask me anything. Only when you speak up can I decide what is just and unjust, and whether I wish to take action. I need to take my identity into consideration? This has nothing to do with that! The Censorate, Central Judicial Office, and the Anti-Corruption Bureau... are only institutions. Laws can only be proven just when enforced by someone.

char_306_leizi_CN_007.voiceText: Rhodes Island's ideals conflict with my beliefs. However, I do recognize the necessity of seeking common ground while understanding our differences... The same is true when providing assistance in exchange for information.

char_306_leizi_CN_008.voiceText: No matter where I am, the electricity flowing through my body never ceases. The thunderbolt is the symbol of justice; it drives me forward and sometimes even wakes me up at night... Someone is complaining that I broke the AC unit? ...How rude! How is that possible?! I don't even need to use a remote for the AC, let alone touch it!

char_306_leizi_CN_009.voiceText: Blaze was implicated in a major incident. All the clues have purposely been eliminated, but I have my doubts about the way the facts of the case are connected based upon a few coincidences between certain persons and times. This has nothing to do with you, but you should take adequate precautions. All I can do is offer you a fair warning.

char_306_leizi_CN_010.voiceText: You can't even properly manage your physical condition... how slovenly! Look at you sprawled out like this... Were you waiting for me to put a blanket over you or something? ...There won't be a next time.

char_306_leizi_CN_011.voiceText: I've signed obtained an investigation authorization with your company. Don't worry about it, this is purely over personal matters. If you so wish, you may call me Leizi. Who am I? Have we met before? Are you serious?!

char_306_leizi_CN_012.voiceText: I see, this is a completely different principle from military training.

char_306_leizi_CN_013.voiceText: Elite status? Is this... a promotion? The promotion process at Rhodes Island seems to differ from that of ordinary private companies...

char_306_leizi_CN_014.voiceText: I, Leizi, am the bearer of the thunder and the law, the vision and reach of Great Yan. My philosophy does not align with that of Rhodes Island, and I have no intention on bridging the gap between the Infected and non-Infected. However, we can now fight side by side against our enemies!

char_306_leizi_CN_017.voiceText: With my own eyes, I shall judge what power Rhodes Island possesses.

char_306_leizi_CN_018.voiceText: I can do that, yes, albeit at a price.

char_306_leizi_CN_020.voiceText: I have no interest in the identity of my enemies.

char_306_leizi_CN_025.voiceText: Rise, thunder of the five elements!

char_306_leizi_CN_026.voiceText: No forgiveness unto sinners! Retribution of thunder!

char_306_leizi_CN_027.voiceText: Through the three thunders is justice governed!

char_306_leizi_CN_028.voiceText: The essence of Lei Fa... is my will becoming one with Terra.

char_306_leizi_CN_029.voiceText: Well done. As my standards are quite high, you should be proud of yourself.

char_306_leizi_CN_030.voiceText: Unacceptable. You can do even better! Do not rest upon your laurels - you have the ability to strive for greater heights!

char_306_leizi_CN_031.voiceText: Impossible, what happened? How can this be?

char_306_leizi_CN_032.voiceText: Shameful...! Begone, you! Go back and reflect! I will hold back the enemies, so just go!

char_306_leizi_CN_036.voiceText: Oh... did that hurt? Please be careful of the static electricity around me.

char_385_finlpp_CN_001.voiceText: Smiling can help you feel revitalized. Why don't you try smiling, Doctor~

char_385_finlpp_CN_002.voiceText: Rhodes Island shouldn't be like those black-hearted corporations, right? Lungmen Industrial Waste Disposal License, Lungmen City Sewage Permit... Well, it seems like there are no problems with your certification, and the sewage treatment seems good enough... It's good that you're a law-abiding organization!

char_385_finlpp_CN_003.voiceText: Woah, this water tastes amazing~! It's cool and sweet, just like the springs back in my hometown... Where's the water source? How is it filtered? What are you using to filter it? Please tell me quickly, Doctor!

char_385_finlpp_CN_004.voiceText: There are signs of excessive wastewater discharge this mon-- Huh? Did I take too many baths again? ...Oh no, I must reflect upon my behavior!

char_385_finlpp_CN_005.voiceText: I love my hometown! Although it's not as lively in the country as it is in the city, and daily life isn't as comfortable, the water there is cool and delicious, and the air is always fresh. Hehe, these are sometimes hard to come by in the city!

char_385_finlpp_CN_006.voiceText: The pollution near the city is getting worse and worse. Earlier, we even had problems with the water supply in my hometown, and resolving that situation required a lot of effort. While Catastrophes pose a very clear threat to us, pollution will also erode away at our habitable spaces! Therefore, protecting our environment is also of great importance!

char_385_finlpp_CN_007.voiceText: Heave, ho! That should be the last shoe... Got it! Phew, now, this waterway will be much cleaner, and my daily efforts here won't go to waste! Thank you for accompanying me, Doctor!

char_385_finlpp_CN_008.voiceText: There is a legend among my people that we came from a place far, far away. Now that there are fewer and fewer of us, nobody seems to know where we came from, or where we are going...

char_385_finlpp_CN_009.voiceText: Back in my hometown during harvest season, each family will make lots and lots of delicious food! Braised, sweet and sour, steamed, fried, marinated, anything you can imagine! Doctor, why don't we go visit together? The people there are very hospitable~

char_385_finlpp_CN_010.voiceText: Ugh... So dry... I want to soak in a bath...

char_385_finlpp_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, I am the municipal waterway cleaner, codename Purestream! From now on, I will handle the water treatment and sanitation of this ship, so please rest assured! Oh, these are pickled vegetables from my hometown. Everyone is welcome to try some - I assure you, it's delicious!

char_385_finlpp_CN_012.voiceText: If the purpose is to gain experience, wouldn't it be faster to do it directly?

char_385_finlpp_CN_013.voiceText: Am I getting a raise? With this promotion and salary increase, I'm well on my way to the top! Hehe, I'll have to tell everyone back home the good news~

char_385_finlpp_CN_014.voiceText: While there is a difference in urgency between visible threats and less evident threats, they are both dangerous to us! I'm glad you understand, Doctor.

char_385_finlpp_CN_017.voiceText: No problem, just leave it to me!

char_385_finlpp_CN_018.voiceText: Such an important task... I'll do my best!

char_385_finlpp_CN_019.voiceText: Rhodes Island Water Treatment Team, heading out!

char_385_finlpp_CN_020.voiceText: Surprise inspection! Seize that scoundrel who just poured paint down the sink!

char_385_finlpp_CN_021.voiceText: Roll up my sleeves and fight? ...Um, my outfit doesn't have any sleeves though.

char_385_finlpp_CN_024.voiceText: I bring the gift of water~

char_385_finlpp_CN_027.voiceText: Water works to the benefit of all.

char_385_finlpp_CN_028.voiceText: How's that? Feeling a bit more awake after being splashed with cold water?

char_385_finlpp_CN_029.voiceText: No more contaminants! Very good, this mission was a great success~

char_385_finlpp_CN_030.voiceText: Operation complete! I'll handle the post-battle clean-up.

char_385_finlpp_CN_031.voiceText: Hey, where'd the enemy run off to? I-I can't find them!

char_385_finlpp_CN_032.voiceText: The situation is looking bad, but we have nothing to fear as long as we stay strong! Let's fall back for now?

char_385_finlpp_CN_033.voiceText: I hope I can get a nice, big bathtub~

char_385_finlpp_CN_036.voiceText: Let me tell you a secret - I can swim while standing up~

char_385_finlpp_CN_042.voiceText: Good morning, Doctor! Would you like a cup of cool, refreshing spring water?

char_222_bpipe_CN_001.voiceText: Assistant? You mean that job where I just stand next to people? I've seen that in the army as well. Wait, I also have to do paperwork? And assess combat data? And compile a report?! Th-that sounds hectic!

char_222_bpipe_CN_002.voiceText: Back in school, Chenchen always had a pissed off look on her face. But that's just the kind of girl she is. She made a lot of enemies at first, but later on, there wasn't a single person who could take their eyes off her! But y'know, bandagin' her wounds, cookin' for her, teamin' up with her squad and whatnot... I had to look after her quite a lot, and that was no easy feat...

char_222_bpipe_CN_003.voiceText: I'm real good at operatin' all sorts of equipment! Wheat threshers, tractors, tillers, I'm good with all that stuff. Hm? PDAs, LED screens, and wireless systems? I'm not too good with that stuff... Woah, I barely just touched it... Why's it goin' up in smoke?!

char_222_bpipe_CN_004.voiceText: Did you not get a good supper in yesterday? I don't wanna hear your old "work, work, work" routine! If your body gives out on you, you won't be able to get a thing done. Tell me what you'd like, and I'll make it for you! Ah, I won't be able to make anything too complicated though.

char_222_bpipe_CN_005.voiceText: The Rhodes Island ship is just... so much better than Victoria's warships by I don't know how many times. There's even sunlight, wheat fields, and packs of beasts... Doctor, why don't we try growin' something, like potatoes? I know all about growin' potatoes!

char_222_bpipe_CN_006.voiceText: Where do you think someone's hometown ends? Is it the house farthest away from the tractors, or where the land meets the sky? Or is it the red and blue bars that are constantly being redrawn on the map? After so many battles... I sometimes suddenly forget what my hometown looks like.

char_222_bpipe_CN_007.voiceText: I know I've seen her before, that girl called Reed. But she looks so lonely and pitiful now... Is she really the same terrifyin' person I once knew? How strange. I should go ask her... I can't talk to her? Huh? Why not?!

char_222_bpipe_CN_008.voiceText: My mum is part of the reason I ended up goin' to military school in the first place. I blame her for sayin' stuff like "Vouivre women must keep gettin' stronger." ...Sounds like I was just bein' stubborn, right? Lookin' back, there's no need to try to be as strong as my mum. Hey, wouldn't you say I'm cuter this way?

char_222_bpipe_CN_009.voiceText: When I was still in the army, I once came across a ghost-like squadron. They haunted the darkness of Victoria, and most of the people who witnessed 'em went missin'. I have a duty to expose 'em, and that's why I've been runnin' all over the world. Oh, you don't need to step in. Don't you have your own stuff to worry about?

char_222_bpipe_CN_010.voiceText: Ah! You're slackin' off again! How nice, but if you're gonna nap, wouldn't it be better to throw yourself atop a pile of hay? Mm, just thinkin' about it is makin' me sleepy too... It should be fine if I go rest for a while, right?

char_222_bpipe_CN_011.voiceText: Hey there! You're the Doctor, right? Superintendent Ch'en from Lungmen said I'd be able to find some helpers here! I need to sign my name here first? Um... Baaag... pipe. All right! Huh? I need to "become an Operator" first? "Full-time room and board?" The heck is that?!

char_222_bpipe_CN_012.voiceText: Woah, you folks here at Rhodes Island sure can fight!

char_222_bpipe_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? Hm... can't tell you if I like it or not. For soldiers, more responsibilities means more battles, and a greater risk of mistakes.

char_222_bpipe_CN_014.voiceText: Joining Rhodes Island has been a good thing for me. Oripathy and the Infected may seem scary at first, but runnin' away from these problems won't solve anything, right? Thank you, I've also understood what I need to do.

char_222_bpipe_CN_018.voiceText: I'll lead the team and execute the operation plan right away!

char_222_bpipe_CN_019.voiceText: Follow the orders, and move out immediately!

char_222_bpipe_CN_024.voiceText: My spear and I hail from Victoria!

char_222_bpipe_CN_029.voiceText: I've seen more serious matters, both in school and in the military.

char_222_bpipe_CN_030.voiceText: Phew... I've managed to live up to the reputation of this uniform once more.

char_222_bpipe_CN_031.voiceText: The enemy is getting away! Everyone, please be careful when givin' chase!

char_222_bpipe_CN_033.voiceText: How do I get to the greenhouse?

char_222_bpipe_CN_036.voiceText: Wanna go on a picnic? Just the two of us!

char_379_sesa_CN_001.voiceText: Hmm, is this the Doctor's room? How boring. It looks just like those never-changing hills of Sargon. At least get a game console, will you?

char_379_sesa_CN_002.voiceText: {@nickname}, I feel something resonating from within you. How strange. Is this because we still have so much untapped potential? But alas, you've forgotten your past. Does it feel like a burden's been lifted off of you, or does it make things more painful?

char_379_sesa_CN_003.voiceText: {@nickname}, I take greater pride in natural wisdom than the knowledge that is deliberately taught! With Rhodes Island at my side, we will get ever-closer to the Great Truth. Hey, don't avert your gaze. There's nothing to be ashamed of, is there?

char_379_sesa_CN_004.voiceText: "I wish to cross over to the distant shores." That used to be the secret phrase people used to communicate with me. That bridge is the link between two worlds, transferring wisdom and imbuing power... Hey, let me finish. It's rude to just turn around and walk off like that!

char_379_sesa_CN_005.voiceText: Rhodes Island has some pretty tasteless folks, acting like their outer appearance is just some decoration, like a skin to be taken off! You'll come off as slovenly to people if you don't carefully coordinate your look, right? What, my clothes are tattered? You simply don't understand the boldness of this fashion statement...

char_379_sesa_CN_006.voiceText: Do you believe that weapons have souls? The things they've experienced, the hands they've been passed through, and the reason they've been swung... No! These have nothing to do with the soul. For a weapon, any belief or meaning has been superimposed upon it. Tell me, are we weapons, or are we people with souls imposed upon us?

char_379_sesa_CN_007.voiceText: A genius? Do people like that really exist...? Most craftspeople in Sargon are just ordinary apprentices who are still learning to walk, tinkering with metals. But as long as they continue down the path, even they can reach the road's destination.

char_379_sesa_CN_008.voiceText: Need my help making some adjustments? My skills aren't something that can ever see the light of day. "Allowing everyone to just pick up a weapon is the way to creating wars." I must wear these shackles to restrict myself. Or, do you wish to unchain me and unleash havoc upon this world?

char_379_sesa_CN_009.voiceText: Do you know about who I am? And about my past? No, you don't know, nor should you know. My incognito exists to bury the past behind me. Forget about it, and let these things sink into the depths of the deserts.

char_379_sesa_CN_010.voiceText: I don't mind this kind of peace and quiet.

char_379_sesa_CN_011.voiceText: I know exactly what you're searching for, Doctor of Rhodes Island! You long for truth and power! And I, Sesa, am willing to grant you these things... Woah, wait, wait up! Don't push my out the door! I'm serious about my job application!

char_379_sesa_CN_013.voiceText: ...You wish for greater power? Don't draw any unnecessary attention before the time is right. Otherwise, it'll be veeery dangerous.

char_379_sesa_CN_014.voiceText: "The bridge is the connection, the ammunition is wisdom, the weapon is the will, and harmony is equality." Shall we tear asunder the veil that obfuscates the Truth? Perhaps I can lend you a bit more power... Just a bit more.

char_379_sesa_CN_017.voiceText: The "bridge" seeks completion... Those weapons in your hands... May I take a closer look?

char_379_sesa_CN_018.voiceText: Let me guide you... Just rub this oil into the bolt slot of your crossbow. Remember to apply it uniformly.

char_379_sesa_CN_019.voiceText: It's time for our efforts to bear fruit! Just remember, these weapons must be handled delicately.

char_379_sesa_CN_020.voiceText: The battlefield destroys both weapons and their hosts.

char_379_sesa_CN_022.voiceText: Set me free! This is what I should yell, right?

char_379_sesa_CN_025.voiceText: Free the weapon from the flesh...

char_379_sesa_CN_027.voiceText: I shall be your end! It's fine for me to say stuff like that, right?

char_379_sesa_CN_028.voiceText: How can you ever understand the suffering of the victims?

char_379_sesa_CN_029.voiceText: Such a fierce battle is inevitably accompanied by great pain, but the weapon in your hands will never lie. It roars triumphantly!

char_379_sesa_CN_030.voiceText: You are a bit too dependent upon my powers. Speak no more of it. You know the old agreement, a cup of black tea with two cubes of sugar.

char_379_sesa_CN_031.voiceText: Being able to escape the weapons' bloodbath is perhaps a good thing.

char_379_sesa_CN_032.voiceText: No matter how much you run, the weapons will always be waiting. For the day you and I are wiped out.

char_379_sesa_CN_033.voiceText: The Great Truth needs an equally great space to house it! Wait, no, I don't need a room this big...

char_379_sesa_CN_034.voiceText: Watch out! I... I'm still not able to fully control my powers!

char_379_sesa_CN_036.voiceText: Do you want to hear a story? I know many old stories.

char_337_utage_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, ready to get to work? I won't take no for an answer! C'mon! 3, 2, 1, start!

char_337_utage_CN_002.voiceText: Nails are part of a girl's appeal. Gotta take care of them properly.

char_337_utage_CN_003.voiceText: Why do I call myself Utage? Well, it's not that complicated. I just want to be happy as if we were throwing a party every night. As long as I'm in a good mood, everything else is gonna be okay.

char_337_utage_CN_004.voiceText: You already saw it, Doctor? Well, that's too bad... C'mon, let's use up this two-person discount coupon.

char_337_utage_CN_005.voiceText: When I contracted Oripathy and was to be sent here, my mother was afraid I'd be bullied, and gave me the family heirloom, Shishiou, to defend myself with. Didn't find any bullies, but I did manage to cut some pretty nasty folks. Doctor, you really know how to appeal to people.

char_337_utage_CN_006.voiceText: Everyone here gets pretty scary when they get serious. I'm as scary as six people combined? Am I really that terrifying...?

char_337_utage_CN_007.voiceText: Help me pick up ten boxes of limited-edition cookie sticks tomorrow? Just take the money out of my account. Huh? Preorders are already sold out? Then... c'mon, you've gotta think of a way, Doctor! Please!

char_337_utage_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, you're razor-sharp some of the time and dull as a piece of wood at others. I don't get why. Oh, I see, right out of "Flirting Guidebook," huh? I'd expect nothing less from you, Doctor.

char_337_utage_CN_009.voiceText: It's not good to rely too much on any single person, but I'll make an exception for... Eek, Doctor! Oh it's nothing, I was just rambling to myself! D-d-did you need anything from me?

char_337_utage_CN_010.voiceText: If you're tired, just go to bed. Not that complicated.

char_337_utage_CN_011.voiceText: Hey, Doctor. I'm the Operator who just joined recently, Utage. My interests are... Oh, I don't need to go into the details? In that case, I look forward to working with you.

char_337_utage_CN_013.voiceText: Do I get to do less work if I get promoted? No dice? Oh well...

char_337_utage_CN_014.voiceText: It's time to move out. Let's crush those nasty folks~

char_337_utage_CN_017.voiceText: All right everyone, I'll be counting on your orders!

char_337_utage_CN_018.voiceText: I'm the team leader? ...Eh? Me? Team leader?

char_337_utage_CN_020.voiceText: C'mon, c'mon! I can't wait any longer.

char_337_utage_CN_026.voiceText: It won't hurt if I don't miss.

char_337_utage_CN_027.voiceText: Just send me the leftover parts.

char_337_utage_CN_028.voiceText: You look rather cute when you're crying.

char_337_utage_CN_029.voiceText: Ahh, I'm finally done blowing off steam, how exciting. Doctor, let's get some crepes.

char_337_utage_CN_030.voiceText: How exciting. Thanks for all the support~

char_337_utage_CN_031.voiceText: You're saving the stragglers for me? Well, I'll dig right in.

char_337_utage_CN_032.voiceText: Doctor, stop spacing out and start running.

char_337_utage_CN_033.voiceText: As long as I can buy the new magazines, it doesn't really matter where I'm staying.

char_252_bibeak_CN_001.voiceText: I don't need to go outside today? Th-thank goodness... Infected people like me have no right to wear these clothes. How strange it is that I cannot wear the clothes I make with my own hands... Eh? Rhodes Island doesn't care about stuff like that? Really?

char_252_bibeak_CN_002.voiceText: Oh, my outfit? Um, I designed this one myself. The skirt incorporates some traditional motifs, though it can't compete with my dad's work... But this is my attempt at emulating an old-fashioned style.

char_252_bibeak_CN_003.voiceText: Good afternoon, Doctor. I'm trying to clean up my room... Sorry, my room often ends up being a mess... I used to never have to organize my room, and now that I'm starting to learn, it's actually rather fun... although I often break things in the process...

char_252_bibeak_CN_004.voiceText: I've always had trouble adjusting after being pulled away from my old life. In the very beginning, I felt like I couldn't continue living after becoming an Infected, and I was just so scared... But I'm not like that anymore. There's so much I want to learn, and I want to do more for those just like me here at Rhodes Island.

char_252_bibeak_CN_005.voiceText: Since I was young, my father required me to study swordsmanship. I didn't like it back then, but... after that incident, sometimes holding the sword has been more reassuring than holding the spinning thread.

char_252_bibeak_CN_006.voiceText: I used to be afraid to go outside. As an Infected, I felt like everything was scorning me... But now I understand that one's self-esteem has nothing to do with whether or not she is Infected or not. After all, that is the most beautiful decoration.

char_252_bibeak_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, um... If, if it's possible, can I make some clothes for you...? I think you'd be just right for bringing out some of my ideas. Um, I sometimes ask the other Operators in the same way...

char_252_bibeak_CN_008.voiceText: The people who stoned me with Originium... Of course I hated them, but now... If I continued to harbor that contempt and despair, it would have driven me to do terrible things. I have no regrets about running away from home, even if it holds many warm memories of my past.

char_252_bibeak_CN_009.voiceText: I want to incorporate the many things I've learned from everyone into something we can all wear...Hehe, even with that in mind, the elements are a bit complicated. But this reflects my emotions, whether I'm brandishing my sword or flourishing my needle.

char_252_bibeak_CN_010.voiceText: Let's use this time to craft something small.

char_252_bibeak_CN_011.voiceText: H-hello, Doctor... My codename is Bibeak... Excuse me, but is there a facility with a loom and a knitting machine here?

char_252_bibeak_CN_012.voiceText: The way they fight... I've never even thought about that before...

char_252_bibeak_CN_013.voiceText: A p-promotion? Are you sure? I'm actually not very good at fighting... Thank you.

char_252_bibeak_CN_014.voiceText: By my side... are all the Operators of Rhodes Island, and you, Doctor. Even with my limited life, I'm still able to live normally like a normal person... No, a life they never would be able to dream is possible.

char_252_bibeak_CN_019.voiceText: Just like a textile, there is only one way to weave.

char_252_bibeak_CN_023.voiceText: Is wielding the sword the same as wielding the needle?

char_252_bibeak_CN_024.voiceText: I... can also fight! Believe in me!

char_252_bibeak_CN_026.voiceText: If you have anything to say, save it for after the battle! There are people I must protect!

char_252_bibeak_CN_028.voiceText: Can the strings of life also be cut?

char_252_bibeak_CN_029.voiceText: Great work, Doctor! Um, what did you think about my performance?

char_252_bibeak_CN_030.voiceText: It, it's finally over! If your uniform is damaged, I can help repair it...

char_252_bibeak_CN_031.voiceText: Oh, someone got away... But, that's a better outcome... than the cruelty of death.

char_252_bibeak_CN_033.voiceText: Hmm... Where is the textiles room?

char_252_bibeak_CN_036.voiceText: Oh, Doctor, can you help grab those textiles for me?

char_159_peacok_CN_001.voiceText: Since you summoned me, you must be eager to feast your eyes upon my elegant dancing form, right? ...Uh, help move the luggage? I didn't come here to do manual labor!

char_159_peacok_CN_002.voiceText: You're such a weak and ineffectual leader! What's up with that? I'd convict you if not for the sorrowful tears Amiya would then shed.

char_159_peacok_CN_003.voiceText: You don't even know how to convict a criminal? Listen up, the art of conviction is an assassination technique created by the first Conviction through combining traditional dance moves with ancient fighting techniques! I am his third-generation successor!

char_159_peacok_CN_004.voiceText: Conviction is not some barbaric fighting technique. It is an artform through which beauty and ideals are poured through the fist and delivered straight into the heart! Now you know!

char_159_peacok_CN_005.voiceText: This art is the crystallization of hard work and great insight. When people ignore the true value of art and use this sacred product as some sort of game, Conviction will descend to right all wrongs.

char_159_peacok_CN_006.voiceText: If you don't even feel the overwhelming pressure radiating from my perfect, classic artwork-like image, then you do not deserve to be on the same team as your savior! Ughhh! Con! Viction!

char_159_peacok_CN_007.voiceText: I'm actually someone infected with Oripathy, an incurable disease?! Curses... is this my destiny? Is this the fate of all who wield the Conviction Punch? Hey, why are you all looking away! I'm clearly telling you a sad story!

char_159_peacok_CN_008.voiceText: You also wish to become Conviction? In that case, chew upon this question!
