"You're standing at a junction in a railroad, with a train full of Durin people approaching. The junction splits off into two tracks, one upon which several artists with meager artistic achievements are..."

char_159_peacok_CN_009.voiceText: You don't even have the gumption to answer the easiest of Conviction's dilemmas! You have no artistic talent! Take this! Conviction - Second Style!

char_159_peacok_CN_010.voiceText: ...Hoo! Hah! Wait, that's not right, that's not what's supposed to happen. Let's try this again...

char_159_peacok_CN_011.voiceText: I am Conviction. I shall use this name, with all the faith it entails, as my code name. You ask what my talents are? I am a master of the deadly and beautiful art of conviction! Need I say more?

char_159_peacok_CN_012.voiceText: An opportunity like this to become stronger is readily taken!

char_159_peacok_CN_013.voiceText: Ahaha, a promotion! The day when Conviction's hidden powers are released is not far away!

char_159_peacok_CN_014.voiceText: This sensation... it feels as if my artistic accomplishments have deepened, but also like something is being created within my body...!

char_159_peacok_CN_017.voiceText: Due to my tendency to sometimes convict teammates, it would be safer for me to work alone.

char_159_peacok_CN_018.voiceText: At last, conviction time is here!

char_159_peacok_CN_019.voiceText: The hour of judgment is nigh!

char_159_peacok_CN_024.voiceText: Is this fellow good enough to be my opponent?

char_159_peacok_CN_029.voiceText: Defeat your enemies and claim the crown... This is the doctrine of Conviction!

char_159_peacok_CN_030.voiceText: How about it! Aren't you awed by my heroic majesty-- Hey, wait up! Don't leave me behind!

char_159_peacok_CN_031.voiceText: It's fine, it's fine. It might not be the most elegant victory, but at least we got the job done.

char_159_peacok_CN_032.voiceText: Ugh... the magnificent Conviction must never allow such a blunder...

char_159_peacok_CN_033.voiceText: It's going to be hard to give this room a dose of Conviction~

char_159_peacok_CN_036.voiceText: Woahh! What are you trying to do this time! I won't let you tease me as you please!

char_159_peacok_CN_042.voiceText: Oh, if it isn't the Doctor!

char_376_therex_CN_001.voiceText: Thermal-EX, ready to commence thermal shock! What, the designated combat time has not been reached yet? Then, I shall postpone it. Commencing thermal shock after a delay of 10 seconds!

char_376_therex_CN_002.voiceText: I heard that theres some expression from the East: No martial art is infallible, except for heat.

char_376_therex_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor, its great to be with you! My burning heart wont calm down! Im talking about the Raythean Industries custom-made full-thermal Arts impact generator on my body!

char_376_therex_CN_004.voiceText: Once upon a time, God said, Let there be light, and so there was light. God said, Let there be strength, and so there was the high-performance version of Raytheans Challenger Hellcat.

char_376_therex_CN_007.voiceText: As a perfect industrial-grade mass-produced combat platform, I am very happy! Nowadays, not only do I get constant performance optimizations from Miss Mayer, but I even get to work with hot partners like Miss Blaze! Life is great!

char_376_therex_CN_008.voiceText: Even though Im already this dazzling, only you, the peerless Doctor, are worthy of becoming the brightest sun!

char_376_therex_CN_009.voiceText: I know that the heat and light I emit is so very short-lived... But all that matters is that I can illuminate the path before you, Dr. {@nickname}!

char_376_therex_CN_010.voiceText: Even when youre asleep, I can continue to work as your heater! Im incredible!

char_376_therex_CN_011.voiceText: Born from Raythean Industries, improved in the hands of the great Mayer. I, Thermal-EX, the throbbing heart of hotness, am here to help!

char_376_therex_CN_012.voiceText: Ohhhhh! This power blazing within me is... is... a hotfix!

char_376_therex_CN_017.voiceText: Now, its my turn to show off!

char_376_therex_CN_029.voiceText: Arent I awesome? I knew that your commands would make a perfect match for me, Dr. {@nickname}!

char_376_therex_CN_031.voiceText: My retreat was just a fluke. Nothing must be allowed through our net on the battlefield.

char_376_therex_CN_032.voiceText: Calculating: Imminent danger! Dropping smoke bombs! Doctor, Ill cover your retreat!

char_376_therex_CN_033.voiceText: Rest? Haha, its too early for me! I just swapped to the newest energy storage device, so there are 50 more hours until the end of todays workday!

char_376_therex_CN_034.voiceText: Uwoooahh! My thermal sensor feels your burning heart!

char_376_therex_CN_036.voiceText: Your burning enthusiasm has melted my processor!

char_376_therex_CN_042.voiceText: Welcome back, Doctor! I see that youre also full of light and heat today!

char_301_cutter_CN_001.voiceText: Excuse me, Doctor, am I on duty today... Huh? Umm, howd my blade get stuck in the doorframe...

char_301_cutter_CN_002.voiceText: Back home, the soil gets more and more barren each day, and what we harvest isnt enough to feed ourselves. Most people arent able to make a living, so their only option is to become mercenaries. Theyll do anything, as long as it pays.

char_301_cutter_CN_003.voiceText: Uhh, they said my blade was too dangerous and forbade me from going back into the kitchen. I just wanted to help, but, as soon as I tapped that cutting board with my blade, it split wide open... Well, um, should I pay for it?

char_301_cutter_CN_004.voiceText: Every time I bask in the sun, I cant help but to get a bit sleepy. But dont worry, before Ive confirmed that its completely safe, I wont actually fall... asleep... ZZZzzzzz...

char_301_cutter_CN_005.voiceText: In my line of work, I have a set of principles that I follow: I dont harm the innocent, and I dont get bystanders involved... To be honest, its really hard.

char_301_cutter_CN_006.voiceText: This necklace, Im lending it to you, its a protective charm. No, I cant give you my blade. When Im not here, just use this.

char_301_cutter_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, I need you to look at me, and dont move. Hey, I said not to move... Hm, hmm... Dont worry, youre not the kind of person who would use others to commit evil. I can tell.

char_301_cutter_CN_008.voiceText: To be honest, I dont really remember much from when I was little. My teacher raised me and taught me how to use a knife. He also told me that my parents got caught up in a fight and died because of it. When he found me, I was holding onto a knife and wouldnt let go even if it was cutting into me.

char_301_cutter_CN_009.voiceText: Those who wield the blade will always pursue the duel, and those who kill will eventually become a notch on the blade of another. Perhaps one day, I will also find such an ending... and when that happens, I hope youll be there to witness it.

char_301_cutter_CN_010.voiceText: Im standing guard, so you can rest easy.

char_301_cutter_CN_011.voiceText: Cutter. Just an ordinary mercenary. I have Oripathy, so I plan to trade my abilities for some treatment. Hope this blades good enough to get things done for you... Mm, thats about it.

char_301_cutter_CN_012.voiceText: Amazing! Didnt know you could use a blade like that!

char_301_cutter_CN_013.voiceText: Other than this blade, freedoms the only treasure I have. If youre willing to protect that, then Ill listen to you.

char_301_cutter_CN_014.voiceText: A mercenarys blade isnt some toy thats never tasted blood before. Maybe one day, Ill no longer be able to control it. But dont worry, at least for now... itll work for you.

char_301_cutter_CN_018.voiceText: Understood. Can I select my own teammates then?

char_301_cutter_CN_019.voiceText: Prepare yourself, and make sure not to get any innocents involved.

char_301_cutter_CN_024.voiceText: Wielding a blade is all I need to do.

char_301_cutter_CN_029.voiceText: Maybe one day, therell be something that my blade cant cut. But that day isnt today, and it certainly isnt you.

char_301_cutter_CN_030.voiceText: Phew... Everything done, just as specified in the contract. Need to take a look?

char_301_cutter_CN_031.voiceText: Those whove lost the will to fight should not be my targets.

char_301_cutter_CN_032.voiceText: Go, Doctor, go as far as you can! Ill... hold them back.

char_301_cutter_CN_033.voiceText: Finally, some sunlight... Ahh, so warm...

char_301_cutter_CN_034.voiceText: Uhh, dont pull on my ears.

char_301_cutter_CN_042.voiceText: Oh, Doctor, youre here. Got any work today?

char_254_vodfox_CN_001.voiceText: There are no evil spirits around you, so can I go now?

char_254_vodfox_CN_002.voiceText: Memories carry fate, and your fate has come to an abrupt end. Thats why the evil spirits no longer haunt you, but I can still clearly see their traces... Doctor, dont just blow off my words... Its for your own good.

char_254_vodfox_CN_003.voiceText: If you need someone to talk to, you can always talk to Morti here. Dont worry, Morti is here to help. When you fall asleep, all your problems will be resolved.

char_254_vodfox_CN_004.voiceText: Those emotions that make people want to cry are just food for Morti, so thats why I dont really cry. Is that bad?

char_254_vodfox_CN_005.voiceText: The true face of the curse? Do you want to see whats inside Morti? Cant... at least not for now... Thatll hurt Morti as well, and yes, those who hurt Morti will writhe in pain. Im serious.

char_254_vodfox_CN_006.voiceText: The checklist is still missing a few items: balls of yarn, used buttons, fresh apples, soil from Laterano, crushed cathode-ray tubes... Doctor, help me.

char_254_vodfox_CN_007.voiceText: Here, this apples for you. Its just a leftover from a ritual, and I dont like letting things go to waste... Why are you thanking me? I just said it wasnt specifically for you... Hey, what, stop patting my head... Ah, whatever.

char_254_vodfox_CN_008.voiceText: Because Morti is here, I have no need for emotions. But when everyone praises me, I feel a bit weird... And Morti doesnt want to take those feelings away, and its scary... Its totally fine? Really? In that case... I guess its fine.

char_254_vodfox_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, here you go. Its a clone of Morti, so make sure to keep it on you at all times... A curse? N-no, Doctor... If you take it, itll be as if Im always with you... Is that okay?

char_254_vodfox_CN_010.voiceText: Swing low~ Sweet chariot~ Be devoured by your dreams~

char_254_vodfox_CN_011.voiceText: My new name is Shamare... and this is Morti... As for the other things... itd be best if you dont find out. Like Morti said, its for everyones sake...

char_254_vodfox_CN_012.voiceText: These things wont help with the ritual...

char_254_vodfox_CN_013.voiceText: Stuff it with cotton, sew shut the mouth. Plug up the ears, and cover the eyes... There, a new doll is done.

char_254_vodfox_CN_014.voiceText: Morti has no need for a ritual like this, but... I... Im really happy. Well both do our best.

char_254_vodfox_CN_018.voiceText: If only they could be as obedient as Morti, thatd be nice.

char_254_vodfox_CN_020.voiceText: Todays fortune is... Oh, thats really bad news for you guys.

char_254_vodfox_CN_024.voiceText: Your resentment, Ill take it all.

char_254_vodfox_CN_026.voiceText: Rest at ease, and allow the land to embrace all.

char_254_vodfox_CN_029.voiceText: The evil spirits, theyre all gone now.

char_254_vodfox_CN_030.voiceText: A predestined victory, just as they whispered.

char_254_vodfox_CN_031.voiceText: Someone may have escaped, but it doesnt matter. Morti has already ensnared their fate.

char_254_vodfox_CN_033.voiceText: This place... reeks of evil spirits... Not bad.

char_254_vodfox_CN_036.voiceText: Do you want to sew something with me? Mortis also very happy...

char_333_sidero_CN_001.voiceText: There are no security risks in your room, and you can work with peace of mind. Ill stand guard at the door to help you turn down any unnecessary busywork.

char_333_sidero_CN_002.voiceText: The automatic door here is broken? Give me a minute Hrmph! All right, go ahead and carry on with your work. Ill contact the maintenance staff.

char_333_sidero_CN_003.voiceText: You want to learn more about Minoss terroir? I see, Ill put together a report for you. No, that is not information that I can clearly disclose in just a few words. I must report it to you in detail.

char_333_sidero_CN_004.voiceText: Mercenaries must always update their pool of knowledge. If you cant keep up with the newest information, youll likely fall into the hands of enemies who utilize new methods, so theres absolutely no room to slack. I hope you understand this, Doctor. Doctor?

char_333_sidero_CN_005.voiceText: Huh, what the hell did that Minosian girl in the garden do...? My head feels strangely empty, and I feel completely relaxed... This doesnt... feel right. Doctor, I need to rest. Please forgive me, Im temporarily unable to carry out my duties as your bodyguard...

char_333_sidero_CN_006.voiceText: Hoo, hah! Looks like Im in pretty good shape today, maybe itll feel even better to exercise a bit with the reserve operators. Oh, is it Hell Week again? Looks like well have to bug Dobermann again to help arrange a place for us.

char_333_sidero_CN_007.voiceText: Corinia was built upon the scales of merchants, and everyone wants to squeeze as much as they can out of everyone else. In comparison, people in other city-states are far more interesting, just like you, Doctor. When Im guarding them, theres always a lot of interesting things happening.

char_333_sidero_CN_008.voiceText: You need to train properly, Doctor. Im not just talking about moving your muscles and bones, thatd just be exercise. What Im talking about is training. It requires a full range of exercises as well as a healthy diet to burn fat and build muscle. Oh, youre fine with that? Let me see your results then. If I find out that youre Hey, Im not done talking yet, get back here!

char_333_sidero_CN_009.voiceText: Done eating again? Another bowl? Sure... This is the first time Ive made a complete meal. Usually I just fill my belly with some rations and dont cook much. Heres the last portion. After you finish, please abide by our agreement and exercise properly so that me learning this skill is not in vain.

char_333_sidero_CN_010.voiceText: Taking a nap to relax, huh? ...What a luxurious way to rest.

char_333_sidero_CN_011.voiceText: Pleased to meet you, my new employer. I am Sideroca, a Corinian mercenary. The paperwork has already been completed, so please look forward to the results of my work.

char_333_sidero_CN_012.voiceText: These clips are only good for reference. Please apply your attention to the actual battle.

char_333_sidero_CN_013.voiceText: Each badge is a symbol of trust. Ill accept it.

char_333_sidero_CN_014.voiceText: I waved my blade around and cut down all the threats. Ive done what I said I would.

char_333_sidero_CN_019.voiceText: Rest assured, Ill always pay attention to the team situation.

char_333_sidero_CN_023.voiceText: Lets see what you all can do.

char_333_sidero_CN_024.voiceText: Dont even think about taking another step.

char_333_sidero_CN_028.voiceText: Ill show you how a Minosian fights!

char_333_sidero_CN_029.voiceText: Judging from your commanding skills, my protection might be a little redundant.

char_333_sidero_CN_030.voiceText: Whats important is that you didnt get hurt. Lets get ready to head back.

char_333_sidero_CN_031.voiceText: You had to suffer through a fright because of my negligence. I am so, so sorry.

char_333_sidero_CN_032.voiceText: No matter what happens... I have to get the Doctor safely back to base...

char_333_sidero_CN_033.voiceText: Its too messy here. Im going to have to give it a good cleaning.

char_333_sidero_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor! You were the one who suggested the training, so why are you trying to run away from your own session? Stop right there!

char_401_elysm_CN_001.voiceText: Please feel free to assign any work to me. I have a lot of experience as a second-in-command.

char_401_elysm_CN_002.voiceText: This communicator can transmit signals over considerable distances and is a powerful means of communicating between teams. And, yes, my Arts can amplify the signal and ensure that communication between teams goes unimpeded. Battlefield communication, simply put, is a job that was practically made for me.

char_401_elysm_CN_003.voiceText: Lost? No worries, let me take a look. To get there, first go up the stairs on the left and head up to the fourth floor. Then turn right, and after passing the third fork, make a left. Go down a floor, then proceed to your left. Its directly across from Miss Closures #3 Engineering Room. Hows that? Were my instructions clear enough?

char_401_elysm_CN_004.voiceText: Thorns and I have reached an agreement- next time, neither of us will hold back, and a victor will be crowned. This time, Ill make sure to end his existence... Huh? Rhodes Island has an explicit ban on personal fights? You must be mistaken, Im simply talking about chess. Loser has to shave his head, what say you to this bet?

char_401_elysm_CN_005.voiceText: Of course Im also not used to being someone elses assistant, since my squad captain relies on me to deliver her orders, and I have to stay on the squad to support her. Wait, these words are just between the two of us. For both of our sakes, dont ever let her know about what I just told you, okay?

char_401_elysm_CN_006.voiceText: There is no overstating the importance of communication on the battlefield, and of course whoever facilitates that will be the first to get targeted. But dont worry, as long as Im here, Ill make sure your orders are smoothly transmitted to every combat personnel.

char_401_elysm_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, you came right on time. Actually, theres something bothering me. Why does everyone prefer looking at a map over asking me for directions? The captain said that my glib tone really gets on peoples nerves, but theres no way thats true, right? Im clearly nothing but compassionate towards everyone!

char_401_elysm_CN_008.voiceText: On the battlefield, few things are more important than morale. Do you see this banner? As a vanguard, just lifting it is enough to imbue everyone with courage Wait, Doctor, you didnt seriously believe that, did you? I was just joking, this things actually a communication device.

char_401_elysm_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, youve earned my trust. Theres no need to be so humble. I have confidence in my perception of others. How about I call you my comrade-in-arms from now on? My captain and I are like oil and water, but I believe that, much like her, you will eventually be moved by my sincerity. No? The captain sent you a letter complaining about me? Ehh?

char_401_elysm_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, the files over here are... Hm? Already asleep, huh? Well, even if its just me, you really shouldnt let your guard down like that.

char_401_elysm_CN_011.voiceText: 3rd Combat Squad, Vanguard and communications specialist, Elysium, reporting in. I do believe that this is our first time speaking face-to-face rather than through electronic means, Doctor?

char_401_elysm_CN_012.voiceText: I can see myself in a lot of these combat records. Talk about weird.

char_401_elysm_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you very much. I wont end up with a higher rank than my captain if I get promoted again, will I?

char_401_elysm_CN_014.voiceText: Ive always trusted my own judgment, Doctor. But if youre the one giving me orders, I would not question it whatsoever. After all, is that not what it means to be a comrade-in-arms?

char_401_elysm_CN_018.voiceText: Dont worry, Im just a stand-in. The captains not here right now after all.

char_401_elysm_CN_019.voiceText: In that case, lets go. Everyone, follow the route I drafted.

char_401_elysm_CN_020.voiceText: Have you finished checking the headsets?

char_401_elysm_CN_022.voiceText: The signal is stable. Ready to go at any time.

char_401_elysm_CN_023.voiceText: I wonder who our target will be.

char_401_elysm_CN_024.voiceText: Gather under this banner in the name of the Lord Hah, Ive always wanted to try saying that.

char_401_elysm_CN_026.voiceText: Who would! Use a flag! As a weapon! On the battlefield!

char_401_elysm_CN_029.voiceText: This just confirms it. We really do make the best partners.

char_401_elysm_CN_030.voiceText: Our teamworks pretty good. High five!

char_401_elysm_CN_031.voiceText: Those whove lost their fighting spirit are no longer our enemies. Lets stop here.

char_401_elysm_CN_032.voiceText: Its too dangerous. Ill make sure our last line of defense holds. Doctor, please give the order to retreat!

char_401_elysm_CN_033.voiceText: Hm? Has this room been renovated?

char_401_elysm_CN_036.voiceText: I heard that if this tuft of red hair on my head falls out, it wont ever grow back. This is a very serious problem Doctor.

char_401_elysm_CN_042.voiceText: Got any missions for me today?

char_250_phatom_CN_001.voiceText: No need to go looking for me. Ive always been here.

char_250_phatom_CN_002.voiceText: People in the dark cannot show you the way, nor can they see where you're pointing. Dont tarry here, its time for you to leave...

char_250_phatom_CN_003.voiceText: Under this mask, even I do not recognize myself.

char_250_phatom_CN_004.voiceText: This is Ms.Christine. I dont know where she came from, nor do I know when she will leave. If she likes you, she will approach you on her own... Yes, just as shes doing right now.

char_250_phatom_CN_005.voiceText: In the past, I was not lonely. I used to have several friends, and we used to travel all over the world as a theatre troupe. But when Oripathy broke out, thats when everything ended, and everything began...

char_250_phatom_CN_006.voiceText: This darkness is a refuge, a throne, and paradise. The spirits of the dead have never left, and Ive cursed the world from atop their bones... Seeing me as I am now, do you still want to hear my song? Do you still dare... to stand before me?

char_250_phatom_CN_007.voiceText: This device embedded above my throat compresses my neck, but it is exactly what I need. Like a mask, it conceals my sins and my voice. Youd like to hear my real voice? No, you cant. Its not something you should have to bear...

char_250_phatom_CN_008.voiceText: My song ended all of their lives. On that endless night, the song that wouldnt stop, those quivering trebles and organ fragments that I kept vomiting from my throat... Frightening and suffocating, but so... miraculous. Doctor, tell me. Back then... what did I really do?

char_250_phatom_CN_009.voiceText: I can end many lives for you, but I first need you to confirm that I am awake. Something is trying to influence me. It doesnt want me to leave the stage. It wants my song to echo forever... and it wants me to kill you. Before I play the role of your assassin once more, I must discover the truth.

char_250_phatom_CN_010.voiceText: The shadows have never left your side, even when it is not nighttime. Do be careful of your untimely somnolence, Doctor.

char_250_phatom_CN_011.voiceText: Code name, Phantom. The Phantom Behind the Curtain, Gaspard de la Nuit. Tell me, who are your enemies, and where do they hide...

char_250_phatom_CN_012.voiceText: Killing is not an end, but a means.

char_250_phatom_CN_013.voiceText: As you wish. You are the one who sets Rhodes Islands tune, and you require neither guide nor guardian... Yes, I know all too well, you are your own master.

char_250_phatom_CN_014.voiceText: There is no looking back after this step, no turning back. What I am about to share with you is not as wonderful as you may believe... Come, come here, and allow me to show you what lies beneath the veil of night.

char_250_phatom_CN_017.voiceText: Is it time for me to take the stage?

char_250_phatom_CN_018.voiceText: I am no stranger to giving guidance.

char_250_phatom_CN_020.voiceText: Let us raise the curtains on this play.

char_250_phatom_CN_022.voiceText: So, let us sink into the night.

char_250_phatom_CN_024.voiceText: Hear my voice. Hear my song.

char_250_phatom_CN_025.voiceText: Do you see your own face within the mirror?

char_250_phatom_CN_026.voiceText: The actors are all puppets of the script.

char_250_phatom_CN_028.voiceText: Yes, lift your voices! Sing for me! Sing for me!

char_250_phatom_CN_029.voiceText: Is this the victory that your leadership has brought...

char_250_phatom_CN_030.voiceText: It is over. Victory is not sweet, as conflict always leaves an aftertaste.

char_250_phatom_CN_031.voiceText: They escaped. Fortunate for them... and perhaps for me as well.

char_250_phatom_CN_032.voiceText: Fall back. ......Youve already lost your way.

char_250_phatom_CN_033.voiceText: Hm? Behind this mirror, it seems as if...

char_250_phatom_CN_036.voiceText: The sound of these footsteps... Its you, Doctor.

char_250_phatom_CN_042.voiceText: The shadow behind you looks heavier than it was yesterday, Doctor.

char_400_weedy_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, youve managed to keep your room clean. Not bad.

char_400_weedy_CN_002.voiceText: Water is the core ingredient of life. Ive talked to Miss Closure about improving Rhodes Islands water purification system. I hope that my research can be of help... so I dont have to worry about the water being dirty anymore.

char_400_weedy_CN_003.voiceText: This is Leaf, a Bionic Seadragon that I produced from a prototype design passed across my family. In addition to auxiliary combat functions, he helps out a lot in my daily life, such as pouring water, lifting heavy things, and so on.

char_400_weedy_CN_004.voiceText: Glaucus and I agreed that wed conduct our automation engineering experiment at about this time. Doctor, if youre interested, want to come take a look?

char_400_weedy_CN_005.voiceText: These reserve water cannons were originally made for industrial usage. In addition to shooting pressurized water, they can also release high-temperature steam. Please dont touch them haphazardly; theyre not like Closures little buggies.

char_400_weedy_CN_006.voiceText: These high-level combat data materials are based upon my own summaries of the combat situation. Doctor, please read them carefully for the sake of future battles. After that, there are a few operation-related experiments Id like to perfect that I will need your help on. I trust that you wont turn me down?

char_400_weedy_CN_007.voiceText: I occasionally go to Perfumers Convalescence Garden to relax. The aroma there can really wash all your stress away, and its a very effective way of relieving the fatigue from research. Doctor, how about we head there together and give it a try next time?

char_400_weedy_CN_008.voiceText: I definitely do not talk to my Bionic Seadragons when Im alone! I only gave him a name to help distinguish him more easily!

char_400_weedy_CN_009.voiceText: Thanks to your compassion, Ive recently become more accustomed to having you around, Doctor. And apart from Glaucus and some other research colleagues, I cant say that about many people.

char_400_weedy_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, Im Weedy from Rhodes Islands Engineering Department. Ive heard of your name a long time ago, so I hope well have a productive relationship from now on. Ah, if you want to shake hands, please use your gloved right hand.

char_400_weedy_CN_012.voiceText: Hmm, I didnt expect these to be this helpful.

char_400_weedy_CN_013.voiceText: After my promotion, can I get another upgrade to my personal room?

char_400_weedy_CN_014.voiceText: Thank you for acknowledging someone as frail as I am, Doctor. Ill continue to work hard for the sake of Rhodes Island.

char_400_weedy_CN_020.voiceText: Everything is as we planned. To battle!

char_400_weedy_CN_029.voiceText: Everythings a piece of cake, as long as we employ the proper tactics.

char_400_weedy_CN_030.voiceText: Dont underestimate the importance of engineering!

char_400_weedy_CN_031.voiceText: ...After I head back and adjust the parameters of this device, this wont happen again.

char_400_weedy_CN_033.voiceText: Has this place been cleaned before?

char_400_weedy_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, is there anything I can help you with?

char_113_cqbw_CN_001.voiceText: Truthfully, Ive thought up countless possibilities about coming back here, looking out at the same scenery that she saw that day... But I never could have imagined that Id actually be standing here with you. Its all too outrageous, Doctor.

char_113_cqbw_CN_002.voiceText: Whered I go? Cant tell you. Kal'tsit bypassed you and directly gave me this order... Dont believe me? Guess the amount of trust you have in her is really telling. Fine, fine. I just went to splurge on some stuff. Just a bunch of clothes, and Ive already gone through inspection. What, are you surprised?

char_113_cqbw_CN_003.voiceText: There are a few cute little operators who always grit their teeth when they look at me, but when are they gonna actually do something...? Kal'tsit already explained the situation? Theyre dealing with it? The hells up with that? This place really should show some respect for personal goals and needs. Just let em do it because like, Im totally bored anyway.

char_113_cqbw_CN_004.voiceText: You used to like working with us a whole bunch. Mercenaries are efficient instruments of war; like fast food, ready to eat and easily disposable. You want to know what happened? Hmm, some people would prefer that I keep my mouth shut about that topic~ Must be such a blessing to not remember anything, right?

char_113_cqbw_CN_005.voiceText: Save the Infected? Almost all the Sarkaz in Kazdel are infected, and you havent even seen the kinds of oppression and conflict that go on there... So, how far do you plan to go with your salvation? For someone like Kaltsit, who cant even protect a single Sarkaz, and for the person youve now become, what exactly do you intend to do?

char_113_cqbw_CN_006.voiceText: I want to know, if these idealistic and starry-eyed operators had witnessed those kind and gentle people die one by one, would they still do things the same way, with the same old song and dance? Hey, Im not trying to look down on anyone. Im just reminding you, dont just go twisting that persons ideas into some simple-minded mockery.

char_113_cqbw_CN_007.voiceText: Hey you, about that thing on Amiyas body, yknow that Kal'tsit is keeping stuff from you, right? Luckily, you can gain the trust of others when you dont remember anything, but no, its stranger that you can even trust other people. I have no idea what those two would say if they saw the way you are now.

char_113_cqbw_CN_008.voiceText: There really are all sorts of people here. More weirdos here than before. Ah, dont get me wrong, I dont give a shit about what the likes of them think about me but Ive gotta say, Amiyas doing a pretty good job. At least shes working hard to become more like that person, and Ive gotta respect that.

char_113_cqbw_CN_009.voiceText: Dr. {@nickname}, since nobodys ever mentioned this to you before, Im pretty curious how youll react when you start to remember that incident No need to look all confused. For now, just remember this name: Theresa. Yes, Theresa.

char_113_cqbw_CN_010.voiceText: You're pretty freewheeling. Never thought thered come a day when THE Dr. {@nickname} would be napping here completely defenseless... You forget the past and sleep that easy, huh?

char_113_cqbw_CN_011.voiceText: Sarkaz mercenary, W. Its been a while, though Im sure that means something altogether different to you. But dont worry, considering the you of the present is not the you that Im looking for, consider yourself safe for the time being. Just for the time being.

char_113_cqbw_CN_012.voiceText: This is all too familiar, almost terrifyingly so. Hey you, are you sure you lost your memories?

char_113_cqbw_CN_013.voiceText: Sure, Im listening. Didnt think you were the type to personally micromanage the small stuff. But yknow, Id much rather snatch something like this than have it be given freely.

char_113_cqbw_CN_014.voiceText: The fact that Id get to fight alongside you the way you are now is certainly a charming little twist of fate. Why look, turns out as long as you dont remember what happened that day, the two of us can get along after all.

char_113_cqbw_CN_017.voiceText: The two of us, lets both try to survive.

char_113_cqbw_CN_018.voiceText: A mercenarys leadership focuses on practicality. Dont expect me to babysit others.

char_113_cqbw_CN_020.voiceText: Just gotta kill them all to finish the job, right? Dont think in such simple terms? But thats a pain in the ass...

char_113_cqbw_CN_023.voiceText: Who knows, I might sneak off to somewhere else.

char_113_cqbw_CN_024.voiceText: Nice, Ill take a nice nap over here.

char_113_cqbw_CN_025.voiceText: Whos gonna hit the jackpot today?

char_113_cqbw_CN_026.voiceText: Step right up, plenty of surprises for everyone~

char_113_cqbw_CN_027.voiceText: Ill give you until the count of three to surrender. Three~

char_113_cqbw_CN_029.voiceText: Seeing you draw out the full extent of everyones power on the battlefield... Its a bit nostalgic.

char_113_cqbw_CN_030.voiceText: Did you see that guys face just now? That absolute despair when he realized he was going to get blown apart and couldnt do a thing about it, have you ever seen anything funnier?

char_113_cqbw_CN_031.voiceText: Its rare for you to make mistakes like this. Are you getting rusty, or do you have more things worrying you?

char_113_cqbw_CN_032.voiceText: Retreat? Keep casualties to a minimum? Heh, hard to imagine Im hearing those words from your mouth.

char_113_cqbw_CN_033.voiceText: This doors already been repaired, huh.

char_113_cqbw_CN_034.voiceText: Looks like theres a lot more stuff here, but far fewer people.

char_113_cqbw_CN_036.voiceText: ...Which side of you is the real one?

char_113_cqbw_CN_042.voiceText: Dr. {@nickname}, what would you like to do for Rhodes Island today? The same as usual?

char_405_absin_CN_001.voiceText: Why do I keep my weapon right here? Didnt I already tell you? You need to be able to work in peace, and anyone who wants to bother you is going to have to answer to my little friend first.

char_405_absin_CN_002.voiceText: This is a nice place. Everyone follows their orders and goes about their business, like an ideal island paradise isolated from reality.

char_405_absin_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor, those students over there, are they all from Chernobog? Theyre all from the same middle school? ...I see, I need to observe them a bit more.

char_405_absin_CN_004.voiceText: Were you the one commanding at Chernobog? If thats the case, you also should have seen the conditions over there. Doctor, why have you stayed silent this entire time? Id never be able to do that...

char_405_absin_CN_005.voiceText: I did a good job? Someone like me who fled from her homeland, with no achievements to speak of, was really able to be of some use? ...Umm, what are you... Why are you patting my head?

char_405_absin_CN_006.voiceText: Who needs my protection? Who can I protect? Since that cataclysm, Ive always been asking myself... I saw the malice in people's hearts spill out until it eventually drowned the city. Under those circumstances, perhaps justice is no longer worth mentioning, and no longer exist.

char_405_absin_CN_007.voiceText: Whats wrong with my hair? Huh, its a little messy? Thats just the way it is. Had to cut it myself when I fled the city... Umm, whats with that expression? Dont worry about it. Its just hair after all, itll grow back by itself eventually.

char_405_absin_CN_008.voiceText: This equipment belonged to my father, a police officer who dedicated himself to protecting the public each and every day. I can understand, and Ive never blamed him, neither I nor my mother. Its just that... Doctor, everything my father did, was it really worth it?

char_405_absin_CN_009.voiceText: Those people, the expressions on those citizens faces, became identical to the ones of the murderers that destroyed the city. But they were clearly the people my father and I were supposed to protect. Doctor, what is actually just in this world, and what is it, that I should do... I just dont know...

char_405_absin_CN_010.voiceText: So sleepy... But I cant afford to... fall asleep... *yawn*...

char_405_absin_CN_011.voiceText: Thank you for rescuing me; this life is yours to spend. Though theres not much Im capable of, if you ever find some way for me to be useful, please let me know. Code name? ......Um, why dont you just call me Absinthe.

char_405_absin_CN_012.voiceText: Whats the point of watching this stuff?

char_405_absin_CN_013.voiceText: Theres no need for a promotion. Ive already been taken care of enough here... Um, I have to take it? I see, then, umm, thank you.

char_405_absin_CN_014.voiceText: I still have not been able to figure out what justice truly is. But you said to me before, everything Ive insisted on is not without purpose... Perhaps you are right, that is what I want to believe.

char_405_absin_CN_018.voiceText: Whoever the squad leader is, whats the status on the... Huh, its me?

char_405_absin_CN_020.voiceText: Stop! There are suspicious people thirty meters in front of us... Oh, those guys again?

char_405_absin_CN_023.voiceText: Raid drill! Hands on your head! No moving!

char_405_absin_CN_027.voiceText: This is your last warning! Get ready to shoot!

char_405_absin_CN_028.voiceText: Why must it always come to this...

char_405_absin_CN_029.voiceText: If only you were there back then, perhaps...

char_405_absin_CN_030.voiceText: Mission complete. Doctor, youre not injured, are you?

char_405_absin_CN_031.voiceText: Do you think there were any Chernobog citizens among these people?

char_405_absin_CN_032.voiceText: Panic and chaos are breaking loose! We need to retreat, quickly, quickly!!

char_405_absin_CN_033.voiceText: This terrace... if enough snow built up on it, you could jump off like this and have a great time. Hup!

char_405_absin_CN_036.voiceText: Oh, Doctor. Are you thirsty? Here, lets have a drink.

char_405_absin_CN_042.voiceText: Whats with you? Want something to help wake you up?

char_373_lionhd_CN_001.voiceText: Hm? Doctor, did you want to have a chat with me to stave off the boredom? Or, did you have something interesting you must tell me?

char_373_lionhd_CN_002.voiceText: Was that Savage who just passed by in the hallway? Back when the autonomous prefecture was established, and later when it reached a cooperation agreement with Rim Billiton, her exploits were no less impressive than mine, you know?

char_373_lionhd_CN_003.voiceText: You know, some places have really problematic stereotypes about us Cautus. Why do they call me timid when Im just good at avoiding danger? As a matter of fact, isnt it more accurate to say that only those whove delved deep into danger can become masters of avoiding it?

char_373_lionhd_CN_004.voiceText: Cmon, Ive been taking my medications like Im supposed to, but the little lass from the Medical Department whos taking care of me is a bit too uptight, I just cant help but to play pranks on her. You should help her loosen up a bit. Oh, but dont tell that to the other medics.

char_373_lionhd_CN_005.voiceText: Doctor, my buddy, Rhodes Island doesnt have a mandatory dress code, so theres no need for you to wear the same old rags all the time. Look at what Im wearing - this stores got some pretty tasteful stuff, so how about I help you pick out a new look?

char_373_lionhd_CN_006.voiceText: Im actually pretty fond of Rhodes Island. Unlike those bigwigs who cant stop preaching and proselytizing their greatness, everyone heres just trying to achieve their goals and work together to keep this ship sailing. Just like the folks at Rim Billiton.

char_373_lionhd_CN_007.voiceText: The one in my hand? Its a standard-issue Rim Billiton blaster that I modified. Before it was modified, it also used to be an Originium-powered focus for Casters. Hmm... Doctor, youre not thinking that using brute force alone to smash open a rock is the most efficient method, are you?

char_373_lionhd_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, are you also interested in hearing about the Eureka Incident? Im not sure there are any secrets left, since there are maybe a dozen pretty good books and documentaries out there. But maybe itd be better if I could write something more detailed about how I rescued those hostages. Yeah, I dismantled a lot of those cages after all.

char_373_lionhd_CN_009.voiceText: Its not uncommon for mining teams to hire Catastrophe Messengers to accompany them. For example, I was born on a mining ship and was always interested in technical books, so I was basically just applying what I already knew. But Doctor, whered you get your knowledge from? I dont think Ive seen any relevant literature here.

char_373_lionhd_CN_010.voiceText: Wanted to take a little nap? No worries, Ill wake you up unceremoniously in the event of emergency!

char_373_lionhd_CN_011.voiceText: Leonhardt, Catastrophe Messenger. Doctor, I dont know if you mightve heard of me before... No? Ah, its better that way. Seems like I wont have to tell the entire story again like I had to when that lady from the HR Department cornered me.

char_373_lionhd_CN_012.voiceText: Looks like my skills are better suited for positional warfare.

char_373_lionhd_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion? Sure, sure... Huh? It doesn't even come with some sort of exclusive, blinged-out elite uniform? Cmon, even a small piece of jewelry would be fine. No? Aww

char_373_lionhd_CN_014.voiceText: The road that Rhodes Island has chosen to take is much bumpier than that of us Catastrophe Messengers, but you dont seem to have any intent on stopping. I suppose Ill have to sacrifice some of my entertainment time to help you clear the road then?

char_373_lionhd_CN_017.voiceText: Its my turn! Huh? The mission this time is to go fight someone?

char_373_lionhd_CN_018.voiceText: You want me to lead the team? Mm, sure. That can be done, piece of cake.

char_373_lionhd_CN_019.voiceText: So this is the route to the objective goal... Can I take a shortcut?

char_373_lionhd_CN_020.voiceText: Lets see if our enemies have anything going for them besides their numbers.

char_373_lionhd_CN_022.voiceText: Doctor, youll save a nice spot for me right?

char_373_lionhd_CN_024.voiceText: Lure more enemies into this ring, then leave the rest to me!

char_373_lionhd_CN_025.voiceText: Who said the tip of a spear is only good for stabbing people?

char_373_lionhd_CN_026.voiceText: Relying on your armor will only make you vulnerable.

char_373_lionhd_CN_027.voiceText: Oh~ Strength in numbers, huh... Is that what you were banking on?

char_373_lionhd_CN_028.voiceText: Lets see whether youre gold or manure!

char_373_lionhd_CN_029.voiceText: Bam! All right, another mighty enemy laid low. Now, lets do what we agreed on and have you treat yourself, Doctor. Wanna go visit a local market with me on our next stop?

char_373_lionhd_CN_030.voiceText: Enemies of this caliber pose no threat to us, right?

char_373_lionhd_CN_031.voiceText: Cleaning up stragglers isnt really my strong suit, so if you dont find someone to send after them, youre going to lose points off your combat evaluation~

char_373_lionhd_CN_032.voiceText: Whoops, looks like we messed up. Doctor, go ahead and withdraw first. Dont worry, as long as Im here, theres no chance of the enemy catching up.

char_373_lionhd_CN_033.voiceText: Wanna head down to the Procurement Department to take a look at the new outfits? How about it?

char_373_lionhd_CN_036.voiceText: Whats the matter, did you want to take me out for a walk?

char_373_lionhd_CN_042.voiceText: Yo, Doctor, done with work for the day?

char_378_asbest_CN_001.voiceText: If youve got something to say, spit it out. If you wanna pass gas, just make it quick. Im busy as hell and dont have time for you.

char_378_asbest_CN_002.voiceText: Hey! ...You asshole, who gave you permission to touch my tail? Watch it or Ill punt your sorry ass! And, forget all about that sound I made just now, Ill help you forget it physically.

char_378_asbest_CN_003.voiceText: This ol door I have here? Cant you tell? I made it myself, its multifunctional. Id advise you not to touch it, or you might get yourself killed.

char_378_asbest_CN_004.voiceText: Ive gotta say, since Rhodes Island is gonna be traveling all over anyway, its faster for me to follow you as I explore than going around on my own. Mm, yeah, I guess Ive changed my view towards you guys a little.

char_378_asbest_CN_005.voiceText: Dont compare me to Magallan. Im no professional explorer, I just run around the world chasing thrills. Trailblazing for those who come after me? I sure as hell aint that noble.

char_378_asbest_CN_006.voiceText: The more dangerous it is, the more I wanna go. The crazier it is, the more I wanna cut loose. Otherwise, life has no meaning.

char_378_asbest_CN_007.voiceText: Magallan? Me and this shrimpy, overzealous videographer girl I got to know her at the Black Flow. Yknow, thats the wildest, craziest adventure Ive ever been on. But, that shrimps got some real skills, Ill be the first to admit.

char_378_asbest_CN_008.voiceText: Friends? Who the hell needs those? My life goal here is to just be an absolute jerk to everyone. So, best not try to get chummy with me, since Im not gonna return the favor. Rather, how bout we go out for a drink instead? Give it to me straight.

char_378_asbest_CN_009.voiceText: My illness? I know its pretty serious, but as long as I dont cause trouble for anyone, how I deal with it is up to me. And thats an easy one - theres nothing wrong with dying on a journey. If you think youre hot shit, you can try to bring me back. Do your worst, Doctor. Im expecting nothing from you.

char_378_asbest_CN_010.voiceText: Sleeping, huh? Good, time to make some noise. Ahaha!

char_378_asbest_CN_011.voiceText: Even though out exploring for a better portion of the year, you still plan to have me on the payroll and even assign me a dorm? And you seriously want an operator like that? ...Oh, you do? Huh? Tsk, something wrong with your head?

char_378_asbest_CN_012.voiceText: Well, whatever. Guess Ill learn some self-defense.

char_378_asbest_CN_013.voiceText: Honorary Captain of the Rhodes Island Research Team? Me? Hah?

char_378_asbest_CN_014.voiceText: I cant guarantee that Ill be able to do anything for Rhodes Island, since thats not my style. However, if there are any mysteries of this world youd like to uncover, Ill be the one to get the job done.

char_378_asbest_CN_018.voiceText: Tsk... If you wanna make my life hard, just say it to my face.

char_378_asbest_CN_019.voiceText: If you cant keep up, just find something to keep yourself busy.

char_378_asbest_CN_020.voiceText: Tsk... What a pain in the ass.

char_378_asbest_CN_029.voiceText: Ive braved the winds and the waves. Something like this aint worth shit.

char_378_asbest_CN_030.voiceText: *sigh* ...How boring. Im gonna take a look around.

char_378_asbest_CN_032.voiceText: Tsk... Am I supposed to comfort this bastard now...?

char_378_asbest_CN_033.voiceText: Time to head back to the dorms and crash.

char_378_asbest_CN_036.voiceText: Oh right, gotta take a trip to the Doctors office first.

char_378_asbest_CN_042.voiceText: You got a lot of free time?

char_343_tknogi_CN_001.voiceText: You should take a little break. Its good for you. Of course that is true, arent you glad to hear that?

char_343_tknogi_CN_002.voiceText: Those who chase Catastrophes. Catastrophe Patrols. Or as they say here, Catastrophe Messengers. The job is bitter and tiring, and we are often ridiculed by ordinary civilians and bureaucrats alike. Will my lot improve as an operator? No? Haha, such is life.

char_343_tknogi_CN_003.voiceText: Tomorrow... Ah, um, I see. My dear boss, remember to bring an umbrella with you when you leave tomorrow.

char_343_tknogi_CN_004.voiceText: If I could have stayed in Higashi, I would not have come all the way here. But... with these things planted inside my flesh, how could I consider anywhere my home?

char_343_tknogi_CN_005.voiceText: It is better to give your salary to those in need than to store it inside your abode. Considering how little there is, if you put it within the hands of someone in need, just seeing their smile and hearing the words of appreciation is enough to warm my heart.

char_343_tknogi_CN_006.voiceText: I often wonder if the strange words that occasionally come from my mouth are born of my own consciousness, or if they are bestowed upon me by the Great Spirit who I have never met. The ritual verses of my relatives are all drawn from ancient scriptures, but Ive always blurted mine out. It is quite distressing.

char_343_tknogi_CN_007.voiceText: Again and again we prance, posture, sing, and pray, with no tolerance for the slightest discrepancies. Some people find joy in filling their lives with these things, and tell others that it will bring joy to the high heavens. How truly sinful.

char_343_tknogi_CN_008.voiceText: My clan and I lived in the mountains, not far from a Shinto shrine. At the foot of the mountain was a Buddhist temple, where the monks would return to at night. Now for the question, Doctor. What do you think would happen? Hehe, I shall leave the answer on your table, feel free to take a look when you have time.

char_343_tknogi_CN_009.voiceText: Up so late? Do you still have something on your mind? Being thoughtful and eloquent is your strong suit, but just dont let it get in the way of your sleep. Here, I have some incense from Higashi for you, what do you think of the scent? Oh my, the effect seems to be a bit too strong? Heh, I suppose I shall stand guard for you tonight.

char_343_tknogi_CN_010.voiceText: Close your eyes, and calm your mind. Good~

char_343_tknogi_CN_011.voiceText: Pleased to meet you. It simply would not do if I was to forget my introduction, yes? I am Tsukinogi, formerly part of a small Catastrophe Patrol in Higashi. It is an honor to be able to work under you.

char_343_tknogi_CN_013.voiceText: Oh, a reward? Now, now, how should I use this?

char_343_tknogi_CN_014.voiceText: The white night is a raging fire, through which a dark haze lingers. I asketh thee, where dost thy steps cease? Take things one step at a time, and do not stray off the path.

char_343_tknogi_CN_017.voiceText: I will not fall short of your expectations.

char_343_tknogi_CN_018.voiceText: Great is the responsibility of leading others.

char_343_tknogi_CN_019.voiceText: The time has come. Let us go.

char_343_tknogi_CN_020.voiceText: There are more important things to do than pray.

char_343_tknogi_CN_026.voiceText: Drown in the gloaming, and never return.

char_343_tknogi_CN_027.voiceText: Wander through this vast land, blind and ignorant.

char_343_tknogi_CN_028.voiceText: O exalted brilliance, separate us from harm!

char_343_tknogi_CN_029.voiceText: I was not able to help at all, but that is a cause for celebration.

char_343_tknogi_CN_030.voiceText: Congratulations. A perfect conclusion to this mission.

char_343_tknogi_CN_031.voiceText: The small issues that besmirch our results can be left to me. You may take your leave.

char_343_tknogi_CN_032.voiceText: The consequences of our recklessness have been unsatisfactory. Let us reflect upon them once more.

char_343_tknogi_CN_033.voiceText: I have no requests for my accommodations, so please assign me as you wish.

char_343_tknogi_CN_036.voiceText: If there is anything displeasing to you, please let me know. Yes, anything at all.

char_197_poca_CN_001.voiceText: It is an honor to serve you, Doctor.

char_197_poca_CN_002.voiceText: I was once naive enough to think I could have anything I wanted. Now I know that while it is true for most things, it is not for others. Those I can never get, not on my own.

char_197_poca_CN_003.voiceText: Any work you might have, I hope you will let me try. Dont worry, after what Ive been through, the dignity of a noblewoman is the least of my worries. Now I am just like Zima and the girls, an ordinary student under protection.

char_197_poca_CN_004.voiceText: Doctor, if you would like to know more about Chernobog, I may be able to provide a unique perspective. I was only a student, but you know, the Student Council President does interact with society at large, in some ways.

char_197_poca_CN_005.voiceText: People like Istina, who forgo the opiate that is entertainment in pursuit of greater knowledge, are quite rare. Even at a noble school like I attended. If she had been my classmate back then... No, its no use thinking about that now.

char_197_poca_CN_006.voiceText: To hate the world on account of a tragedy is as shortsighted as loving the world over a comedyIs it? Doctor, have you already decided how to handle all that you will soon face? And how should I? Im still unsure.

char_197_poca_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, I have a favor to ask of you. Would you please look after Zima and the girls... specifically their mental health? They look like theyre adjusting well, but I know theyre not. Even I, occasionally, think back to those times...

char_197_poca_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, I wonder if you could ever understand? I was a victim, at times, I know. And at times, I found myself on the other side. I... I can never forgive myself for that.

char_197_poca_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, is it easier to forget, when youre fully grown? When I come of age, will I be able to forgive myself? Will becoming as mature as you allow me to finally deal with the misery in my heart?

char_197_poca_CN_010.voiceText: The Doctor is asleep... kind of cute, isnt it?

char_197_poca_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, Doctor. Allow me to once again express my gratitude to Rhodes Island for taking in me and my friends. Ive had enough of a break working in Logistics, and Id like to do as Zima and the girls do.

char_197_poca_CN_012.voiceText: I too must prepare for the battlefield...

char_197_poca_CN_013.voiceText: It seems my experience in student government is paying dividends in my work life. How delightful.

char_197_poca_CN_014.voiceText: There is still much I dont understand about what I am doing, about my future, about myself, and about so much more. But I am young. I still have time to think. Dont I, Doctor?

char_197_poca_CN_017.voiceText: Let us put my training to the test.

char_197_poca_CN_018.voiceText: I will do all I can.

char_197_poca_CN_020.voiceText: Comrades, let us keep to the plan.

char_197_poca_CN_027.voiceText: Rosa, believe in yourself. You can do it!

char_197_poca_CN_028.voiceText: There may not be enmity between us...

char_197_poca_CN_029.voiceText: Doctor, we did it...! Ah, oh, what a delightful victory.

char_197_poca_CN_030.voiceText: Ah, we met the Doctors expectations.

char_197_poca_CN_031.voiceText: Doctor, my apologies, if we had tried harder...

char_197_poca_CN_032.voiceText: We must review this carefully after we get back...

char_197_poca_CN_033.voiceText: I wonder if theres anywhere quite like the salon?

char_197_poca_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, its great to see you.

char_258_podego_CN_001.voiceText: Ehehe~ Oh, Doctor, is your day going well?

char_258_podego_CN_002.voiceText: This is a floral tea that I made myself! Doctor, come try a cup, I promise youll feel cozy all day!

char_258_podego_CN_003.voiceText: The sunlight in the greenhouse is so comfortable. Even though Im an operator, it sometimes makes me want to slack.

char_258_podego_CN_004.voiceText: Use the fruits of your labor to make everyone forget about their sorrows and worries. Thats probably the tenet of all gardeners, dont you think~?

char_258_podego_CN_005.voiceText: I much rather prefer growing things to destroying them. But as long as I think about how I can help everyone, I can muster up my courage.

char_258_podego_CN_006.voiceText: These bottles? Inside are all the pollen and seeds that Ive been collecting. I usually wear a gas mask and gloves before handling them, or I might get poisoned.

char_258_podego_CN_007.voiceText: Umm, everyone seems to be a bit weary these days. But, Im sure theyll cheer right back up when they see the flowers Ive planted!

char_258_podego_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, Doctor! Are you coming to the greenhouse today? It seems like everyones been really busy the last few days... If nobody comes by the greenhouse, the blooming seasons going to pass right by. Wouldnt that be a darn shame?

char_258_podego_CN_009.voiceText: Tending to the greenhouse is really hard. But, as long as I can make others smile with the flowers I grow, all my hard work will be worth it!

char_258_podego_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor? Oh, youre asleep... I hope the fragrance of these petals can drift over to your dreams.

char_258_podego_CN_011.voiceText: Doctor, this is Podenco, here to say hi! If you have time, Id love if you could come by the greenhouse!

char_258_podego_CN_012.voiceText: Aw, I thought this was a video about gardening techniques.

char_258_podego_CN_013.voiceText: Artist? N-n-no, Im just a normal gardener.

char_258_podego_CN_014.voiceText: Look, Doctor! The new varieties Ive been tending to for so long have finally started to bloom! Arent they so pretty?

char_258_podego_CN_017.voiceText: Hm? Am I coming along as well?

char_258_podego_CN_018.voiceText: Ah... I only have experience in tending a greenhouse. Is there anything I can do?

char_258_podego_CN_019.voiceText: I see the enemy! Everyone, lets go!

char_258_podego_CN_020.voiceText: Everyone, make sure to take care of yourselves!

char_258_podego_CN_026.voiceText: Ah, Ill take care of them.

char_258_podego_CN_027.voiceText: Ive seen weeds like these before.

char_258_podego_CN_029.voiceText: Phew, is it safe already? Good job, everyone!

char_258_podego_CN_030.voiceText: Achieving a flawless victory is like cultivating a beautiful flower. Both require a lot of hard work.

char_258_podego_CN_031.voiceText: Doctor, everyone is awaiting your next orders.

char_258_podego_CN_032.voiceText: Ah... I never thought things could become like this...

char_258_podego_CN_033.voiceText: Shall we plant some flowers over here?

char_258_podego_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor! Would you like to decorate your office with some flowers?

char_358_lisa_CN_001.voiceText: Do you need any help, Doctor? Then, Ill do my homework later...

char_358_lisa_CN_002.voiceText: Youd like to know more about my tails? Well, after I came to Rhodes Island, I realized that I have more tails than the other Vulpo sisters here, and I dont know who I should talk to about it... But, the people my dad worked with all had a lot of tails... How strange.

char_358_lisa_CN_003.voiceText: Upset? Thank you for your concern, Doctor. Everyone treats me well, so I cant be too needy, but... the beds here at Rhodes Island are a bit small, and its hard to manage all my tails when Im trying to sleep at night; And, someones always watering the potted plants Ive been growing, but they dont need that much attention.

char_358_lisa_CN_004.voiceText: Big sister Amiya is really amazing. She always has so many ideas that I havent thought of, and shes a great role model. But, shes also just like me. Shes not an adult yet, so shell sometimes feel lost and confused. Doctor, you should spend more time with her.

char_358_lisa_CN_005.voiceText: That first time I took a really long ride from Higashi to Siracusa, I was so surprised! I never knew that other places could look so different! Even though right now I can only stay behind my mentors, and not all my memories are rosy, I still really love my life right now. Mhm!

char_358_lisa_CN_006.voiceText: The flame that my dad conjured was very beautiful. Of course it was fire, but it looked like crystal. After I came to Rhodes Island, I realized that it was the power my dad used to protect others. I can use what he taught me to help my mentors here! So, Ill continue to do my best!

char_358_lisa_CN_007.voiceText: Since my arm was injured, my mom has rarely let me go out. I dont blame her though, and Im even more worried about how shes going to deal with those bad people. Thats why I should live the best life I can right now, so she doesnt have to worry about anything, right? As long as she stays calm, shes super strong!

char_358_lisa_CN_008.voiceText: Although I havent been an operator for very long, I know that what were doing is very difficult, right? Even though my mentors are always chatting and laughing, theyre also hiding their thoughts and feelings. If I can become a bit stronger, will I be able to help them share their troubles?

char_358_lisa_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, you... lost your memories? Really? Dr. Kal'tsit only just told me about this today... Um, you should rest for the day. You also need some time to think about this, right? Just leave the rest of the work to me and, um, go spend some time with Amiya! Hehe!

char_358_lisa_CN_010.voiceText: Youll catch a cold like this. Ill need to find a blanket...

char_358_lisa_CN_011.voiceText: Rhodes Island Operator, Lisa... Ah, I mean, Suzuran! Operator Suzuran! Its the code name I chose for myself. Starting today, Im officially an operator, so Ill be in your care!

char_358_lisa_CN_012.voiceText: S-so this is how my mentors fight... They seem so powerful...

char_358_lisa_CN_013.voiceText: Doctor, earlier today, Dr. Kal'tsit praised me... Um, a promotion? Not just praise? Eh?

char_358_lisa_CN_014.voiceText: Look, Doctor! Look at my Originium Arts! Ive been working so hard on this! Now Ill be able to go to more places with my mentors, see more things, and help more people, right?

char_358_lisa_CN_017.voiceText: Ill make sure to work hard and make good use of this opportunity!

char_358_lisa_CN_018.voiceText: Eh, Ill be leading my mentors? O-okay, leave it to me! As the captain, I mustnt be too weak!

char_358_lisa_CN_020.voiceText: The enemy appeared! Um, cant we persuade them to give up?

char_358_lisa_CN_023.voiceText: Dont be nervous, dont be nervous.

char_358_lisa_CN_024.voiceText: We can all do this! Mm!

char_358_lisa_CN_026.voiceText: Is everyone okay? Everyones safe, right?

char_358_lisa_CN_029.voiceText: So this is the actual battlefield that my mentors faced... Doctor, I think we can do even better. Ill work harder.

char_358_lisa_CN_030.voiceText: Doctor, did I do a good job? I didnt hold the others back, right? Really? Thank goodness...

char_358_lisa_CN_031.voiceText: Doctor, are you okay? Is there anyone whos injured? I, Ill go take care of them!

char_358_lisa_CN_032.voiceText: Sorry, its my fault I didnt work hard enough...

char_358_lisa_CN_033.voiceText: Ive lived here for a long time, so I wont get lost.

char_358_lisa_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor? Oh, would you like some mini cakes? I was planning to take these to everyone in the Medical Department, but you also work very hard... so please help yourself!

char_328_cammou_CN_001.voiceText: Dont you just need me to push some papers around? I do this stuff all the time, piece o cake.

char_328_cammou_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor, hurry up and check out my new video. Youre gonna love it.

char_328_cammou_CN_003.voiceText: Yeah, thats the icon. Mind clicking on it for me? And if possible, can you click that icon next to it? Hehe, thanks a bunch.

char_328_cammou_CN_004.voiceText: Raw footage! Ideas! Plotlines! I cant think up any content! Im gonna lose subs......

char_328_cammou_CN_005.voiceText: Im just an amateur explorer. I only plan to take a few shots and then come right back, so I wont be gone for long. Besides, how could being outdoors be as cozy as chilling in my room?

char_328_cammou_CN_006.voiceText: The folks in the Medical Department mustve put some weird ideas in your head again. Look, I admit, I get weird impulses every now and then, but I promise, Ill never cause you any trouble.

char_328_cammou_CN_007.voiceText: My unique skill is video editing. Did you wanna do a Rhodes Island promo, Doctor? Got a plan for me? All righty, lets take a look. Hmm... Rhodes Island precautions, balanced diet videos, fire safety videos... What the hell are these?!

char_328_cammou_CN_008.voiceText: My instincts are telling me, theres a terrible Feline approaching, Doctor. Dont let your guard down. The moment youre distracted, theyll jump out of a dark corner and smack you to the ground in a single swipe of the paw. Eh? They wont?

char_328_cammou_CN_009.voiceText: The joy of living together with everyone, and the thrill of finding new things to film go hand in hand! It is for that reason I decided to become an operator, so I can share my happiness with you.

char_328_cammou_CN_010.voiceText: Time to quietly sneak in a photo op. Mm, just one.

char_328_cammou_CN_011.voiceText: Sup everyone, this is the Click Channel! Eh? Im not allowed to take footage of the Doctors office? Fine...

char_328_cammou_CN_012.voiceText: Let me do the filming next time.

char_328_cammou_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion? Sweet! Lets take a group photo to celebrate the occasion, Doctor!

char_328_cammou_CN_014.voiceText: Relax, Doctor. This happens every time I get excited, but theres nothing to be afraid of.

char_328_cammou_CN_019.voiceText: Doctor, youd better not forget anything~

char_328_cammou_CN_020.voiceText: Lets see what interesting things can be filmed this time~

char_328_cammou_CN_029.voiceText: That was a sweet clip I just got! Make sure to come by and watch it after you return to the ship.

char_328_cammou_CN_030.voiceText: Wonderful! We can just use this as a real-time combat record!

char_328_cammou_CN_031.voiceText: I was too caught up with filming that someone slipped through.

char_328_cammou_CN_033.voiceText: My video studios about to open!

char_328_cammou_CN_036.voiceText: Hey Doctor, lemme show you something good!

char_344_beewax_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, youll be working hard today? Then, Ill stay with you. If you slack off, then Ill use this stick... Like this... and give you a smack on the head. Bonk, bonk.

char_344_beewax_CN_002.voiceText: Beeswax, Beeswax, Beeswax... Mm, okay. I should get used to it after reading it a few more times. Oh, Doctor, do you need something? Im just trying to get used to hearing my code name... so I dont overreact and get made fun of when others call me.

char_344_beewax_CN_003.voiceText: This bug... Mister Midnight seemed very scared of it and jumped up into the air as soon as he saw it, so I helped him catch it. But, where should we put it now... Um, Doctor, why are you backing away?

char_344_beewax_CN_004.voiceText: My clothes are a bit big, so I feel at ease when drape over my body. I like that sensation. But, sometimes, Ill accidentally step on them Uu, uwah, ahh...! ...Fweh, I tripped again... Ow...

char_344_beewax_CN_005.voiceText: The new piece the Folk Song Association put out this month is my new favorite song. Oh, youve never heard of them before, Doctor? The full name is the Folk Song and Originium Arts Research Association... Still havent heard about it? What about the Electronic Arts Alliance? How about the Rap and Folk Joint Vantage? Havent heard of any of them?

char_344_beewax_CN_006.voiceText: The mark on my head? Ah... this is a ceremonial seal passed down from generation to generation in my tribe, and it is a symbol of our Golden Gods blessings towards our tribe and our peoples. The faceless gods will protect us, no matter where we go, whether or not we remember them......

char_344_beewax_CN_007.voiceText: Leaving the tribe and traveling to other city-states and countries is a trial of passage that all the members of our tribe must go through. Only by successfully passing it can one become a full-fledged adult like my sister. Um, Doctor, you dont think Ill run into any problems, right?

char_344_beewax_CN_008.voiceText: Hehe, my horns are big and pretty, right? There arent many people in the tribe whose horns can compare to mine! The secret to maintaining them is to apply essential oils once a day, gently massage them with a soft brush W-wait, doctor, I havent finished todays maintenance yet, you cant just touch them like that!

char_344_beewax_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, please come here. Mm, okay, close your eyes, and let me touch your forehead. The scorching sun, the raging storm, and waves of golden sand washing across the desert. The gods set foot upon the land where we were nurtured, and bestowed our tribe with their blessings. Now, I will share this blessing with you, Doctor.

char_344_beewax_CN_010.voiceText: Zz... zzz... Sister... you dummy... zzz... mm... H-huh, Doctor? I feel asleep...? Sleeptalking? Did I say something?

char_344_beewax_CN_011.voiceText: Hmm... Wah, excuse me, I let my mind wander. Hello, Doctor, I am, my code name is... Umm... Ah, I remember! Its Beeswax. Do you like it? My tribe helped decide it for me.

char_344_beewax_CN_012.voiceText: Hm...? I have to watch all of this?

char_344_beewax_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion? Mm... I dont quite understand.

char_344_beewax_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor, perhaps the path that lies ahead for Rhodes Island is destined to be long and difficult, but please remember, the gods decrees and my blessings... will always be with you.

char_344_beewax_CN_017.voiceText: Where are we going this time?

char_344_beewax_CN_018.voiceText: Im the leader...? Even though Im not sure how you select your team leaders, Ill try my best.

char_344_beewax_CN_020.voiceText: Someones over there. Everyone, please be careful.

char_344_beewax_CN_023.voiceText: Over here? Leave it to me.

char_344_beewax_CN_024.voiceText: The land beneath my feet is the domain of the gods.

char_344_beewax_CN_028.voiceText: This is the blessing of the gods.

char_344_beewax_CN_029.voiceText: May they also receive the blessing of the gods......

char_344_beewax_CN_030.voiceText: Phew... Its over. Doctor, was I able to be of use?

char_344_beewax_CN_031.voiceText: Ooh, they got away! Mm... but I guess thats fine?

char_344_beewax_CN_032.voiceText: We cant do this anymore, Doctor. Ill hold the enemies back, so please escape!

char_344_beewax_CN_033.voiceText: What a beautiful room... Itd be troublesome if I accidentally spilled sand over it, right?

char_344_beewax_CN_034.voiceText: W-woah... I stepped on my clothes again...

char_344_beewax_CN_036.voiceText: Ah, Doctor, please look at this! I caught another bug~!

char_336_folivo_CN_001.voiceText: Please give any tasks that require doing directly to Lens.

char_336_folivo_CN_002.voiceText: Miss Scene is the simultaneous champion of the Nature and Still-Life categories in major photography competitions. If anyone is willing to wait, the probability of winning the Portrait category will also increase significantly. Doctor, do you want to be a model for Miss Scene?"

char_336_folivo_CN_003.voiceText: Detecting that the Doctors patience is fading. Commencing conciliation sequence  there is only less than half an hour left before Miss Scene completes the shooting. Please hold on a bit longer.

char_336_folivo_CN_004.voiceText: The Zalak next door is looking for Miss Scene again. Though she hasnt laughed yet, I can tell shes very happy.

char_336_folivo_CN_005.voiceText: "Truthfully, Miss Scene originally wanted to work as a full-time photographer for a giant photographic equipment company in Columbia, but she ended up as an operator here anyway. According to Lens, it may be because the other party asked her to take pictures that she didnt want to. Indeed, Miss Scene is very picky."

char_336_folivo_CN_006.voiceText: W h e n  y o u  s e e  s o m e t h i n g  y o u  l i k e ,   y o u  h a v e  t o  t a k e  a  p h o t o .

char_336_folivo_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, are you trying to get Miss Scene to laugh again? In actuality, she is already laughing, but if you want to see it, youll have to wait, and wait, and wait... and continue waiting until the curvature of her mouth becomes perfect. This process will take time  I cant tell you in exactly how many minutes, but it all depends on how the lass is feeling today.

char_336_folivo_CN_008.voiceText: Lens has long been waiting for someone who can understand Miss Scene, but now there are many people in Rhodes Island who are willing to interact with her. This makes Lens very happy, and I wish that one day Miss Scene can find someone who can replace me.

char_336_folivo_CN_009.voiceText: T h i s  c a m e r a.  F o r  y o u . T h a n k y o u .  D o c t o r .

char_336_folivo_CN_011.voiceText: Photographer, Scene, and Robotic Photography Assistant, Lens. We are pleased to make your acquaintance. H e l l o .

char_336_folivo_CN_012.voiceText: Please repeat it again. Repeat. Please repeat it again.

char_336_folivo_CN_013.voiceText: Accessory upgrade complete. Miss Scene thanks you.

char_336_folivo_CN_014.voiceText: I s  t h e r e  s c e n e r y  y o u  w a n t  t o  s e e ?

char_336_folivo_CN_021.voiceText: Lens is here to work for you.

char_336_folivo_CN_029.voiceText: C o n g r a t s .

char_336_folivo_CN_030.voiceText: Mission complete! Miss Scene is currently being transported back to base.

char_336_folivo_CN_031.voiceText: The way back to the base wont be smooth.

char_336_folivo_CN_032.voiceText: Please evacuate from the area! Please evacuate from the area!

char_336_folivo_CN_033.voiceText: Please order a hammock for Miss Scene. Thank you for your cooperation.

char_336_folivo_CN_036.voiceText: W a n t  a  p h o t o ?

char_336_folivo_CN_042.voiceText: H e l l o . Hello! Hello!

char_294_ayer_CN_001.voiceText: Before you leave, I am responsible for protecting you.

char_294_ayer_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor, Im looking for a way to quickly increase the charge my body can carry. Look for an operator who uses electricity? That makes sense, Ill try it.

char_294_ayer_CN_003.voiceText: Go to Leonhardt if you need ore identified. Im no good at this.

char_294_ayer_CN_004.voiceText: The boss lady of Rhine Lab frowned when she saw me, as if I was some kind of pest. What a pain. When did I ever do anything to her?

char_294_ayer_CN_005.voiceText: My ears are standing up? Dont worry, *bzzt*, its just the static, and it actually feels pretty good. Itll, *bzzt*, come down on its own after a while.

char_294_ayer_CN_006.voiceText: It took me two years of scrouging and going into debt to buy this baby. If not for its value, the Cautus profiteers on the black market wouldve thrown me away onto some mining ship. The fact that I can have a comfortable life today is all due to this little electricity-leaking guy.

char_294_ayer_CN_007.voiceText: Oh, there you are. How about a fresh, chilled piece of salted edamame? Dont want it? Youve gotta learn to appreciate this kind of food. Here, eat it.

char_294_ayer_CN_008.voiceText: Leonhardts too noisy and causes too much trouble. I prefer hanging out with you. What? He got surrounded by the Medical Department staff for pulling too many pranks on them? He just doesnt know whats pushing it too far, and I dont think hes ever going to learn. Tsk, Im going to take a look. Doctor, want to come with me if youre free?

char_294_ayer_CN_009.voiceText: I protect Wright because weve been together ever since we were little. Something happens to him, I pay it back, and vice versa. But as for us, we havent had such a long and stable relationship. Dont think you can get close to me just because you helped bandage my wounds, got it? ...I said the same thing last time? Tsk, damn it.

char_294_ayer_CN_010.voiceText: Huh?! Oh... its you. Its nothing, Im just lying here to recuperate. If you want to rest as well, Ill make space for you.

char_294_ayer_CN_011.voiceText: Catastrophe Messenger bodyguard, Ayerscarpe. Pleased to meet you.

char_294_ayer_CN_013.voiceText: Havent I been getting overpaid recently? A promotion? Oh, I see. Thank you.

char_294_ayer_CN_014.voiceText: Being a bodyguard is not about defense, but rather control. Control the space around the target and eliminate all threats. Shall I prove it to you?

char_294_ayer_CN_018.voiceText: Begin the operation at your own pace.

char_294_ayer_CN_019.voiceText: No abnormal changes detected. The squad can begin moving.

char_294_ayer_CN_027.voiceText: The best defense is a good offense.

char_294_ayer_CN_028.voiceText: There is no winning or losing. Only life or death.

char_294_ayer_CN_029.voiceText: Good job controlling the entire situation. Hmph. Congratulations.

char_294_ayer_CN_030.voiceText: We made good time. We should get going.

char_294_ayer_CN_031.voiceText: Im willing to believe that letting that person through was part of your plans.

char_294_ayer_CN_032.voiceText: Dont worry about my injuries. Just make sure you get back safely.

char_294_ayer_CN_033.voiceText: Ill leave the arrangements to you. I have no demands.

char_294_ayer_CN_036.voiceText: You look troubled. Whats on your mind?

char_349_chiave_CN_001.voiceText: Yo, Doctor, got anything fun for me?

char_349_chiave_CN_002.voiceText: Tsk, I need to think of some way to make all the bell peppers disappear from the cafeteria forever.

char_349_chiave_CN_003.voiceText: Theres this Yen saying that goes something like, Live life in the present. Heh, dont you think that saying is really well-suited for me? The future? Eh, Ill let Aosta chew on that kind of stuff.

char_349_chiave_CN_004.voiceText: Hey Doctor, dont just sit there all the time. Why dont we have some fun, like remodeling this whole office?

char_349_chiave_CN_005.voiceText: Aosta once said that Im not gonna live long like this. At the time I told him, whats the point of living for a long time if I cant do what I want?

char_349_chiave_CN_006.voiceText: Fight for what you want, snatch up what you like. Theres no such thing as giving up in my vocabulary!

char_349_chiave_CN_007.voiceText: I think up what to do, Aosta thinks up how to do it, and Brocas responsible for making sure we get it done together. Thats how weve always done things, and its how we ended up here.

char_349_chiave_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, what are you doing all frowny-faced over there? If theres anything weighing down on you, just lemme hear it. Im good at that kind of stuff.

char_349_chiave_CN_009.voiceText: I told you, Doctor, if you decide that becoming the head of Rhodes Island aint for you, how about you come work with us? I normally dont answer to anyone, but in your case, Ill make an exception.

char_349_chiave_CN_010.voiceText: Yo, Doctor... How the heck did you fall asleep? Whatever, guess Ill tell you later.

char_349_chiave_CN_011.voiceText: Yo, are you the Doctor? Hello, and well met. The names Chiave. Im your underling from now on!

char_349_chiave_CN_012.voiceText: Tsk, tsk. Hey Aosta, get over here. Im gonna become this strong one day!

char_349_chiave_CN_014.voiceText: Incredible. There are just too many amazing people here at Rhodes Island. How am I supposed to just stay in my seat? Ive gotta get stronger and stronger!

char_349_chiave_CN_018.voiceText: Listen up, everyone, I have a plan!

char_349_chiave_CN_019.voiceText: Haha, lets go make some noise!

char_349_chiave_CN_020.voiceText: Just gotta knock em all down, right?

char_349_chiave_CN_021.voiceText: Its still not my turn yet?

char_349_chiave_CN_027.voiceText: Fine, fine. Youve all done a great job.

char_349_chiave_CN_029.voiceText: Hah, now this kind of task is the fun stuff!

char_349_chiave_CN_030.voiceText: Tsk, tsk. Wheres the challenge in that, Doctor?

char_349_chiave_CN_031.voiceText: Huh? I left a few? Never even saw em.

char_349_chiave_CN_036.voiceText: Yo, Doctor, you seem to be in a pretty good mood.

char_345_folnic_CN_001.voiceText: Tabletop, 60 points. Floor, 63 points. Air quality...... 56 points. Theres room for improvement, Doctor.
