char_345_folnic_CN_002.voiceText: Have you experienced any bodily discomfort recently? Umm, dry skin, err, um, stiff shoulders, dry eyeballs, hair loss, fatigue? ...Very good, just an old problem then, nothing serious. As long as you start exercising, these problems should go away in no time.

char_345_folnic_CN_003.voiceText: Life in the Medical Department is just daily meetings, visits around the Island, learning the operators physical conditions, and developing new drugs. Never anything fresh and exciting.

char_345_folnic_CN_004.voiceText: Mother, no matter where you are, please watch over me.

char_345_folnic_CN_005.voiceText: Thanks for always taking care of us medics. I feel so much less anxiety while working, and am very happy. Of course, there are troublesome things to deal with as well, for example, when Blaze comes back, her body is always covered in blood. Does she know how hard it is to clean up those bodily fluids?

char_345_folnic_CN_006.voiceText: How many times have I told you, dont stay up late, and dont overeat! You just wont listen, right? How are you going to take care of other peoples health then? You might as well spend the rest of your life in that chair then!! ......Im sorry, I need to go calm down first.

char_345_folnic_CN_007.voiceText: I never quite know what Dr. Kal'tsit is thinking. Has she always been that... unique? I hope I can catch up to her one day, even if its in just one area.

char_345_folnic_CN_008.voiceText: As long as the wicked can be punished, whats a little bit of criticism? I dont mind spilling these poisons on my enemies. They deserve it.

char_345_folnic_CN_009.voiceText: The word Ursus only gives me pain. I dont want to hear it, not again for the rest of my life. But it is a giant, and its voice is deafening. And Im the only its going to drive mad.

char_345_folnic_CN_010.voiceText: You also know that your previous environmental cleanliness evaluation scores werent very high, right? If you dont turn things around, Doctor, youll be on the business end of the Rhodes Island sanitation crane. Phew, Ill help you take care of these for now, so make sure you clean up the rest in your free time.

char_345_folnic_CN_011.voiceText: I am Folinic from the Medical Department, and I am now participating in field medic missions. Meanwhile, per Dr. Kal'tsits request, I will also help you manage your health. I look forward to working with you.

char_345_folnic_CN_012.voiceText: It seems that the volume of drug input was insufficient last time, and it should be able to achieve its intended effect next time at triple the dosage.

char_345_folnic_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you for your acknowledgment. I am simply doing what I should.

char_345_folnic_CN_014.voiceText: One day, I will become as capable a physician as Dr. Kal'tsit. Just you wait and see.

char_345_folnic_CN_017.voiceText: I will do my best to protect everyones life.

char_345_folnic_CN_018.voiceText: The whole squad has been covered by medical support. The rest is up to you, Doctor.

char_345_folnic_CN_019.voiceText: No problem, I can handle some psychological burden.

char_345_folnic_CN_020.voiceText: Enemy engaged. Preparing for counterattack and treatment.

char_345_folnic_CN_024.voiceText: Permission to attack has been granted.

char_345_folnic_CN_026.voiceText: Dont worry, the effects will kick in soon.

char_345_folnic_CN_029.voiceText: I was able to be of some help, right?

char_345_folnic_CN_030.voiceText: Saving medical supplies is a good thing, but theres no need for that on the battlefield, is there?

char_345_folnic_CN_031.voiceText: Luckily, its just a scratch. Just apply a bandage after cleansing the wound.

char_345_folnic_CN_032.voiceText: Transfer the wounded! Get ready for emergency operation! Prepare for intraosseous infusion!

char_345_folnic_CN_033.voiceText: Inspection complete. This area is habitable.

char_345_folnic_CN_036.voiceText: Sometimes the things I say to you can be a bit... excessive, but you should also recognize that you have your shortcomings, all right?

char_293_thorns_CN_001.voiceText: Before you start working, take some of this. Good. Now, for the duration of this drug, you wont be slacking off, right?

char_293_thorns_CN_002.voiceText: Separation and analysis of the extract are almost complete, next step is purification. Actual effect needs further testing... Huh? Why are you staring at my hair, Doctor? My hair...is a total mess? Dont worry about it. Wouldnt be the first time my experiment has failed, or the second.

char_293_thorns_CN_003.voiceText: The drugs I carry on me? Theyre not fatal, but itd be best not to touch them.

char_293_thorns_CN_004.voiceText: Always keep your mind running. Giving up on thought is tantamount on handing your keys to your enemies. Ive been taught this many times,and always think back to it.

char_293_thorns_CN_005.voiceText: My people originally had a completely different appearance. Our skin was as hard as a carapace, and our hair was as smooth as flowing water. However, the scorching sun and dry air have turned us into what we are today. You believed that? Sorry, I was just speaking gibberish just now.

char_293_thorns_CN_006.voiceText: If you are not a follower of the Laterano religion, it is best not to go to Iberia. Their so-called purest faith is rooted in that land, and the people there are so pious that even the Laterano people are ashamed of it. As for me? None of that concerns me in the slightest.

char_293_thorns_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, have you heard anything about the past history of the Iberian Correctional Army? If youve heard even anything remotely relevant, you should know that the inhabitants of that chunk of land are far crazier than their cold, plain gray buildings suggest.

char_293_thorns_CN_008.voiceText: The angle of attack, the vector of evasion, the posture of defense. Every action is calculated, and there are no wasteful movements. This is what they call the Destreza. Dont you think this is similar to your commanding style, Doctor?

char_293_thorns_CN_009.voiceText: I need to unwind a bit more when Im resting? Not thinking about anything and just bask in the sun or let my hair blow in the wind? ...Well, it might be nice to give it a try every now and then. Come up, over here. The breeze up here reminds me of my hometown...

char_293_thorns_CN_010.voiceText: Zzz... zzz... Huh? ...What happened? Did I fall asleep too?

char_293_thorns_CN_011.voiceText: So youre the Doctor? Ill give a brief introduction then. Code name, Thorns. Starting today, Ill be taking my post Huh? One trouser leg is rolled up? ...Dont worry about it, this happens a lot.

char_293_thorns_CN_012.voiceText: Hmm... This information does have some merit.

char_293_thorns_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? You should decide on things like that. Can I go now?

char_293_thorns_CN_014.voiceText: Quickly and efficiently seal the opponents ability to act, and attain victory at the lowest cost  I think I fully understand your orders. In that case, Ill use this paralytic neurotoxin in tandem with my attacks. I take it that you have no issue with this?

char_293_thorns_CN_017.voiceText: Let me see how Rhodes Island fights.

char_293_thorns_CN_018.voiceText: Team leader? Itd be best not to have any expectations. Im not very good at leading.

char_293_thorns_CN_019.voiceText: Lets make this quick. My time is valuable.

char_293_thorns_CN_024.voiceText: Lets just incapacitate them and move on.

char_293_thorns_CN_025.voiceText: Stop moving around. Itll spare all of us the effort.

char_293_thorns_CN_026.voiceText: Your attacks are all within my calculations.

char_293_thorns_CN_028.voiceText: Watch carefully, this is the Destreza of Iberia!

char_293_thorns_CN_029.voiceText: A pristine outcome. Was this also a part of your calculations?

char_293_thorns_CN_030.voiceText: Mission complete. Very precise and efficient command, Doctor.

char_293_thorns_CN_031.voiceText: There was an omission in your command, and my improper execution amplified this omission. We should both reflect upon this after we return.

char_293_thorns_CN_032.voiceText: Considering the losses of our squad, there is no better option than to retreat immediately.

char_293_thorns_CN_033.voiceText: How are the protective measures here?

char_293_thorns_CN_034.voiceText: Shoot, the potions going to spill.

char_293_thorns_CN_036.voiceText: My hair? Gah... I just combed it, whys it messed up again?

char_293_thorns_CN_042.voiceText: You seem tired. Should I help wake you up, Doctor?

char_218_cuttle_CN_001.voiceText: I hope youre not a pain to deal with like Monica, Doctor.

char_218_cuttle_CN_002.voiceText: Monica has a strange taste in just about everything. For example, when selecting her code name, her alternatives were all weird things like Wiseman or Baker. At least Incandescence is somewhat normal-sounding.

char_218_cuttle_CN_003.voiceText: That Skadi and Spectre, those friends from the same race, when I see those two, its almost as if... I dont know exactly how to describe it, but its kind of like that love at first sight from those fairy tales? No way, huh. If that was the case, maybe I should get dressed up...

char_218_cuttle_CN_004.voiceText: To be honest, I wasnt really interested in coming to Rhodes Island at first. After all, Monica was the one you hired, and Im just her bodyguard. But after she left, I ended up unemployed and finding new work is a pain in the ass, so I decided to take my chances.

char_218_cuttle_CN_005.voiceText: Monica and I lived together when we were in Iberia. It was a real hassle taking care of someone like that with no semblance of regularity in her life. But thats just how things are. I dont get along with my family, and I have nowhere else to go. So she just took me in.

char_218_cuttle_CN_006.voiceText: Because of the way my weapon looks, I often got visits from the Tribunal. They disassembled it, saw its structure, and then chewed me out. Though I know it gives them the wrong idea, but thats not really my problem. They get used to it after a while, as long as I dont go around scaring people with it. Heheh.

char_218_cuttle_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, Rhodes Island doesnt have any restrictions on their operators making friends, right? ...No, um, I just wanted to make friends with those Laterano folks. Ive always loved Lateranos guns ever since I was little, so I tried to emulate one when I made this gun.

char_218_cuttle_CN_008.voiceText: Speaking of which, the old hag once told me that I got myself involved in something when I was little, though I was too young to remember anything at that time. She also doesnt want to tell me anything. In any case, my lifes pretty normal now, so it must not have been a huge deal.

char_218_cuttle_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, you really amaze me at times. Just dealing with Monica already takes everything out of me, and yet you have to take care of so many operators... In any case, let me know if you ever have any difficulties. I have some experience looking after people.

char_218_cuttle_CN_010.voiceText: Your work-rest balance is all out of whack, just like Monica. *sigh*...Blanket, blanket...

char_218_cuttle_CN_011.voiceText: I used to be Monicas... Err, I guess I should call her Incandescence now... Anyway, I used to be her bodyguard. She finally found herself a proper job now, so Im free to do other stuff. Anyway, pleased to meet you.

char_218_cuttle_CN_012.voiceText: So this is how the pros do things...

char_218_cuttle_CN_013.voiceText: Before I came here, I thought being a security guard at a pharmaceutical company would be pretty chill. If I didn't make the cut, I could've been doing janitorial work or something. Not going to lie, Im starting to regret that a bit now.

char_218_cuttle_CN_014.voiceText: To be honest, I never thought Id be able to achieve something like this... I never really gave it much thought before, but the feeling of getting stronger isnt half bad. Thanks, Doctor.

char_218_cuttle_CN_017.voiceText: Time for the mission? Got it.

char_218_cuttle_CN_018.voiceText: Im leading? Mm... Ill try my best.

char_218_cuttle_CN_019.voiceText: Hopefully we dont run into any trouble.

char_218_cuttle_CN_022.voiceText: *sigh* Id like to listen to some music.

char_218_cuttle_CN_023.voiceText: The enemy doesnt seem to have noticed yet.

char_218_cuttle_CN_028.voiceText: Theres a lot of em. What a pain.

char_218_cuttle_CN_029.voiceText: Doctor, want some candy? You should relax a bit. Im pretty tired too.

char_218_cuttle_CN_030.voiceText: Ill double-check to see if we missed anything.

char_218_cuttle_CN_031.voiceText: Good enough? All right. I dont want to deal with that annoying stuff either.

char_218_cuttle_CN_032.voiceText: Lets go, Doctor. Ive secured the retreat route.

char_218_cuttle_CN_033.voiceText: Guess Ill take a look around first.

char_218_cuttle_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, is there anything I can help with?

char_272_strong_CN_002.voiceText: Here you go, Boss. And this. You mentioned it before... Everyone says I have a good memory, but I dont know.

char_272_strong_CN_003.voiceText: When Im off, I practice cooking... Not just seafood. What do you like to eat, Boss?

char_272_strong_CN_004.voiceText: ...Boss, is it usually on me to find something to talk about?

char_272_strong_CN_005.voiceText: Boss, if you ever want to see a Lungmen night market, I can take you. Its fun, but not exactly safe.

char_272_strong_CN_006.voiceText: Boss Lady Kal'tsit gave me permission to use Rhodes Islands special channels to get some new stuff. Any requests, Boss?

char_272_strong_CN_007.voiceText: I had Officer Hoshiguma on me for a while, for a couple of reasons... But I know she was just looking out for me, same as the neighborhood aunties and uncles.

char_272_strong_CN_008.voiceText: Ive been told that with my looks, plus my knife skills, I was born to be evil. I didnt like that, but what could I do...? After coming to Rhodes Island, I realized I should just do what makes me happy.

char_272_strong_CN_009.voiceText: Boss, do you think theres any way to put my memory to good use...? I never thought about it before, but it would be nice if I could help.

char_272_strong_CN_010.voiceText: Bo... Oh, youre asleep. Ill just keep reading.

char_272_strong_CN_011.voiceText: Hey, Boss. Im Jaye. Officer Hoshiguma said Id be better off working here, so here I am. I know seafood, I can cook, and Im pretty good with a knife. I think I can help.

char_272_strong_CN_012.voiceText: Huh, so cooking and warfare are pretty much the same.

char_272_strong_CN_013.voiceText: Boss, does this mean I can spread out a bit more?

char_272_strong_CN_014.voiceText: Boss, I figured it out. If you just treat the enemy as food, this battle thing is a lot easier.

char_272_strong_CN_017.voiceText: Oh, I forgot to close up...

char_272_strong_CN_018.voiceText: I know how to lead a fishing crew.

char_272_strong_CN_029.voiceText: Boss, did we just do something special?

char_272_strong_CN_031.voiceText: Boss, should we go after them?

char_272_strong_CN_032.voiceText: Boss, I think we should probably run.

char_272_strong_CN_033.voiceText: I don't know if there's a suitable place to set up my stall

char_272_strong_CN_036.voiceText: Boss, I dont know if you have any vices...

char_272_strong_CN_042.voiceText: Hey Boss, the weathers not bad today.

char_366_acdrop_CN_001.voiceText: No problem, Doctor. Ive got your back.

char_366_acdrop_CN_002.voiceText: How do Iaimwhile Im skating? Its real simple, want me to show you? Here, put your hand on mine.

char_366_acdrop_CN_003.voiceText: Way back when, I, like a lot of my friends, took pride in being different. But after I became infected, I realized that alone wasnt cool. Life isnt something that you should let a little bit of Originium dust control, you gotta take charge yourself.

char_366_acdrop_CN_004.voiceText: An old cop taught me how to shoot with a crossbow, and his daughter taught me how to skate. As for how to put the two together... thats called being self-taught.

char_366_acdrop_CN_005.voiceText: Dont get me wrong, skateboarding is just one of my hobbies... and the first way I had to really find myself. The real exciting part comes after that though, wanna hear?

char_366_acdrop_CN_006.voiceText: Whyd I want to become a combat operator...? Doctor, what do you think is most important for us giggling and laughing street gangsters? Of course its freedom. Im willing to fight for freedom, so thats why Im fighting for Rhodes Island.

char_366_acdrop_CN_007.voiceText: I have a lot of regrets about becoming Infected, such as the graffiti mural at the park that I left half-finished. Also, I cant eat any more of that old cops secret-formula onion rings, huh? Thats about it.

char_366_acdrop_CN_008.voiceText: I came to Rhodes Island with the mindset of getting my illness treated. Thought itd be some stuffy place that reeked of disinfectant where everyone would be confined to their rooms... But man, I was surprised to find out, even though tagging isn't allowed inside the ship and all, that Ethan guy... Actually, nevermind.

char_366_acdrop_CN_009.voiceText: I found a way to express myself through donut hamburger combo meals, skateboarding, and hip-hop competitions. How bout you, Doctor? If you get burnt out, you should come kick it with me and Vigna. Well just... hang out. Hanging out is in our DNA. Gotta respect it.

char_366_acdrop_CN_010.voiceText: If youre tired, just go rest. Ill be here.

char_366_acdrop_CN_011.voiceText: Aciddrop, Operator. This skateboard here is a piece of registered equipment, yeah. If you have any problems, just give me a holler.

char_366_acdrop_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion, huh? Thanks. The last time this happened was when I just won the CrabCup, huh?

char_366_acdrop_CN_014.voiceText: That old geezer originally taught me to use a crossbow so I could protect myself from the chaos on the streets. Who wouldve thought that one day, Id be using it to protect the freedom of the Infected?

char_366_acdrop_CN_018.voiceText: Teamworks an important part of scoring as well.

char_366_acdrop_CN_022.voiceText: Cmon, how do I deal with these guys?

char_366_acdrop_CN_023.voiceText: Now this is some exciting stuff.

char_366_acdrop_CN_026.voiceText: Time to show off a bit.

char_366_acdrop_CN_029.voiceText: Good work out there, Doctor... Oh, can you come with me to get a couple screws switched out after we get back?

char_366_acdrop_CN_030.voiceText: The moment when you overcome a challenge is always the best feeling, right?

char_366_acdrop_CN_031.voiceText: Should we chase after em? If you ask me, I can still catch up.

char_366_acdrop_CN_032.voiceText: Ugh... Cant believe I messed up such an amateur move...

char_366_acdrop_CN_033.voiceText: This bit of wall here looks pretty suitable... Uh, I didnt say anything.

char_366_acdrop_CN_036.voiceText: Wanna head down to the canteen together? If I dont make any mistakes on this trip, promise to treat me to some juice.

char_411_tomimi_CN_001.voiceText: Gavial doesnt know how to do this kind of work, and nobody in the tribe thought to do this stuff either. So, thats why Ill do a little bit when I have the time.

char_411_tomimi_CN_002.voiceText: If theres no trainee nurse at the Medical Department, I can give it a try. I have some basic nursing knowledge.

char_411_tomimi_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor, the pen seems to be out of ink. Ah, wait, please dont throw that out! If its not too much to ask, um, could I hang onto that?

char_411_tomimi_CN_004.voiceText: Rhodes Island cant dig underground? Are there no treasures underground? All the precious things are locked inside the rooms? Thats too bad...

char_411_tomimi_CN_005.voiceText: My tail got longer again. If it keeps getting longer like this, other people will really start to reject me. Ugh... so upsetting.

char_411_tomimi_CN_006.voiceText: A big tail is something youre born with. Being strong and cool are things youre born with. Being smart is also something youre born with. Since we cant choose how were born, lets just live life and embrace what makes us unique. Um, of course, if you can help me out every now and then, Doctor... that would be best.

char_411_tomimi_CN_007.voiceText: Its understandable that Gavial would skip work, but why would she skip a meal? Is there something bothering her to the point that its sending her into hiding? No one seems to have noticed yet. Im the only one who can save her! Ah, Doctor, there you are. Can you help me with something?

char_411_tomimi_CN_008.voiceText: Are you sure you want to see? I have a whole lot of stuff in my backpack. All right, I also havent checked through everything in quite some time either. Um, lets take a look: a piece of amber wrapped in a leaf, a loose fang? A black crystal with a speck of blood... and a stack of signatures?! Doctor, thats as far as you can go! Stop right there!

char_411_tomimi_CN_009.voiceText: Someone who steals your gaze, making you not want to close your eyelids until the flames have burned your eyes from their sockets. You know, Gavial is the kind of person who shines just like this. Oh, by the way, I read that previous description in a book and thought it sounded pretty neat, so I memorized it so I could use it myself.

char_411_tomimi_CN_010.voiceText: Heres a dreamcatcher. Ill leave it over here. I hope youll be able to have pure and peaceful dreams.

char_411_tomimi_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, Doctor. Um, Im not here to make trouble. Im, uh, yeah. Here to study. Right, study. Since Gavial is over here, it wouldnt make sense for me to stay back home alone, right?

char_411_tomimi_CN_012.voiceText: I, I think itd be better to directly practice on the battlefield, right?

char_411_tomimi_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you for giving me such a pretty badge, Doctor. Huh? Oh, a promotion badge? Ah, um, uhhh... Am I really qualified to have this?

char_411_tomimi_CN_014.voiceText: Ill be worthy of this flag one day, I swear it.

char_411_tomimi_CN_017.voiceText: Let me try learning some of your techniques. Itd be great if I could pick them up.

char_411_tomimi_CN_018.voiceText: Youre leaving it to me? Really?

char_411_tomimi_CN_019.voiceText: Lets go. Fight. Mm, were going to beat them up.

char_411_tomimi_CN_021.voiceText: You didnt see me, you didnt see me...

char_411_tomimi_CN_024.voiceText: Anyone who needs a good beating, step forward!

char_411_tomimi_CN_026.voiceText: Hold on a bit longer, hold on a bit longer!

char_411_tomimi_CN_029.voiceText: You used to smack me around like that before, Doctor.

char_411_tomimi_CN_031.voiceText: Ugh, my backs sore. Need to take a break.

char_411_tomimi_CN_033.voiceText: Ah, um, you cant throw that away yet. Please give it to me, Ill take care of it myself.

char_411_tomimi_CN_036.voiceText: Want to try Sargons local barbecue? Ill do all the barbecuing, so you can just enjoy the food.

char_415_flint_CN_001.voiceText: Handling files? Alright, then. Teach me how. Right. Sort them first. Like this? Then put them in order. By chronological... uh. Paper got torn... S-sorry. I didnt mean to.

char_415_flint_CN_002.voiceText: Some of the people here. Dont you think theyre a little too tall? ...No, I dont care. Not actually. How tall you are and how strong you are dont relate. I just need to bring every last one of them down.

char_415_flint_CN_003.voiceText: Whats my tribe gonna do now that Im gone? What a dumb question that is. See who has the bigger fists. Pick a new leader that way and just carry on. Thats it.

char_415_flint_CN_004.voiceText: I heard a lot about Gavial. Like how she can crush a rock with her abs. Tear a raging beast apart with one hand. Is she actually that strong? Stronger than Chief Blaze? Warfarin said if I get treatment from Gavial, I can learn firsthand how strong she is... huh? Doctor, why are you stopping me?

char_415_flint_CN_005.voiceText: I came here so I could get stronger, and that hasnt changed. Its not just Chief Blaze and Gavial. Theres a lotta people worthy enough for me to challenge here... what? You think I look happy? Well, thats not wrong. I dont hate it, being here.

char_415_flint_CN_006.voiceText: Everyone in Rhodes Island. Dont they all think too much? You too, Doctor. You have to think about so much every day. You get tired, right. You dont? You have to do it? ...I guess thats true. Theres a lotta stuff only you know how to sort out. No other way. Yeah. Then keep it up. Shout any time if you ever need me.

char_415_flint_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, give me a hand. Up there. The flower basket up there. Help me get it down. What? You cant reach either? This sucks... Okay. What if I lift you up? Why dont we try that?

char_415_flint_CN_008.voiceText: Zumamas going on the same mission as me this time? Dont worry. Im not gonna start hitting her out of nowhere. If we wanna settle a score, weve got all the opportunities we want. Also, I mean, if we start fighting, that makes things hard for you, right? Yeah. I dont really want to do that to you.

char_415_flint_CN_009.voiceText: This flower. Dont you think its pretty? I grew this one myself. Hey, what makes you so surprised? Im not the kind of battle lunatic who only cares about getting stronger. Having a hobby or two is completely normal, right. Huh? You like it too? Then Ill give you this one. Yeah. Not bad. Suits you well.

char_415_flint_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, I picked a flower and... huh? Fell asleep? Heh, youre real laid-back. The flower... Ill just put it on your head. Yeah, that looks pretty good.

char_415_flint_CN_011.voiceText: We meet again, huh. Im the tallest, strongest warrior of my tribe, Flint. I hear youve got a lot of strong people around here? Great. Ill challenge them one by one. Oh, right. Do you know where I can find Chief Blaze?

char_415_flint_CN_012.voiceText: Not bad. This techniques not bad! Doctor, I wanna challenge them! Where can I find where this warrior is?

char_415_flint_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion? Sure, do whatever you want. Anyway, I can keep fighting like I was already, right?

char_415_flint_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor, you. Youve been thinking too much. Any enemies, we can hit them away with our fists! Cmon. Relax a little. You need to loosen up when its time to take a rest. Wanna come over here and lie down with me?

char_415_flint_CN_017.voiceText: Got it. Shout for me when its time to go.

char_415_flint_CN_018.voiceText: No problem. Leave it to me.

char_415_flint_CN_019.voiceText: Were going. Each of you, watch your cover. Dont leave any signs.

char_415_flint_CN_024.voiceText: Wanna come one by one? Or all at once?

char_415_flint_CN_027.voiceText: The look in all your eyes. Screw that.

char_415_flint_CN_029.voiceText: You can find victory even without your fists? Heh. I guess thats your style...

char_415_flint_CN_030.voiceText: Good job. Didnt know it. Youve got something going up there.

char_415_flint_CN_031.voiceText: Tch. If the small fry wanna escape, let em. Theyre not worth chasing.

char_415_flint_CN_032.voiceText: Dont blame yourself. Im just still not strong enough.

char_415_flint_CN_033.voiceText: Hey. Can I hang a sandbag or two in my room?

char_415_flint_CN_036.voiceText: Huh? What are you doing squatting down over here? You want me to pat your head?

char_415_flint_CN_042.voiceText: Lets pull it together. Anything you need me to help with today?

char_416_zumama_CN_001.voiceText: Anything you need help with, Boss? Good.

char_416_zumama_CN_002.voiceText: We arent allowed to sleep on the ground here? Ill put up a tent in the hallway, then... that wont do either? Why not? At my tribe, wed just sleep wherever we were when we got tired.

char_416_zumama_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor, why was my application to room with Lancet-2 rejected? Because shes a robot? Youre mistaken. The two of us are sisters now. Shes my big sister, and Im her little sister.

char_416_zumama_CN_004.voiceText: Doctor, are medics outside always like Gavial? When she gives me my Oripathy checkups, it always feels like shes just trying to beat me up... Thats why we always end up fighting each other as soon as my tolerance runs out.

char_416_zumama_CN_005.voiceText: The Big Priest? Yeah, he didnt come with me, but he did say hed come visit from time to time. Speaking of which, does he even know where Rhodes Island is...?

char_416_zumama_CN_006.voiceText: Before, my dream was to build a gigantic robot like the nomadic cities. Now, my dream is not only to build a gigantic robot like the nomadic cities, but one that can talk too. Master Closure has already promised to teach me the best of the best about machineries.

char_416_zumama_CN_007.voiceText: ...Oh, I get it now. So, just like Great Chieftain, Doctor is a title we use to honor people who are knowledgeable. So that means everyone will start calling me Dr. Zumama once I learn everything I can here, right? Oh, they wont?

char_416_zumama_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, I was hoping you could accompany me back to Sargon when you have time to teach me how to go about all sorts of things there. But you look busy... In that case, may I ask Lancet-2 to accompany me? Otherwise, Master Closure is fine.

char_416_zumama_CN_009.voiceText: People outside are always worried about things that dont matter and fighting over them. Its so strange. You too, Doctor. You always look like youre giving yourself a hard time over everything. Here, take this wrench. Lets build some machines together. Im sure youll enjoy seeing a machine in the works getting bigger and greater bit by bit.

char_416_zumama_CN_010.voiceText: Im starting to get a bit tired myself, watching the Doctor sleeping... *yawn*...

char_416_zumama_CN_011.voiceText: I passed all the exams, so that means I can stay here, right? I want to learn how to build a talking robot like Lancet-2... Oh, codename? My name is Zumama. Cant I use that as my codename?

char_416_zumama_CN_012.voiceText: To think theres someone who could go up against Gavial on an equal footing...

char_416_zumama_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? Is that something like going from a fighter to a warrior? ...In that case, we must celebrate. I think Ill have a barbeque with Lancet-2 on the bridge tonight.

char_416_zumama_CN_014.voiceText: The High Priest told me before its a vast, big world out here. He sounded kind of heartbroken when he said that. I didnt understand why at the time, but Im starting to understand after having spent so much time here. The world being so vast, might not necessarily be a good thing.

char_416_zumama_CN_020.voiceText: I just need to take care of all of them, right?

char_416_zumama_CN_023.voiceText: Itll be even more efficient if someone who can work with me comes along.

char_416_zumama_CN_025.voiceText: You people are no match for Gavial!

char_416_zumama_CN_026.voiceText: Im not all that weak either!

char_416_zumama_CN_027.voiceText: Ill give it my all no matter the prey!

char_416_zumama_CN_030.voiceText: Compared to Gavial, youve still got a ways to go.

char_416_zumama_CN_032.voiceText: Dont worry about it. Ive lost to Gavial too many times myself. Its nothing to be ashamed of.

char_416_zumama_CN_036.voiceText: What do I need to do to become as educated as the Doctor?

char_416_zumama_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, good timing. Theres something I wanted to ask you.

char_271_spikes_CN_001.voiceText: The files are in order. Is that all we have to do today? Why dont we talk about the operation the other day, Professor?

char_271_spikes_CN_002.voiceText: Try not to come too close when I use Arts, okay? Not moving out of the way? Okay, if you insist.

char_271_spikes_CN_003.voiceText: Why do I call you Professor, you ask? Because Im actually learning quite a lot from you. The placement of personnel on the battlefield, how to command, among other things... What more reason do we need?

char_271_spikes_CN_004.voiceText: Here, you can have this. I think its some sort of candy? No need to thank me. I got it from someone else anyway, and I dont really like these things very much.

char_271_spikes_CN_005.voiceText: You dont see Sankta using staves much? The guys who shoot up everything day and night and solve all their problems with violence must have given you a bad impression. Not all Sankta use guns as their weapons. At the very least, I dont like them.

char_271_spikes_CN_006.voiceText: Rather than sharing a single secret, we should exchange our secrets with each other. Thats how you build a strong, equal relationship. So if you want to learn any of my secrets, you better come up with something just as saucy for me, Professor.

char_271_spikes_CN_007.voiceText: There are no Infected in Laterano. Once a Sankta contracts Oripathy, he is immediately exiled. But even if you become Infected, no matter where you are, you still enjoy all kinds of privilege as a Laterano... You just dont get to set foot in your homeland again, thats all.

char_271_spikes_CN_008.voiceText: My parents will left me with quite a bit of trouble, and it was really a hassle to get it taken care of. If it wasnt for that uptight executor making things difficult for me, it all couldve been much easier... Oh, whatever, it still went according to plan.

char_271_spikes_CN_009.voiceText: I want to capture a few people to try out some new Arts in our next operation.  I cant...? Alright, fine. Its a shame, but if thats what you say, Professor, maybe some other time, then.  Eh? Not this time, and not ever? Geez, dont be so uptight.

char_271_spikes_CN_010.voiceText: Are you asleep? People who fall asleep at work get their faces drawn on, you know...? Just kidding, I know youre awake.

char_271_spikes_CN_011.voiceText: Codename Arene, officially joining today, it seems. So you are the Doctor... I hope well get along, Professor {@nickname}.

char_271_spikes_CN_013.voiceText: This doesnt seem all that different than before. Or are you going to teach me some secret strategies you have, Professor?

char_271_spikes_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor, you arent testing me, are you? Alright then, Im just getting in the mood.  Okay, starting right now, whatever that happens is going to be our own little secret.

char_271_spikes_CN_018.voiceText: So actual combat for my next assignment? Okay, let me think about the placement...

char_271_spikes_CN_019.voiceText: As long as we achieve our goals, it doesnt matter if the process of getting there is a little rough, huh?

char_271_spikes_CN_024.voiceText: I can do whatever I want, right?

char_271_spikes_CN_027.voiceText: Tell me. How are you feeling right now?

char_271_spikes_CN_028.voiceText: Thats not a bad scream at all.

char_271_spikes_CN_029.voiceText: That went far better than I expected. I shouldnt have thought so little of you.

char_271_spikes_CN_030.voiceText: That was just as expected. No surprises, even a little boring.

char_271_spikes_CN_031.voiceText: A few of them slipped past. Should I go after them? Strategically speaking, I dont recommend it.

char_271_spikes_CN_032.voiceText: This is quite the bad situation... I shouldnt have to tell you what the appropriate course of action is now, right?

char_271_spikes_CN_033.voiceText: Isnt there a closer room to the Professors?

char_271_spikes_CN_036.voiceText: We have some time to spare. Why dont we review our last mission, Professor?

char_271_spikes_CN_042.voiceText: You look tired. Its okay if you sleep a little longer, Professor.

char_365_aprl_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, anything I can help with?

char_365_aprl_CN_002.voiceText: Ahhh... A hot shower every day is amazing... After I got infected and had to move, it was really hard for me to find a hot shower. And the food here is so clean. Oh, I love Rhodes Island~

char_365_aprl_CN_003.voiceText: April?  April is a song about spring. The lyrics are about the feeling of lying on the grass on a warm spring day, looking up at the sky and thinking about stuff. You wanna hear it? Im sure youll love it~

char_365_aprl_CN_004.voiceText: Hey, wheres my lip gloss...? Oh, I remember. I lent it to Rope. Hm? Oh, because I was gonna teach her to do makeup. Shes got a good foundation, so shell be super cute after some sprucing up.

char_365_aprl_CN_005.voiceText: Back in Rim Billiton, the company promised a pension for the Infected, but you only get scraps in the end, and theres no jobs... Good thing I decided to try Rhodes Island as soon as I saw the ad. You treat me like a human being here.

char_365_aprl_CN_006.voiceText: After I got infected, people started asking me like whats an Infected wearing such bright colors for and whats an Infected listening to music for... I always just tell them: Because I wanna.

char_365_aprl_CN_007.voiceText: Back in Rim Billiton, I was a professional hunter. I had to keep animals away from the city and sometimes escort company people. But after I got Oripathy, I lost my job and had to hunt on my own for a living. It was real rough...

char_365_aprl_CN_008.voiceText: My parents died in a mining accident when I was little, and I grew up on a company pension, so I was always real grateful to the company. I figured getting Oripathy was my own dumb fault... But thats not really what happened, is it, Doctor?

char_365_aprl_CN_009.voiceText: Doing something for the Infected... I never thought about it before. I mean, its hard enough to keep yourself alive. But after coming to Rhodes Island, I decided I wanted to try to do something not just for myself, but for everyone who suffers like me.

char_365_aprl_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, if you wanna nap, I can lend you my earplugs.

char_365_aprl_CN_011.voiceText: Rhodes Island has such great stuff, and they treat you so good... Oh, sorry, Doctor, Im just a little shocked. My codename is April. Yeah, its the name of my favorite song.

char_365_aprl_CN_013.voiceText: Huh? A raise...? Oh, its not that Im disappointed, Im thrilled. Its just been a long, long time since anyone told me I was doing a good job.

char_365_aprl_CN_014.voiceText: Back in Rim Billiton, I liked to sit on the roof and listen to my music while I watched the whole city go by. Now, I can see even more from the bridge of Rhodes Island. There was a silver lining to me getting sick, huh, Doctor?

char_365_aprl_CN_025.voiceText: Lets get some fast music going.

char_365_aprl_CN_026.voiceText: Now this is a good rhythm!

char_365_aprl_CN_027.voiceText: Ive got a lock on you~

char_365_aprl_CN_029.voiceText: Doctor, how would you like to relax with some music?

char_365_aprl_CN_031.voiceText: Doctor, a few got away, should we chase them?

char_365_aprl_CN_033.voiceText: Ive been around Rhodes Island a couple times and I think its really big.

char_365_aprl_CN_036.voiceText: The Doctor should be in the office, right?

char_388_mint_CN_001.voiceText: Can I read any of the books here? I can read all of them? Mm-hm, mm-hm, Ill be careful! I wont mess them up!

char_388_mint_CN_002.voiceText: Ah. Sorry, no. You shouldnt just carelessly touch my book. It might bite your hand. Im actually not joking. Im serious. Look. I even have to tie it shut like this.

char_388_mint_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor, do you know where the library is? I asked someone just now, but they were talking too fast. It was hard to understand.

char_388_mint_CN_004.voiceText: Skyfire, um, Skyfire, wait for me! Uwwhh, please dont walk so fast... I promise I wont run off halfway this time, I promise!

char_388_mint_CN_005.voiceText: I like reading, but I like hanging out with everyone too! It makes me so happy when I can be with the people I like.  Also, dont be fooled. Im really good at sporty stuff! Especially climbing trees. I can climb super high!

char_388_mint_CN_006.voiceText: I got some new inspiration after talking to Miss Eyjafjalla today! Shes very well-researched on environmental geology. Thank goodness my groups research wasnt stopped because of my accident. Heheh! If I get results this time, I can reapply to the Institution to resume my studies.

char_388_mint_CN_007.voiceText: Skyfire is an alumna from my university. Although she skipped a year and graduated soon after I entered, theres times shes looked after me... Oh, thats right! Shes also the one who introduced me to Rhodes Island so I could receive treatment.

char_388_mint_CN_008.voiceText: Um, are you wondering why I always follow you, Doctor? Its because when Im near you, I feel really at ease, so I just unconsciously... Doctor, am I just annoying you  Do you want me to go away?

char_388_mint_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, this is for you. Yep, I found it on the way back with a whole lot of nice-looking stones, but then I realized Id gotten separated from the others  Eh? The ore chunk on your desk from before? I put that there too, yes... Did you like it, Doctor?

char_388_mint_CN_010.voiceText: Nnh... mmmmnnh... there! Ah, Doctor! Sorry! Did I wake you up? A bug landed on your head just now, and for a moment, I, um... did it hurt? I can shush it better!

char_388_mint_CN_011.voiceText: Thank you for helping me move all these books! Just leave them here, please. Um, my codename is Mint. Whats yours? ...Huh? Doctor? Wait, so youre the Doctor Skyfire was telling me about?

char_388_mint_CN_013.voiceText: Are there any rewards for promotion? Can I borrow even more books than before?

char_388_mint_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor, come sit down here. How is it? The sun feels really nice, right? Eheheh. This is my secret base. I love it here more than anywhere. Dont tell anyone else about it, okay?

char_388_mint_CN_017.voiceText: Got it. Are you coming with us, Doctor?

char_388_mint_CN_021.voiceText: Whuh? What is it? Im listening, Im listening!

char_388_mint_CN_024.voiceText: Please dont get in our way!

char_388_mint_CN_028.voiceText: Would you like to see some of my magic?

char_388_mint_CN_029.voiceText: Everything went just like you said it would, Doctor! That was amazing...!

char_388_mint_CN_030.voiceText: Phew... its over. We can finally head back now.

char_388_mint_CN_031.voiceText: It doesnt look like any more are coming for us... This is fine for now, right?

char_388_mint_CN_032.voiceText: We cant, its too dangerous... Doctor, you need to get away!

char_388_mint_CN_033.voiceText: Um, to tell the truth, Id be alright sleeping in the library too.

char_388_mint_CN_036.voiceText: Ah! Doctor, would you like to read with me? Its really comfortable sitting here.

char_388_mint_CN_042.voiceText: So this is where you were, Doctor! Found you.

char_350_surtr_CN_001.voiceText: Youve failed to complete the tasks within your purview, and are now asking me for help?

char_350_surtr_CN_002.voiceText: Dont expect me to instruct others in Originium Arts. I have no interest in wasting time with plebeians.

char_350_surtr_CN_003.voiceText: I'm not here because I have to, but because I want to.

char_350_surtr_CN_004.voiceText: The people I hate most are the ones who ask too many questions. I hope you are not one of them.

char_350_surtr_CN_005.voiceText: It appears that you have gained some understanding of my Arts by now. I do hope you are aware of the danger as well.

char_350_surtr_CN_006.voiceText: Before I realized it, these Arts and this staff had already become my steadfast companions.  I do not remember when I gained such power. Of course, I do not actually care.

char_350_surtr_CN_007.voiceText: I possess all kinds of memories. I dont know from whence did they came, nor do I know which truly belong to me. To discover the source of my memories, I have been traveling back and forth, from country to country, and now I have arrived at Rhodes Island.

char_350_surtr_CN_008.voiceText: There is truly nothing better than an ice-cream to calm me down when I am absorbed in chaotic memories. I always relied on ice-cream, when I was alone.

char_350_surtr_CN_009.voiceText: These memories of Rhodes Island are completely different from those before. They have a sense of realism about them. For the first time, Im able to feel that I am truly myself. All of this is thanks to you, and all of Rhodes Island.  ...What? I am capable of giving thanks where it is deserved, all right?

char_350_surtr_CN_010.voiceText: Tch... what a waste of time.

char_350_surtr_CN_011.voiceText: I am Surtr. Are you the Doctor they mentioned? I will be working at Rhodes Island, starting today. I hope that you will not bore me too much.

char_350_surtr_CN_013.voiceText: Have you started to value me after witnessing my power?

char_350_surtr_CN_014.voiceText: You value not my power, but me myself? Then I shall put in the appropriate level of effort to repay you.

char_350_surtr_CN_020.voiceText: Are they the ones to be eliminated?

char_350_surtr_CN_031.voiceText: Can you not even do such a simple thing?

char_350_surtr_CN_032.voiceText: If can do nothing to help, just retreat! Ill handle this.

char_350_surtr_CN_033.voiceText: An acceptably clean room, I suppose.

char_350_surtr_CN_034.voiceText: I know how to walk on my own.

char_381_bubble_CN_001.voiceText: Lets see what goodies the Doctor hides in this drawer.

char_381_bubble_CN_002.voiceText: Im probably only about as big as one of Papas legs right now, but Im gonna be as big as him and trample over all the bad guys! Graaagh!

char_381_bubble_CN_003.voiceText: Im really, really sorry! I wont run in the hallways ever again!

char_381_bubble_CN_004.voiceText: Fighting is easy. I point my shield one way, and nobody can beat me. Huh? What if they get behind me? Uh oh, why didnt I think of that?

char_381_bubble_CN_005.voiceText: Gavial? Never heard of her. Shes tough? And famous in Sargon? Okay, whatever. Ill see for myself how tough she is.

char_381_bubble_CN_006.voiceText: Oh, youre talking about Gavial? Im Gavials number one fan. See, she even signed my shield for me. Thats her autograph! I think, besides Papa, pretty much nobody could take down Gavial.

char_381_bubble_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, shhh, tell me the truth. Kay says Vulcan can hammer straight through the floor, can she? No? I knew it. That means my Papa is definitely stronger. He could bust down a Rhodes smoke stack with one punch.

char_381_bubble_CN_008.voiceText: Do I really... have to keep writing this...? Fine... I knocked over Lancet-2 today. I wont do it again.

char_381_bubble_CN_009.voiceText: This is my shield. Itll be one of my greaves someday, or maybe a pauldron. Then as long as Im standing behind you, hehe, nobodyll ever bully you.

char_381_bubble_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, wake up! Somebodys here to see you.

char_381_bubble_CN_011.voiceText: Youre the boss of this training camp? And they call you the Doctor? Hrm... But you dont look strong... Whatever. Im Bubble. I may be the weakest in my tribe right now, but youre gonna train me until Im the second strongest.

char_381_bubble_CN_012.voiceText: Hit em! Hit em again! What, whyd they stop. Is it over?

char_381_bubble_CN_013.voiceText: A reward for my training? Great! I cant eat it? Grrr...

char_381_bubble_CN_014.voiceText: I think I got a good chance of beating Kay now! Okay, lemme at her. Doctor, you come watch!

char_381_bubble_CN_018.voiceText: I count down to one and we charge, okay?

char_381_bubble_CN_029.voiceText: Doctor, if youre strong enough, you gotta be warrior like my Papa!

char_381_bubble_CN_030.voiceText: What did I tell you? Im super strong.

char_381_bubble_CN_031.voiceText: Huh? Some of them got away? Did I let them through?

char_381_bubble_CN_032.voiceText: I cant beat them! What do I do?!

char_381_bubble_CN_033.voiceText: I need a way, waaay bigger room. How can anyone live in a little place like this?

char_346_aosta_CN_001.voiceText: If you want me to be your assistant, is it okay if I do some craftwork here?

char_346_aosta_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor, if you like excitement, you should probably hang out in Siracusa for a while. You wont enjoy it so much after that.

char_346_aosta_CN_003.voiceText: Considering his personality, sometimes even I wonder why no ones beaten Chiave to death yet.

char_346_aosta_CN_004.voiceText: Doctor, are you interested in DIY? See, the three of us actually design and make our weapons and outfits ourselves. You could join us sometime, if you want.

char_346_aosta_CN_005.voiceText: I came to realize one thing while I was cleaning up after Chiaves messes: If you want to be really strong, you arent going to get there with just violence.

char_346_aosta_CN_006.voiceText: In Siracusa, most people my age just want to join a family, but there are also a lot of people who want to live an honest life instead. Sometimes, I think those ones are the best of us all.

char_346_aosta_CN_007.voiceText: (Yawn) ...Sorry, Doctor, I didnt get much sleep last night. Rhodes Island is way too safe. Its taking some time to get used to.

char_346_aosta_CN_008.voiceText: Chiave, Broca, and me. The three of us are like brothers, and weve done all kinds of things together. But, sometimes, I really wonder if this really is the life for us.

char_346_aosta_CN_009.voiceText: To tell you the truth, I wanted to be a public servant when I was a kid. Up until my dad made me pick up a weapon for the first time, that is. I dont hate drifting around with the two of them, but I always felt like there was something I was missing, and I know what it is now. I wanted to become someone as strong-willed as you, Doctor.

char_346_aosta_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor... youre asleep? Taking it easy, arent we?

char_346_aosta_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, Doctor. Im Aosta. Its thanks to you that the three of us are still alive. If you dont mind, please let us work here for the time being.

char_346_aosta_CN_012.voiceText: ...Looks like its just luck that the three of us only managed to survive this long.

char_346_aosta_CN_013.voiceText: Doctor, is Rhodes Island really a pharmaceutical company? Ive got the feeling that we might just be able to take over a Siracusan city if everyone here put themselves to it.

char_346_aosta_CN_014.voiceText: I think I might just be able to live the life Ive always wanted at Rhodes Island... Doctor, do I have permission to open a DIY shop here?

char_346_aosta_CN_017.voiceText: I hope this isnt going to be too much of a pain in the back.

char_346_aosta_CN_018.voiceText: Ill give it my best shot.

char_346_aosta_CN_020.voiceText: Guess we dont have a choice. Lets get this taken care of.

char_346_aosta_CN_027.voiceText: Time to put an end to this.

char_346_aosta_CN_029.voiceText: Phew... phew... Doctor, do you enjoy challenging yourself so much?

char_346_aosta_CN_030.voiceText: I got all of them. I just hope theyre worth it.

char_346_aosta_CN_031.voiceText: A few of them got through, but I think well be fine.

char_346_aosta_CN_032.voiceText: Doctor, you go on ahead. Ill clean up the mess here. Its what Im good at.

char_346_aosta_CN_033.voiceText: Ill just sorta walk around, then.

char_265_sophia_CN_001.voiceText: You hear about burdenbeasts who dont even drag themselves to work until theyre whipped. Youre not like that, Doctor. Youre smarter than a beast, arent you?

char_265_sophia_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor. Just to put any scary little misunderstandings to rest, let me say this now. Maria might call me her aunt, but thats only because Im higher in the family. Im not much older than her. Im still young. Im still not married. Clear?

char_265_sophia_CN_003.voiceText: A spat between me and Dobermann? Oh, dont worry, shes a top-of-the-top instructor, I know that. Weve just had a bit of a... bit of a difference on how we like to train our people, thats all.

char_265_sophia_CN_004.voiceText: Theres plenty at Rhodes Island packing personality AND strength, hm? You could pick your fancy, turn them into competition knights and grab everyone in there by the eyes... Mm, well, or maybe lets not stir that pot.

char_265_sophia_CN_005.voiceText: Doctor, can I borrow you? I just want you to help me carry some things. If youre asking, well... er, just... all sorts of random things I buy when the mood strikes me.

char_265_sophia_CN_006.voiceText: Oh, my injury...? Im not setting foot on that stage ever again, and Ive long since learned to get along with my right, so lets not worry yourself, okay. Or maybe youre just being polite, Doctor? Tiptoeing around saying I cant fight at operator standards?

char_265_sophia_CN_007.voiceText: Honestly, Maria. She runs away to the Engineering Department any time shes free. You get used to it fast. *Sigh* I wonder where her education gave her those ideas... Well! Compared to forcing herself to arm up and do what she doesnt want to, I think things are fine this way.

char_265_sophia_CN_008.voiceText: Hm? Hello, Doctor. No, Ive just been feeling a little empty. Margaret never wants fussing over, Marias found what shes wanted to do here, and what about me...? Oh, god, what am I doing talking to you about this? Dont you worry about me, let me make that clear.

char_265_sophia_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, we dont get along half bad, but you dont just lie there and leave it all up to me, not in your wildest dreams. I hate danger plenty, but layabouts leave another bad taste in my mouth. Though, when your backs against the wall... *cough* Well, we can talk about it then!

char_265_sophia_CN_010.voiceText: Someones easygoing, arent you? Well, I can let you rest for ten minutes or so.

char_265_sophia_CN_011.voiceText: Ahh, this is Rhodes Island, is it? Im Zofia the Whislash, then. As a former competition knight of Kazimierz, trust me when I say Ill whip your operators into shape.

char_265_sophia_CN_012.voiceText: These are ways of fighting Ive never even heard of before!

char_265_sophia_CN_013.voiceText: So this is a Rhodes Island promotion, then...? Why not. I dont pay much attention to my wages, but being compensated for my troubles isnt all that bad a feeling. Thank you.

char_265_sophia_CN_014.voiceText: Hmm, thinking about it carefully, the pays not bad, life is good enough here, and I get to see Maria and Margaret all the time. Staying here as an instructor sounds nice.

char_265_sophia_CN_017.voiceText: Lets take a look at how you all deploy.

char_265_sophia_CN_018.voiceText: Leave the team to me, then.

char_265_sophia_CN_019.voiceText: Turn up the heat! Were going out!

char_265_sophia_CN_020.voiceText: You havent forgotten what you need to do, right?

char_265_sophia_CN_029.voiceText: Really, I was going to have a word with you about taking such a dangerous mission, but seeing you tie things up so beautifully, Ill just let it slide...

char_265_sophia_CN_030.voiceText: A perfectionist, then... well, nothing wrong with that.

char_265_sophia_CN_031.voiceText: We won, and thats enough, no? Dont obsess over it.

char_265_sophia_CN_032.voiceText: Doctor, dont just stand there! Follow me!

char_423_blemsh_CN_001.voiceText: Though I wouldnt dare boast of my prowess with a sword or Originium Arts... If you ever have any problems with equipment maintenance, you can come talk to me!

char_423_blemsh_CN_002.voiceText: Zofia is my distant aunt, as well as my swordsmanship instructor. Its thanks to her that I can survive in the knight sports scene, but my aunt sometimes Gaah! I mean, my sister! Um, Doctor! Please dont tell her I let that slip, shes actually super sensitive about it!

char_423_blemsh_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor, to be honest, Im a much better craftsman than I am a knight! Whether its repairing an alarm clock or forging armor, I can help! Thats why, Doctor! Can you please take me to see Vulcans and Closures workshops? Pretty pleeease!

char_423_blemsh_CN_004.voiceText: Those two Sarkaz ladies seem hard to talk to, but if my sister trusts them so much, they must be pretty awesome. The Radiant Knight fighting alongside the Sarkaz for the sake of the Infected... Woahh, doesnt that sound like a breaking news headline?

char_423_blemsh_CN_005.voiceText: I actually never got an official title like my sisters Radiant Knight. Blemishine is the codename I chose for myself... But if I was to continue down the path of knighthood, maybe Blemishine wouldnt be a bad name.

char_423_blemsh_CN_006.voiceText: Kazimierzs knight sports are nothing more than a huge commercial game, and we all eat out of its palm... I didnt realize it until after I came to Rhodes Island, but Kazimierzs sickness might run deeper than the fact that weve strayed from our knightly traditions... much, much deeper.

char_423_blemsh_CN_007.voiceText: Rhodes Islands operators are way more like the ancient knights in the novels than the competition knights. In fact, Ive been pretty obsessed with these knight novels for a long time. Knights, enemies, adventures, and treasures. But anyone can get that stuff from knight sports, so theyre not as big as they used to be.

char_423_blemsh_CN_008.voiceText: When I first saw my sister after all this time, it was like she was a totally different person. Instead of that dazzling, blinding light she used to give off, she was more like the gentle sun, warm and stalwart. Did she change for Rhodes Island? Then I want to see for myself what my sister found here!

char_423_blemsh_CN_009.voiceText: I couldnt become a real knight, but maybe thats why I was able to see the wider world. I might be seeing things a bit more clearly now. To be a knight is to be the noble light that illuminates the land. Doctor, you will bear witness to my resolve.

char_423_blemsh_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor? Huh, you fell asleep? I wonder if you also have dreams~

char_423_blemsh_CN_011.voiceText: Kazimierz knight, codename Blemishine. Hehe, Ive heard all about you from my sister, Doctor. You can just call me Maria if you want~

char_423_blemsh_CN_012.voiceText: Wait, hold on... Ehhh? You can do it like that?

char_423_blemsh_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion...? For the glory of the Nearl family, Ill continue to give it my all!

char_423_blemsh_CN_014.voiceText: I just realized this, but its all older folks around me, and dont really have any friends around to ask... So, Doctor? What do you think about this equipment I made for myself? Pretty cool, yeah? Does it look good on me?

char_423_blemsh_CN_018.voiceText: S-squad leader? Me? But I dont have any experience with team battles...

char_423_blemsh_CN_020.voiceText: Our family motto is, fear neither hardship nor darkness!

char_423_blemsh_CN_029.voiceText: Small as it may be... our light persisted until the end!

char_423_blemsh_CN_030.voiceText: Each victory will become a light that illuminates the path forward. Good job, Doctor.

char_423_blemsh_CN_032.voiceText: Ill protect the wounded. Take the others and retreat, quickly!

char_423_blemsh_CN_033.voiceText: So this is the inside of Rhodes Island... Id sure love to see the schematics.

char_423_blemsh_CN_034.voiceText: Woah! D-dont scare me like that...

char_423_blemsh_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor! Shh! I snuck over here to hide from auntie Zofia. Hehe, let me take the day off!

char_1001_amiya2_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, what's wrong? Ah, I'm fine, just a little tired. Please check these two files in a moment. A lot of new Operators have joined Rhodes Island, and we can't disappoint them.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_002.voiceText: Rhodes Island and this world at large have already lost so much. We will put a stop to it... Rage may destroy us, but when confronting malice, ever more people have no other choice. Until the land finds peace, no one will be able to extinguish this fury.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_003.voiceText: My rings look different? I couldn't hide it from you, Doctor... You're right, one of them broke. But it's okay, Dr. Kal'tsit helped me switch it for a new one. Did... that have something to do with when I blacked out, you ask? Doctor

char_1001_amiya2_CN_004.voiceText: In this whole operation, we gained no commercial profit at all, and we even gave so much... But there are many things you can't weigh in terms of business value. Rhodes Island was never a company born exclusively for profit, and this land needs more than just physical medications.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_005.voiceText: Chernobog's Reunion... it's over, and is there any more point to denouncing what they've done? Think of the people who trampled them, abused them, massacred them... hatred breeds hatred. That was something that should've never happened in the first place.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_006.voiceText: Once, there was a Sarkaz betrayed, who walked the earth bent on vengeance, and finally cast his own life to the cycle of revenge. What I can't understand is, he'd already settled on his own end before he drew his sword. In rage, he was clear... and decided his death.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_007.voiceText: Death should be carved into our memories, never to be forgotten, no matter who brought that death about, nor who it was brought to. Our mistakes will never be right... those scars should always remind us, warn us how frail we are.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_008.voiceText: Even now, they still sometimes come to mind. Misha's gaze, FrostNova's roars, Patriot's cries... Ace, Scout, and so many operators sacrificed their lives for a single belief. But the Infected all across Terrawhat is it that they've died for?

char_1001_amiya2_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor... recently... have I been a little less like myself? The nameless anger that rises up, time and again... is that mine? If so... no, even if so, I won't give up. I will protect you, Doctor, by this sword.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, are you okay? Do you need to rest a little? I'll help carry you. Don't worry, I'm doing fine. So long as you're rested.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_011.voiceText: Doctor, it's so good to see you. My appearance? Um, please don't be afraid... I can explain this. But don't worry, Doctor. Whatever happens, I won't ever let you come to harm. I swear it.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_012.voiceText: "If the fight is unavoidable..." This is what the person I most trusted once taught me.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_018.voiceText: I shoulder the wrath of so many others.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_022.voiceText: This sword thirsts for revenge... I won't permit it.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_023.voiceText: My sword is cloaked in Chi Xiao's shadow.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_024.voiceText: Madam Ch'en's swordsmanship... flows within this weapon.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_026.voiceText: Your thought, your Arts, I can cut them.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_027.voiceText: "With what do I answer your failure of justice?"

char_1001_amiya2_CN_029.voiceText: Doctor, thank you for always supporting me. Our battles will only get harder from here, but we can't give up.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_030.voiceText: How long do we fight? How long until the flames of anger on Terra subside...

char_1001_amiya2_CN_031.voiceText: Doctor, good job. Let me handle the clean-up.

char_1001_amiya2_CN_033.voiceText: Phew... we can take a little breather now, right?

char_1001_amiya2_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, could you... hear me out for a bit? Is that okay?

char_311_mudrok_CN_001.voiceText: Hm? Ah, this soil... it can murmur. It can dance. It is my friend.

char_311_mudrok_CN_002.voiceText: Miss Closure told me I shouldn't walk about Rhodes Island "fully equipped"... but I'm not used to... revealing... myself. Sorry...

char_311_mudrok_CN_003.voiceText: Thank-you letters? Ah, from the Sarkaz workers yesterday? My equipment and type of Arts are a good match for physical work. Besides, their materials and fuel weren't featherweight. And they relied on the power of flesh and blood to ensure Rhodes Island sails smooth... it's incredible.

char_311_mudrok_CN_004.voiceText: That elite operator... I thought I'd seen enough bizarre Originium Arts in Leithania to write any wild fantasy. But the moment he pushed apart the fog with a wave of his hand, I understood, as a Sarkaz, he was young yet incredibly ancient.

char_311_mudrok_CN_005.voiceText: I often think of the soldiers and companions that have left us. Sometimes, I have a sort of delusion that even now, I'm still fleeing... Doctor, have you been to Kazdel before? That was where my journey started, and once, where I'd thought it would end.

char_311_mudrok_CN_006.voiceText: Dr. Kal'tsit, huh... She startled me, but she's reassuring in spades... One thing, though. Rhodes Island seems to get along well with another mercenary group, too. Could you tell me about them, Doctor? It's best I don't know? I see... then I think I can more or less guess who.

char_311_mudrok_CN_007.voiceText: I became a Rhodes Island Operator so they could be treated properly, live on properly, and only then would those warriors... have died with meaning. But... since coming to Rhodes Island, I've seen clearly what I, myself, am truly fighting for. That was a first for me.

char_311_mudrok_CN_008.voiceText: Me, alone, talking to a clay doll...? You're... you're telling you saw me? That was just a kind of ceremony... huh? So everyone already knew? Really? Then I'll be more careful next time, do it late when nobody's up... um, I shouldn't?

char_311_mudrok_CN_009.voiceText: From Kazdel to Leithania, so many marks have been carved onto the suffering. The moment they had no choice but to fight, I realized I had nothing at all. How do you see me, Doctor? You trust me? Will that trust... allow me to live on?

char_311_mudrok_CN_010.voiceText: ...The person napping there is the Doctor. Remember that well. Our road together is sure to be long and far.

char_311_mudrok_CN_011.voiceText: Sarkaz mercenary, Mudrock... You're the Doctor, then. Rhodes Island has saved me many times, and now, I'd like you to let me return the favor.

char_311_mudrok_CN_012.voiceText: I've had a taste of how Rhodes Island fights before, but, well, this still makes a great reference...

char_311_mudrok_CN_013.voiceText: I used to be known as Reunion, and then under the Mudrock Squad, and now... I've been promoted by my former enemy. Is this what they meant by "life is a rollercoaster?"

char_311_mudrok_CN_014.voiceText: Hm? This seems fresh? I never take my helmet off in battle, after all... There's a lot of reasons why, but things have changed now. S... staying like this? If I have to...

char_311_mudrok_CN_017.voiceText: I'm simply a Rhodes Island Operator, now. I'll obey your command.

char_311_mudrok_CN_018.voiceText: The captain... I don't like leading, but... I'm used to it.

char_311_mudrok_CN_025.voiceText: The land is as my friend.

char_311_mudrok_CN_029.voiceText: Running is useless... resist it, even if you are not willing to resist. This is the only way I've come to know to face suffering.

char_311_mudrok_CN_030.voiceText: My friends are whispering their celebration. They cheer our victory, Doctor.

char_311_mudrok_CN_031.voiceText: Chase them... I'll watch over the battlefield with my friends' eyes.

char_311_mudrok_CN_032.voiceText: It's not the first I've fled with my back to the enemy. If even more can live on this way... I'll cover your backs.

char_311_mudrok_CN_033.voiceText: The ceiling's... a little lower than I imagined.

char_311_mudrok_CN_034.voiceText: ...Mm? Did you touch me just now?

char_311_mudrok_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor? Could you stay with me for a bit? I'd like... to ask you a little about Kazdel. Ah, and my friends have missed you, too.

char_391_rosmon_CN_001.voiceText: Umm, Doctor... I'm not very good at filing and writing reports. Do you think you can assign me to another position? Eh? I don't need to do anything. All I need to do is hang out here? Doctor... You're a weirdo.

char_391_rosmon_CN_002.voiceText: Everyone at Rhodes Island is my friend. The elite operators and my squad mates are my family. Ms. Kal'tsit doesn't want me to treat them as family. I didn't get it at first, but I do now. They're like flowers in a vase. If you don't pay attention to them, they'll wither. But they're all I have.

char_391_rosmon_CN_003.voiceText: What am I reading? Oh, it's an entry from two days ago. Closure spilled her coffee that morning and stained a couple scrolls in the library. And she got cursed, I think. For every five words she says, she ends up spitting on someone's face. Scary, isn't it?

char_391_rosmon_CN_004.voiceText: Painful things, sad things, and scary things all go away when you least expect them to. But it's not okay to forget them. I need to remember them, because those emotions are still there inside me. I don't want to end up crying without knowing why. Memories are a burden, and I have to carry my own burden.

char_391_rosmon_CN_005.voiceText: I can't use a shield, I can't use a bow, I can't make guns glow, and I can't turn those iron rods into weapons very well. More importantly, the other elite operators are much warmer than me. This warmth is what helps them fight for everyone else and for what's right. I will do my best.

char_391_rosmon_CN_006.voiceText: Ms. Kal'tsit has lost lots of family, right? I see it in her eyes. How does she keep it to herself and manage to live with it? Just thinking about how everyone will disappear eventually one after another is enough to make my heart ache. Like it's going to explode. Is it because she's a grown-up? Then I want to grow up soon.

char_391_rosmon_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, could you tell me what this word means? I asked Blaze about it, and she just kept giggling, and Amiya just kept hitting her. Oh, it means kissing? I know what that is, then. Doctor, bend down a little, okay? Can I kiss you on the cheek? Thanks for always taking care of us. Meow.

char_391_rosmon_CN_008.voiceText: I won't forget about those people. They created me and those monsters. They wanted to use us to do bad things. Before the world finally stops hurting us all... I'll punish these people. I will make it really, really hurt, so they never, ever forget.

char_391_rosmon_CN_009.voiceText: Oh... You're the Doctor, right? I went over the records on the terminal just yesterday. Yep, I remember now, Doctor. You can give me orders. Let's go on a mission? Make sure to use my powers well.

char_391_rosmon_CN_010.voiceText: Hmm... the Doctor is taking a nap. Looks restless, too. Must be tired. If I give the Doctor a hug, it should feel a little better, right? Just relax and sleep well. I know how it feels... It hurts even in your dreams, right? I can tell.

char_391_rosmon_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, Doctor. I am Elite Operator Rosmontis. Ms. Kal'tsit has given her permission. You can give me and my team orders now. Use my power where it matters, Doctor. I also tend to forget about things pretty easily. Be sure to remind me if it looks like I might forget something.

char_391_rosmon_CN_012.voiceText: Yeah... I got that down now. I can use this in battle.

char_391_rosmon_CN_013.voiceText: I asked Ms. Kal'tsit why I'm an elite operator. Lots of people talk behind my back. They say I'm not right for the job. Ms. Kal'tsit said that if I become an elite operator, I'll remember more, and I'll become a better person. Yep, I'm doing my best.

char_391_rosmon_CN_014.voiceText: This world isn't going to get better so easily, but humans tend to get worse because of their surroundings. Doctor, we can't turn into bad people. If you do, I am sure you'll be really, really bad. I won't let you turn out like that.

char_391_rosmon_CN_017.voiceText: Time for a mission? Yeah, I know. I will protect all of Rhodes Island's operators. I promise.

char_391_rosmon_CN_018.voiceText: I am the leader? Don't worry. They may not be from my team, but I'll make sure their support doesn't go to waste.

char_391_rosmon_CN_019.voiceText: Don't worry. I know how to control my Arts.

char_391_rosmon_CN_020.voiceText: I don't want to see my family get hurt. I will destroy everything that could hurt my family.

char_391_rosmon_CN_022.voiceText: Give me your order. I will see it through.

char_391_rosmon_CN_024.voiceText: Stand back. If you don't want to see what's about to happen, don't look.

char_391_rosmon_CN_025.voiceText: If it hurts, just cry out. It'll feel better.

char_391_rosmon_CN_026.voiceText: If you surrender now, I won't hurt you.

char_391_rosmon_CN_027.voiceText: You won't die... I'll make sure you don't die.

char_391_rosmon_CN_028.voiceText: There are things that have to be done by someone. There are things that only I can do.

char_391_rosmon_CN_029.voiceText: If there comes a day when I can't use these Arts again... Hmm. What will that day be like? I can't imagine.

char_391_rosmon_CN_030.voiceText: That was very nice, Doctor. There, there. Thanks.

char_391_rosmon_CN_031.voiceText: I will take care of the rest. It won't take long.

char_391_rosmon_CN_032.voiceText: No... I won't retreat. I can't disappoint the others. I still have my sword... Even without my sword, I can still fight! I won't leave!

char_391_rosmon_CN_033.voiceText: P-Please don't lock me in a small room. They're scary... I... I don't really like those kinda rooms.

char_391_rosmon_CN_036.voiceText: Um... I-I'll try to bear with it... and not break your hand...

char_436_whispr_CN_001.voiceText: Please, leave all these reports to me. Being able to handle text-related work makes me very happy...

char_436_whispr_CN_002.voiceText: I wonder if I shouldn't have turned that Suzuran girl down just now?  But she said I'd be drinking tea with everyone, and I'm not too good with those sorts of things.

char_436_whispr_CN_003.voiceText: My body is more frail than most others.  I may easily die, forget all that happened, then come to be young, and born anew.  "Rejuvenation"... what a cruel fate it is...

char_436_whispr_CN_004.voiceText: All memories become foam on the waves in the end. Whether suffering, happiness, inevitably, quietly, pasts I do not want to forget will shed themselves from my side.

char_436_whispr_CN_005.voiceText: I no longer can remember it, but there is still something flowing within my blood.  Be careful of the sea, Doctor. It is capable of devouring us all, a stygian nightmare. It is... fear itself.

char_436_whispr_CN_006.voiceText: There are times I become curious. For races with true longevity like Miss Warfarin's, how do they view death and parting?  If such things no longer cause them to suffer, is it only because they long since hurt, until they were used to it... until they were numbed?

char_436_whispr_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, could you take these flowers to the children being treated, for me? Yes, just like always, place them by their bedsides.  ...Thank you, for helping keep this secret.

char_436_whispr_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, come quickly, we need to find Miss Closure! It seems Mr. Thorns and his companions burst a water pipe open in the corridor, and it's provoked Weedy's interminable wrath!  I'm soaked to the skin... Um, I seemlike I'm enjoying myself? Wh-What do you mean?!

char_436_whispr_CN_009.voiceText: Every time I watch a film, I'll keep the ticket stub afterwards. Even if I've forgotten all its contents, these leftover vestiges will always serve as a reminder to me.  ...Doctor, could you come watch a film with me? I'd like to preserve the time I've passed with you, too.

char_436_whispr_CN_010.voiceText: Sleep sound, now. *chuckle* By the time you wake, will you have forgotten about me?

char_436_whispr_CN_011.voiceText: My code name is Whisperainbut I'm a mere roving doctor. If possible, treat me like a traveler lodging under the eaves, away from the rain. You needn't pay me much mind...

char_436_whispr_CN_012.voiceText: In the face of such fierce combat, I worry... I wouldn't survive.

char_436_whispr_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you very much. But I hope you treat me same as always

char_436_whispr_CN_014.voiceText: Those sorrows I could not wash away with one deathI always feel they're like strands, wisps, winding about my skin... Doctor, you've come to forget the past toocould you maybe understand this feeling?

char_436_whispr_CN_017.voiceText: Please leave the assistive work to me.

char_436_whispr_CN_019.voiceText: Please keep with me. Don't go too far.

char_436_whispr_CN_020.voiceText: Please, everyone, be careful. You must keep yourselves safe.

char_436_whispr_CN_028.voiceText: I know this scent of death well.

char_436_whispr_CN_029.voiceText: Sleep, now. May all dream well in the sound of rainfall.

char_436_whispr_CN_030.voiceText: This is how their story ends. One tragedy, following another...

char_436_whispr_CN_031.voiceText: Leave the pursuit for later. Please let me treat everyone first.

char_436_whispr_CN_032.voiceText: I'm sorry, I've been such a burden on everyone...

char_436_whispr_CN_033.voiceText: Such a peaceful place this is. I can hear the patter of rainfall.

char_436_whispr_CN_036.voiceText: Pplease don't move! My hair's gotten tangled...

char_436_whispr_CN_042.voiceText: What will we be doing today, Doctor?

char_347_jaksel_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor, you've been sitting there for a while, that's really unhealthy. Come do some stretches with me! Exercise and recover your energy. That way, you'll be able to work better.

char_347_jaksel_CN_003.voiceText: Doctor, Doctor! She's here at Rhodes Island! Ah, her codename should be Dur-nar now. Anyway, she's really amazing! I've only ever seen her in recruitment ads before! She's also a really good person! She gave me so many snacks, ehehe.

char_347_jaksel_CN_004.voiceText: Doctor, I'm actually pretty lithe for my age, you know. Let me show you a standing backflip! Watch!

char_347_jaksel_CN_005.voiceText: This gun? Oh, it's a gun-type Arts... Arts something. Ah, right, Arts Unit! I applied for one out of habit when I came here, but I still prefer my fists over Arts.

char_347_jaksel_CN_006.voiceText: Even though I know I'm very lucky, I only realized how badly other Infected are doing after coming to Rhodes Island... Doctor, what can I do to help? I really want to help them!

char_347_jaksel_CN_007.voiceText: ...Hm? Ah, Doctor! I'm writing a letter to my dad. Eh, I haven't introduced my dad to you yet? He's a really amazing policeman, you know! Let me tell you how great he is!

char_347_jaksel_CN_008.voiceText: Actually, it was my dad who suggested Rhodes Island. After he found out you could treat Oripathy, he pushed really hard for me to be able to come here. I don't really want to be away from him, but I know that he'll be happiest if I live a healthy life.

char_347_jaksel_CN_009.voiceText: You're really reliable, although dad is still better. Yup, you're now the second most reliable person in my heart! Hehe. Ah, Doctor, I talked a lot about you in my letters to dad. He said he really wants to meet you!

char_347_jaksel_CN_010.voiceText: Doc! Ah, Doctor's asleep. I'll have to be quieter...

char_347_jaksel_CN_011.voiceText: Nice to meet you, Doctor! I'm the new operator, codename Jackie! I used to be an auxiliary police officer in Columbia. Let's get along!

char_347_jaksel_CN_012.voiceText: Amazing... It feels even more amazing than dad...

char_347_jaksel_CN_013.voiceText: Eh, am I being promoted? Wow, that's great!

char_347_jaksel_CN_014.voiceText: I've learnt a lot living at Rhodes Island... Maybe I can even catch up to dad one day! Doctor, I'll continue to work hard. Please guide me well~

char_347_jaksel_CN_024.voiceText: Time for me to show my power!

char_347_jaksel_CN_028.voiceText: I'll do it in one go!

char_347_jaksel_CN_029.voiceText: I thought we were gonna lose a few time, but we actually won in the end. Doctor, you're amazing!

char_347_jaksel_CN_031.voiceText: Doctor, want me to chase after them?

char_347_jaksel_CN_032.voiceText: Sorry, Doctor. If only I'd put in more effort...

char_264_f12yin_CN_001.voiceText: It's a good thing to be alert, Doctor. Well, please continue with your work. Rest assured, I'm here to protect you.

char_264_f12yin_CN_002.voiceText: I've met plenty of people who claim to practice martial arts, but they are all just weaklings putting up a front. Not that girl, Waai Fu, however.
